          but each satisfied the other.    "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "She replied, \u201CWhy would a Jewish man ask a Samaritan woman for
        a drink of water?\u201D (For Jews have no dealings with Samaritans.)"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CIf you only knew who I am and the gift
        that God wants to give you, you\u2019d ask me for a drink, and I would give
        you living water.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The woman replied, \u201CBut sir, [[COMMENT(0)]] you don\u2019t even
        have a bucket, and the well is very deep. So where do you find this \u2018living
        water\u2019? "
      comments:
      - number: 4:11
        content: "  The woman used the Greek title    (\u201Clord\u201D) when she
          addressed Jesus. However,    is not a word used here for \u201Cexalted
          or sovereign Lord,\u201D but more like \u201Csir.\u201D    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Do you really think that you are greater than our ancestor Jacob
        who dug this well and drank from it himself, along with his children and
        livestock?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Jesus answered, <JESUS>\u201CIf you drink from Jacob\u2019s well,
        you\u2019ll be thirsty again,</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "<JESUS>but if anyone drinks the living water I give them, they will
        never be thirsty again. For when you drink the water I give you, it becomes
        a gushing fountain</JESUS>  <JESUS>of the Holy Spirit</JESUS><JESUS>, flooding
        you with endless life!\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 4:14
        content: "  The Greek verb for \u201Cspringing up\u201D is  , and is never
          used for inanimate objects (water). It is a verb used for people (living
          things) and means \u201Cjumping\u201D or \u201Cleaping up.\u201D The Septuagint
          translates this verb elsewhere as an activity of the Holy Spirit.    "
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The woman replied, \u201CLet me drink that water so I\u2019ll never
        be thirsty again and won\u2019t have to come back here to draw water.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CGo get your husband and bring him back here.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CBut I\u2019m not married,\u201D the woman answered.<JESUS>\u201CThat\u2019s
        true,\u201D</JESUS> Jesus said, "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "<JESUS>\u201Cfor you\u2019ve been married five times,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>and now you\u2019re living with a man who is not your husband. You
        have told the truth.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 4:18
        content: '  In a sense, every one of us has married five husbands: our five
          senses. The six men speak of our fallen humanity, for six is the number
          of man (who was created on the sixth day). Our heart can never be satisfied
          with what is on this earth; we must drink the living water that comes from
          heaven. Christ is the seventh husband, the only One who satisfies. Christ
          is the real husband. See  .      After offering the woman living water,
          Jesus first confronted her with her sin and steered her away from religious
          debates (the proper place to worship, v.  ), and unveiled himself to her
          as the true Messiah. Jesus does the same thing to everyone who comes to
          him.    '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "The woman changed the subject. \u201CYou must be a prophet! "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So tell me this: Why do our fathers worship God on this nearby mountain,
        [[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>  </smallcaps> but your people teach that Jerusalem
        is the place where we must worship. Who is right?\u201DJesus responded, "
      comments:
      - number: 4:20
        content: "  This \u201Cnearby mountain\u201D is most likely Mount Gerizim
          where the Samaritans had a shrine to worship God. However, Jacob\u2019s
          well lies at the base of Mount Ebal, the mountain that  told the Levites
          to curse. See  ;  . Both Gerizim and Ebal are mountains in Samaria.    "
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CBelieve me, dear woman, the time has come when you will
        worship</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>the Father neither on a mountain
        nor in Jerusalem,</JESUS>  <JESUS>but in your heart.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 4:21
        content: "  The Aramaic word for \u201Cworship,\u201D  , means \u201Cto bow
          down\u201D or \u201Cto surrender.\u201D    "
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "<JESUS>Your people don\u2019t really know the One they worship, but
        we Jews worship out of our experience, for it\u2019s from the Jews that salvation
        is available.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 4:22
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe life-givers are from the Jews.\u201D    "
    - name: '23-24: '
      title: 
      number: 23-24
      content: "<JESUS>From now on, worshiping the Father will not be a matter of
        the right place but with a right heart. For God is a Spirit,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>and he longs to have sincere worshipers who adore him in the realm
        of the Spirit and in truth.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: "4:23\u201324"
        content: "  Or \u201CGod is breath\u201D or \u201CGod is wind.\u201D Jesus
          referred to \u201CSpirit\u201D more than one hundred times in the four
          Gospels.    "
    - name: '23-24: '
      title: 
      number: 23-24
      content: "<JESUS>From now on, worshiping the Father will not be a matter of
        the right place but with a right heart. For God is a Spirit,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>and he longs to have sincere worshipers who adore him in the realm
        of the Spirit and in truth.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: "4:23\u201324"
        content: "  Or \u201CGod is breath\u201D or \u201CGod is wind.\u201D Jesus
          referred to \u201CSpirit\u201D more than one hundred times in the four
          Gospels.    "
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "The woman said, \u201CThis is all so confusing, but I do know that
        the Anointed One is coming\u2014the true Messiah. And when he comes, he will
        tell us everything we need to know.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Jesus said to her, <JESUS>\u201CYou don\u2019t have to wait any longer,
        the Anointed One is here speaking with you\u2014I am the One you\u2019re
        looking for.\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 4:26
        content: "  Or \u201CI am the I AM who speaks to you.\u201D    "
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'At that moment, his disciples returned and were stunned to see Jesus
        speaking with a Samaritan woman, yet none of them dared ask him why or what
        they were discussing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'All at once, the woman left her water jar and ran off to her village
        and told everyone, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CCome and meet a man at the well who told me everything I\u2019ve
        ever done! [[COMMENT(0)]] He could be the One we\u2019ve been waiting for.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: 4:29
        content: '  No doubt, this woman was the talk of the town. Having had five
          marriages, she was well known for what she had done. For her to say these
          words was an honest confession of her past. The miracle here is that the
          people believed her and went out to see for themselves.    '
    - name: '30: The Harvest Is Ready'
      title: The Harvest Is Ready
      number: 30
      content: Hearing this, the people came streaming out of the village to go see
        Jesus. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 4:30
        content: "  Although unnamed in the biblical account, church tradition identifies
          the Samaritan woman to be Photini. An internet search of her name will
          yield many interesting stories about her post-conversion ministry, including
          her being named as an \u201Capostle\u201D of Jesus and her eventual martyrdom.
          Regardless of the validity of the extrabiblical references, history records
          her as the first New Testament evangelist to win a city to Christ. God
          is faithful to use anyone to reach others when we are honest to tell others
          that Jesus knows everything we\u2019ve ever done and still loves us.    "
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then the disciples began to insist that Jesus eat some of the food
        they brought back with them, saying, \u201CTeacher, you must eat something.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "But Jesus told them, <JESUS>\u201CI have eaten a meal</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>you don\u2019t know about.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 4:32
        content: "  There is a fascinating word play here in the Aramaic. The word
          Jesus used isn\u2019t the common word for \u201Cfood,\u201D but a specific
          word that means \u201Cnutrients.\u201D It also has a homonym more commonly
          translated \u201Ckingdom.\u201D Jesus has a kingdom feast that no one else
          knows about. He feasts upon the devotion of his bride. See  ;  . The church
          is truly the \u201Cwoman at the well.\u201D    "
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Puzzled by this, the disciples began to discuss it among themselves,
        \u201CDid someone already bring him food?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "To clarify, Jesus spoke up and said, <JESUS>\u201CMy food is to do
        the will of him who sent me and bring it to completion.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "As the crowds emerged from the village, Jesus said to his disciples,
        <JESUS>\u201CWhy would you say, \u2018The harvest is another four months
        away\u2019? Look at all the people coming\u2014now is harvest time! Their
        hearts are like vast fields of ripened grain\u2014ready for a harvest.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: '<JESUS>Everyone who reaps these souls for eternal life will receive
        a reward. Both those who plant</JESUS>  <JESUS>spiritual</JESUS>  <JESUS>seeds
        and those who reap the</JESUS>  <JESUS>spiritual</JESUS>  <JESUS>harvest
        will celebrate together with great joy!</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "<JESUS>And this confirms the saying, \u2018One sows the seed and
        another reaps the harvest.\u2019</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 4:37
        content: '  See  ;  .    '
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "<JESUS>I have sent you out to harvest a field that you haven\u2019t
        planted, where many others have labored long and hard before you.</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>And now you are privileged to profit from their labors
        and reap the harvest.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 4:38
        content: '  See  ;  .    '
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Many from the Samaritan village became believers in Jesus because
        of the woman\u2019s testimony: \u201CHe told me everything I ever did!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Then they begged Jesus to stay with them, so he stayed there for
        two days, '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: resulting in many more coming to faith in him because of his message.
      comments: []
    - name: '42: Jesus Returns to Galilee'
      title: Jesus Returns to Galilee
      number: 42
      content: "The Samaritans said to the woman, \u201CNow we\u2019ve heard him
        ourselves. We no longer believe just because of what you told us, but we\u2019re
        convinced that he really is the true Savior of the world!\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 4:42
        content: "  They acknowledged Jesus not just as the Messiah, but the \u201CSavior
          of the world,\u201D including the Samaritan people who were outcasts from
          Judaism. The word    in Aramaic is literally translated \u201CLife-Giver.\u201D    "
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'On the third day Jesus left there and continued his journey to Galilee,
        where he had been raised. [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 4:43
        content: '  See v.  .    '
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Now Jesus knew that prophets are honored everywhere except in their
        own hometown. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: Even so, as Jesus arrived in the province of Galilee, the people welcomed
        him with open arms. Many of them had been in Jerusalem during the Passover
        Festival and had witnessed firsthand the miracles he had performed. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 4:45
        content: '  See  .    '
    - name: '46-47: '
      title: 
      number: 46-47
      content: "Jesus entered the village of Cana of Galilee where he had transformed
        water into wine. He met there a governmental official from Capernaum whose
        son was very sick and dying. When he heard that Jesus had left Judea and
        was staying in Cana of Galilee, he decided to make the journey to Cana. [[COMMENT(0)]]
        When he found Jesus, he begged him, \u201CYou must come with me to Capernaum
        and heal my son!\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: "4:46\u201347"
        content: '  The distance from Capernaum to Cana was over seventeen miles.    '
    - name: '46-47: '
      title: 
      number: 46-47
      content: "Jesus entered the village of Cana of Galilee where he had transformed
        water into wine. He met there a governmental official from Capernaum whose
        son was very sick and dying. When he heard that Jesus had left Judea and
        was staying in Cana of Galilee, he decided to make the journey to Cana. [[COMMENT(0)]]
        When he found Jesus, he begged him, \u201CYou must come with me to Capernaum
        and heal my son!\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: "4:46\u201347"
        content: '  The distance from Capernaum to Cana was over seventeen miles.    '
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "So Jesus said to him, <JESUS>\u201CYou</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>never
        believe unless you see signs and wonders.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 4:48
        content: "  Or \u201CYou all.\u201D      The Samaritans believed without
          seeing miracles. See  .    "
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "But the man continued to plead, \u201CCome with me to Capernaum before
        my little boy dies!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "Jesus looked him in the eyes and said, <JESUS>\u201CGo back home
        now. I promise you, your son will live.\u201D</JESUS>The man believed in
        his heart the words of Jesus and set off for home. "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "When he was still a distance from Capernaum, his servants met him
        on the road and told him the good news, \u201CYour son is healed! He\u2019s
        alive!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "Overjoyed, the father asked his servants, \u201CWhen did my son begin
        to recover?\u201D\u201CYesterday,\u201D they said, \u201Cat one in the afternoon.
        All at once his fever broke\u2014and now he\u2019s well!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: "Then the father immediately realized that it was at that very same
        hour that Jesus spoke the words to him, <JESUS>\u201CYour son will live.\u201D</JESUS>
        From that day forward, the man, his servants, and all his family believed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: "Healing the official\u2019s son was Jesus\u2019 second extraordinary
        miracle in Galilee after returning from Judea. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 4:54
        content: "  There is an interesting parallel in Jesus\u2019 ministry in John
          with  . Jesus began first in Jerusalem (Nicodemus\u2014), then went to
          Judea (), then to Samaria (the Samaritan woman\u2014), and then to the
          people with no Jewish heritage (the healing of the nobleman\u2019s son,
          a gentile\u2014).  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Healing at Bethesda'
      title: The Healing at Bethesda
      number: 1
      content: 'From Galilee, Jesus returned to Jerusalem to observe one of the Jewish
        feasts. [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 5:1
        content: '  It is difficult to determine with certainty which of the feasts
          it was: Passover, Tabernacles, or Purim. Most of the ancient expositors
          taught that it was the Feast of Pentecost. There is no mention of the disciples
          being with him at this time.    '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Inside the city, near the Sheep Gate, [[COMMENT(0)]] there is  a
        pool called in Aramaic, The House of Loving Kindness,  surrounded by five
        covered porches.   '
      comments:
      - number: 5:2
        content: "  Literally \u201Cthe place of the sheep.\u201D The word    is
          not in the Greek text. The sick gathered at the pool were like bruised,
          wounded sheep, needing healing.      The present tense    here in the text
          indicates that when John wrote his Gospel, the pool of Bethesda was still
          there. However, by AD 68\u201370, Jerusalem had been destroyed, along with
          the temple, by the Roman invasion. This would indicate John\u2019s Gospel
          has an earlier date of origin than believed. It is likely that John wrote
          his gospel prior to AD 67.      Or Bethesda. In Hebrew,  , meaning \u201CHouse
          of Loving Kindness.\u201D The spelling of this varies from manuscript to
          manuscript. Some have \u201CBethsaida,\u201D or \u201CBethsatha,\u201D
          or \u201CBelzetha (House of the Olive).\u201D Archaeologists have discovered
          a deep double pool near St. Anne\u2019s Church in Jerusalem surrounded
          by five porticoes located near the Sheep Gate, confirming the validity
          of the biblical account. The Sheep Gate is where the sacrificial animals
          were brought into the temple. This points us to the Lamb of God whose cross
          and sacrifice brought us healing. There is a pool of mercy near the Sheep
          Gate.      Or \u201Ccovered walkways\u201D or \u201Calcoves.\u201D The
          sick were under the \u201Ccovering\u201D of the Law (the five books of
          the Torah). But the Law cannot heal; it wounds and brings death (). Christ
          is the healer, the living Torah ().    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Hundreds of sick people were lying under the covered porches\u2014the
        paralyzed, the blind, and the crippled\u2014all of them waiting for their
        healing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: For an angel of God periodically descended into the pool to stir the
        waters, and the first one who stepped into the pool after the waters swirled
        would instantly be healed. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 5:4
        content: '  The majority of manuscripts do not have v.  , and a few Greek
          manuscripts do not even have v.  . However, the absence of the data found
          in these verses would leave a tremendous gap in the narrative, leaving
          unanswered why all these sick people would have congregated at the pool
          of Bethesda, and making v.    very confusing. There remains a strong basis
          found in a diverse set of manuscripts, both Greek and Aramaic, to argue
          for the inclusion of vv.    and    here.    '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Among the many sick people lying there was a man who had been disabled
        for thirty-eight years. [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 5:5
        content: "  Under the shelter of religion, there are the sick and lame and
          blind who can\u2019t be healed unless they do the work and step into the
          pool. They are helpless and hopeless so near the Sheep Gate. But Jesus
          puts none of the law\u2019s requirements upon us for our healing, only
          to believe in one who is greater than angels (). The man had been sick
          for thirty-eight years, the length of time Israel had wandered in the wilderness.
          See  .    "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "When Jesus saw him lying there, he knew that the man had been crippled
        for a long time. [[COMMENT(0)]] Jesus said to him, <JESUS>\u201CDo you truly
        long to be well?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 5:6
        content: "  Jesus knew by divine revelation this man\u2019s situation.     
          Or \u201CAre you convinced that you are already made whole?\u201D The Greek
          phrase    is actually not a future tense (\u201Cwant to be healed\u201D)
          but an aorist middle infinitive that indicates something already accomplished.
          Jesus was asking the crippled man if he was ready to abandon how he saw
          himself and now receive the faith for his healing ().    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The sick man answered, \u201CSir, [[COMMENT(0)]] there\u2019s no
        way I can get healed, for I have no one to lower me into the water when the
        angel comes. As soon as I try to crawl to the edge of the pool, someone else
        jumps in ahead of me.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 5:7
        content: "  The Greek word    means \u201Clord\u201D or \u201Csir.\u201D    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Jesus said to him, <JESUS>\u201CStand up! Pick up your sleeping mat
        and you will walk!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Immediately he stood up\u2014he was healed! So he rolled up his mat
        and walked again! Now Jesus worked this miracle on the Sabbath. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 5:9
        content: "  The healed man took his sleeping (resting) mat with him. The
          Sabbath was meant to be a day of rest, but the healed man carried his Sabbath
          \u201Crest\u201D with him. The Sabbath is not a day, but a realm of rest
          that we carry in our hearts.    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "When the Jewish leaders saw the man walking along carrying his sleeping
        mat, [[COMMENT(0)]] they objected and said, \u201CWhat are you doing carrying
        that? Don\u2019t you know it\u2019s the Sabbath? It\u2019s not lawful for
        you to carry things on the Sabbath!\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 5:10
        content: "  Or \u201Ccot\u201D or \u201Cstretcher.\u201D The Aramaic word
          is \u201Cquilt\u201D or \u201Cmat.\u201D    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "He answered them, \u201CThe man who healed me told me to pick it
        up and walk.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CWhat man?\u201D they asked him. \u201CWho was this man who
        ordered you to carry something on a Sabbath?\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 5:12
        content: "  Malice filled the Jewish leaders. They should have been filled
          with joy that the man was healed. They should have asked, \u201CWho is
          the wonderful one who healed you?\u201D    "
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But the healed man couldn\u2019t give them an answer, for he didn\u2019t
        yet know who it was, since Jesus had already slipped away into the crowd."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "A short time later, Jesus found the man at the temple and said to
        him, <JESUS>\u201CLook at you now! You\u2019re healed! Walk away from your
        sin</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>so that nothing worse will happen to
        you.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 5:14
        content: "  Or \u201CDon\u2019t continue sinning any longer.\u201D    "
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then the man went to the Jewish leaders to inform them, \u201CIt
        was Jesus who healed me!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Jesus Responds to the Jewish Leaders'
      title: Jesus Responds to the Jewish Leaders
      number: 16
      content: From that day forward the Jewish leaders began to persecute Jesus
        because of the things he did on the Sabbath.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Jesus answered his critics by saying, <JESUS>\u201CEvery day my Father
        is at work, and I will be, too!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "This infuriated them and made them all the more eager to devise a
        plan to kill him. For not only did he break their Sabbath rules, [[COMMENT(0)]]
        but he also called God <JESUS>\u201Cmy Father,\u201D</JESUS> which made him
        equal to God. "
      comments:
      - number: 5:18
        content: "  Jesus did not break the Sabbath, he \u201Cloosed\u201D it (literal
          Aramaic) from the bondage of tradition and man-made rules.      They clearly
          understood that Jesus was claiming God as his Father in a unique way.    "
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CI speak to you eternal truth. The Son
        is unable to do anything from himself or through his own initiative. I only
        do the works that I see the Father doing, for the Son does the same works
        as his Father.</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CBecause the Father loves his Son so much, he always
        reveals to him everything that he is about to do. And you will all be amazed
        when he shows him even greater works than what you\u2019ve seen so far!</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: <JESUS>For just as the Father has power to raise the dead, the Son
        will also raise the dead and give life to whomever he wants.</JESUS>
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThe Father judges no one, for he has given to the Son
        all the authority to judge.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: <JESUS>Therefore, the honor that belongs to the Father he will now
        share with his Son. So if you refuse to honor the Son, you are refusing to
        honor the Father who sent him.</JESUS>
      comments: []
    - name: '24: Two Resurrections'
      title: Two Resurrections
      number: 24
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CI speak to you an eternal truth: if you embrace my message
        and believe in the One who sent me, you will never face condemnation. In
        me, you have already passed from the realm of death into eternal life!\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CI speak to you an eternal truth: Soon the dead will
        hear the voice of the Son of God, and those who listen will arise with life!</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: '<JESUS>For as the Father is the source of life, so he has given the
        Son the power to impart life.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: <JESUS>The Father has transferred to the Son the authority to judge,
        because he is the Son of Man.</JESUS>
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CDon\u2019t be amazed when I tell you these things, for
        there is a day coming when everyone who has ever died will hear my voice</JESUS> 
        <JESUS>calling them back to life,</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: <JESUS>and they will come out of their graves! Those who have done
        what is good will experience a resurrection to eternal life. And those who
        have practiced evil will taste the resurrection of judgment!</JESUS>
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CNothing I do is from my own initiative. As I hear the
        judgment passed by my Father, I execute those judgments. And my judgments
        will be perfect, because I seek only to fulfill the desires of my Father
        who sent me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: '<JESUS>If I were to make claims about myself, you would have reasons
        to doubt.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 5:31
        content: "  According to the Mosaic laws, a man\u2019s testimony about himself
          is inadmissible. See  .    "
    - name: '32: John the Baptizer'
      title: John the Baptizer
      number: 32
      content: "<JESUS>But there is another</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>who bears
        witness on my behalf, and I know that what he testifies of me is true.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 5:32
        content: '  This is the Father (see v.  ). Some believe it to be John because
          of v.  . However, Jesus states that he does not need human validation.    '
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CYou have sent messengers to John, and what he testified</JESUS> 
        <JESUS>about me</JESUS>  <JESUS>is true.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "<JESUS>I have no need to be validated by men, but I\u2019m explaining
        these things so that you will</JESUS>  <JESUS>believe</JESUS>  <JESUS>and
        be saved.</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CJohn was a blazing, shining torch,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>and for a short time, you basked in his light with great joy.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 5:35
        content: "  Or \u201Ca lantern of chasing flames.\u201D    "
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "<JESUS>But I can provide more substantial proof of who I am that
        exceeds John\u2019s testimony\u2014my miracles! These works which the Father
        destined for me to complete\u2014they prove that the Father has sent me!</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: '<JESUS>And my Father himself, who gave me this mission, has also
        testified that I am his Son.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>But you have
        never heard his voice nor seen his form,</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: 5:37
        content: "  Or \u201Ctestified about me.\u201D Jesus was referring to the
          audible voice that God the Father spoke over Jesus at his baptism. For
          this reason and the reference to God\u2019s voice, this translation has
          chosen to make it explicit that it refers to the Father\u2019s testimony
          at Jesus\u2019 baptism. See  . The four witnesses of Christ\u2019s glory
          are: Jesus himself, John the Baptizer, the Father who spoke over his Son,
          and the miracles of Jesus.    "
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "<JESUS>nor does his Word truly live inside of you, for you refuse
        to believe in me or to embrace me as God\u2019s messenger.</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CYou are busy analyzing the Scriptures, poring over them
        hoping to gain eternal life. Everything you read points to me,</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "<JESUS>yet you still refuse to come to me so I can give you the life
        you\u2019re looking for\u2014eternal life!</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 5:40
        content: "  There are five witnesses to Christ\u2019s authority and deity
          in this chapter. Jesus himself (vv.  ), John the Baptizer (vv.  ), Jesus\u2019
          miracles (v.  ), the Father (vv.  ), and the Scriptures (vv.  ; see also 
          ).    "
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CI do not accept the honor that comes from men,</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: '<JESUS>for I know what kind of people you really are, and I can see
        that the love of God has found no home in you.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: '<JESUS>I have come to represent my Father, yet you refuse to embrace
        me in faith. If someone comes in their own name</JESUS>  <JESUS>and with
        their own agenda</JESUS><JESUS>,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>you readily
        accept him.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: 5:43
        content: '  Implied in the text.    '
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "<JESUS>Of course you\u2019re unable to believe in me. For you live
        to enjoy the praises of others and not the praise that comes from the one
        true God.</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CI will not accuse you before the Father. The one who
        will incriminate you is Moses, the very one you claim to obey, the one in
        whom you trust!</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 5:45
        content: '  Jesus prophesied that Moses, on the final judgment day, will
          be the one to accuse those who would not listen to the laws and teachings
          of the Torah, which point to their fulfillment in Christ.    '
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: '<JESUS>If you really believed what Moses has written, then you would
        embrace me, for Moses wrote about me!</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "<JESUS>But since you do not believe what he wrote, no wonder you
        don\u2019t believe what I say.\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 5:47
        content: "  Apparently this concluded Jesus\u2019 ministry in Jerusalem at
          this time. The text does not tell us of his return to the province of Galilee.  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Multiplies Food'
      title: Jesus Multiplies Food
      number: 1
      content: 'After this Jesus went to the other side of the Lake of Tiberias,
        [[COMMENT(0)]] which is also known as Lake Galilee. '
      comments:
      - number: 6:1
        content: "  Or \u201Cwhich is also called the Lake of Tiberias.\u201D Tiberias
          was the largest Jewish city in the Galilee province, located on the western
          shore of Lake Galilee. This could also be translated \u201CJesus went   
          Tiberias to Lake Galilee.\u201D    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And a massive crowd of people followed him everywhere. They were
        attracted by his miracles and the healings they watched him perform. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Jesus went up the slope of a hill and sat down with his disciples. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Now it was approaching the time of the Jewish celebration of Passover,
        and there were many pilgrims on their way to Jerusalem in the crowd.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "As Jesus sat down, he looked out and saw the massive crowd of people
        scrambling up the hill, for they wanted to be near him. So he turned to Philip
        and said, <JESUS>\u201CWhere will we buy enough food to feed all these people?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Now Jesus already knew what he was about to do, but he said this
        to stretch Philip\u2019s faith."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Philip answered, \u201CWell, I suppose if we were to give everyone
        only a snack, it would cost thousands of dollars [[COMMENT(0)]] to buy enough
        food!\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 6:7
        content: "  Or \u201Ctwo hundred pieces of silver.\u201D This equates to
          about eight months\u2019 wages of the average person. Philip didn\u2019t
          answer the question and was focused on how much money it would cost, but
          Jesus\u2019 question was, \u201CWhere will we buy bread?\u201D Jesus was
          testing Philip to see if he would look to Jesus to supply all that was
          needed and not consider their limited resources.    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But just then, Andrew, Peter\u2019s brother, spoke up and said, "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CLook! Here\u2019s a young person [[COMMENT(0)]] with five barley
        loaves and two small fish&nbsp;.&nbsp;.&nbsp;. but how far would that go
        with this huge crowd?\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 6:9
        content: "  The Aramaic is literally translated \u201Cboy.\u201D However,
          the Greek uses a word,  , which can also mean a girl or young woman.    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CHave everyone sit down,\u201D</JESUS> Jesus said to
        his disciples. So on the vast grassy slope, more than five thousand hungry
        people sat down. [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 6:10
        content: "  The number five thousand would have likely been only the number
          of men in the crowd. Jesus had everyone sit down. To receive bread from
          Jesus, the Source, doesn\u2019t require that you stand and work hard for
          it, you simply sit down and rest to be fed the living bread.    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Jesus then took the barley loaves [[COMMENT(0)]] and the fish and
        gave thanks to God. He then gave it to the disciples to distribute to the
        people. Miraculously, the food multiplied, with everyone eating as much as
        they wanted! '
      comments:
      - number: 6:11
        content: "  Barley is the first crop to harvest in Israel. It is a picture
          of the resurrected Christ. A barley loaf becomes a picture of Christ given
          to us in resurrection life. He is the firstfruit of resurrection life.
          See  ;  .      When tempted by the devil, Jesus refused to turn stones
          into bread to satisfy his own hunger. Yet here Jesus multiplied bread to
          satisfy the hunger of others. Philip was hoping to give each one a little
          to eat, but Jesus\u2019 supply is always abundant to satisfy the hunger
          of all.    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "When everyone was satisfied, Jesus told his disciples, <JESUS>\u201CNow
        go back and gather up the pieces left over so that nothing will be wasted.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: The disciples filled up twelve baskets of fragments, a basket of leftovers
        for each disciple.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "All the people were astounded as they saw with their own eyes the
        incredible miracle Jesus had performed! They began to say among themselves,
        \u201CHe really is the One\u2014the true prophet [[COMMENT(0)]] we\u2019ve
        been expecting!\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 6:14
        content: '  See  .    '
    - name: '15: Jesus Walks on Water'
      title: Jesus Walks on Water
      number: 15
      content: So Jesus, knowing that they were about to take him and make him their
        king by force, quickly left and went up the mountainside alone. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 6:15
        content: "  Jesus knew the time of liberating Israel had not yet come. Men
          don\u2019t just need better government; we need new hearts.    "
    - name: '16-17: '
      title: 
      number: 16-17
      content: "After waiting until evening for Jesus to return, the disciples went
        down to the lake. But as darkness fell, he still hadn\u2019t returned, so
        the disciples got into a boat and headed across the lake to Capernaum. [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: "6:16\u201317"
        content: "  Capernaum means \u201Cthe village of Nahum.\u201D Nahum means
          \u201Ccomfort\u201D or \u201Cthe village of comfort.\u201D    "
    - name: '16-17: '
      title: 
      number: 16-17
      content: "After waiting until evening for Jesus to return, the disciples went
        down to the lake. But as darkness fell, he still hadn\u2019t returned, so
        the disciples got into a boat and headed across the lake to Capernaum. [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: "6:16\u201317"
        content: "  Capernaum means \u201Cthe village of Nahum.\u201D Nahum means
          \u201Ccomfort\u201D or \u201Cthe village of comfort.\u201D    "
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'By now a strong wind [[COMMENT(0)]] began to blow and was stirring
        up the waters. '
      comments:
      - number: 6:18
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe Spirit stirred up on their behalf.\u201D    "
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The disciples had rowed about halfway [[COMMENT(0)]] across the lake
        when all of a sudden they caught sight of Jesus walking on top of the waves,
        coming toward them. The disciples panicked, '
      comments:
      - number: 6:19
        content: "  Or \u201Cthree or four miles.\u201D The lake was approximately
          seven miles across, so they would have rowed about halfway.    "
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "but Jesus called out to them, <JESUS>\u201CDon\u2019t be afraid.
        You know who I am.\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 6:20
        content: "  Or \u201CFear not. I Am!\u201D    "
    - name: '21: Jesus, the Living Bread'
      title: Jesus, the Living Bread
      number: 21
      content: They were relieved to take him in, and the moment Jesus stepped into
        the boat, they were instantly transported to the other side!
      comments: []
    - name: '22-23: '
      title: 
      number: 22-23
      content: "The next morning, the crowds were still on the opposite shore of
        the lake, near the place where they had eaten the bread he had multiplied
        after he had given thanks to God. [[COMMENT(0)]] Yet Jesus was nowhere to
        be found. They realized that only one boat had been there and that Jesus\u2019
        hadn\u2019t boarded, and they concluded that his disciples had left him behind. "
      comments:
      - number: "6:22\u201323"
        content: '  This information from v.    is included here for the sake of
          the English narrative.    '
    - name: '22-23: '
      title: 
      number: 22-23
      content: "The next morning, the crowds were still on the opposite shore of
        the lake, near the place where they had eaten the bread he had multiplied
        after he had given thanks to God. [[COMMENT(0)]] Yet Jesus was nowhere to
        be found. They realized that only one boat had been there and that Jesus\u2019
        hadn\u2019t boarded, and they concluded that his disciples had left him behind. "
      comments:
      - number: "6:22\u201323"
        content: '  This information from v.    is included here for the sake of
          the English narrative.    '
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "So when the people saw on the shoreline a number of small boats from
        Tiberias and realized Jesus and the disciples weren\u2019t there, they got
        into the boats and went to Capernaum to search for him."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "When they finally found him, they asked him, \u201CTeacher, how did
        you get here?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CLet me make this very clear,</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>you came looking for me because I fed you by a miracle,
        not because you believe in me.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 6:26
        content: "  Or \u201CAmen, amen, I say unto you\u201D or \u201CTimeless truth
          I speak unto you.\u201D    "
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "<JESUS>Why would you strive for food that is perishable and not be
        passionate to seek the food of eternal life, which never spoils?</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>I, the Son of Man, am ready to give you what matters
        most, for God the Father has destined me for this purpose.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 6:27
        content: "  The Aramaic is \u201CWhy would you not seek the food that fastens
          you to eternal life?\u201D      Or \u201Chas set his seal (of approval)
          upon me\u201D or \u201Cthe Father has sealed me as God with his seal of
          approval.\u201D The Aramaic word for \u201Cseal\u201D can also mean \u201Cdestine\u201D
          or \u201Cdetermine.\u201D    "
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "They replied, \u201CSo what should we do if we want to do God\u2019s
        work?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Jesus answered, <JESUS>\u201CThe work you can do for God starts with
        believing in the One he has sent.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '30-31: '
      title: 
      number: 30-31
      content: "They replied, \u201CShow us a miracle so we can see it, and then
        we\u2019ll believe in you. Moses took care of our ancestors who were fed
        by the miracle of manna [[COMMENT(0)]] every day in the desert, just like
        the Scripture says, \u2018He fed them with bread from heaven.\u2019  What
        sign will you perform for us?\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: "6:30\u201331"
        content: "    means \u201CWhat is it?\u201D This is the bread of mystery
          that became the wilderness food for the Hebrews for more than thirty-eight
          years.      See  ;  ;  .    "
    - name: '30-31: '
      title: 
      number: 30-31
      content: "They replied, \u201CShow us a miracle so we can see it, and then
        we\u2019ll believe in you. Moses took care of our ancestors who were fed
        by the miracle of manna [[COMMENT(0)]] every day in the desert, just like
        the Scripture says, \u2018He fed them with bread from heaven.\u2019  What
        sign will you perform for us?\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: "6:30\u201331"
        content: "    means \u201CWhat is it?\u201D This is the bread of mystery
          that became the wilderness food for the Hebrews for more than thirty-eight
          years.      See  ;  ;  .    "
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThe truth is,\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] Jesus said,
        <JESUS>\u201CMoses didn\u2019t give you the bread of heaven. It\u2019s my
        Father who offers bread that comes as a dramatic sign</JESUS>    <JESUS>from
        heaven.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 6:32
        content: "  The Aramaic is \u201CTimeless truth I speak unto you.\u201D     
          The Aramaic can be translated \u201Ca rainbow sign.\u201D Just as Noah
          was given a rainbow sign of the covenant God was making with him, Jesus\u2019
          earthly life was a rainbow sign from heaven of the new covenant life given
          to every believer today. See  ;  ;  . The Greek is \u201Ctrue bread out
          of heaven.\u201D    "
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "<JESUS>The bread of God is the One who came out of heaven to give
        his life to feed the world.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "\u201CThen please, sir, give us this bread every day,\u201D they
        replied."
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Jesus said to them, <JESUS>\u201CI am the Bread of Life.</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>Come every day to me and you will never be hungry.
        Believe in me and you will never be thirsty.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 6:35
        content: "  The Aramaic can be translated \u201CI am the living God, the
          Bread of Life.\u201D    "
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "<JESUS>Yet I\u2019ve told you that even though you\u2019ve seen me,
        you still don\u2019t believe in me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: '<JESUS>But everyone my Father has given to me, they will come. And
        all who come to me, I will embrace and will never turn them away.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: '<JESUS>And I have come out of heaven not for my own desires, but
        for the satisfaction</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>of my Father who sent
        me.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: 6:38
        content: '  As translated from the Aramaic.    '
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: '<JESUS>My Father who sent me has determined that I will not lose
        even one of those he has given to me, and I will raise them up in the last
        day.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "<JESUS>For the longing of my Father is that everyone who embraces
        the Son</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>and believes in him will experience
        eternal life and I will raise them up in the last day!\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 6:40
        content: "  Or \u201Csees the Son.\u201D    "
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "When the Jews who were hostile to Jesus heard him say, <JESUS>\u201CI
        am the Bread that came down from heaven,\u201D</JESUS> they immediately began
        to complain, "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "\u201CHow can he say these things about himself? We know him, and
        we know his parents. How dare he say, \u2018I have come down from heaven?\u2019&nbsp;\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "Jesus responded, <JESUS>\u201CStop your grumbling!</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "<JESUS>The only way people come to me is by the Father who sent me\u2014he
        pulls</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>on their hearts to embrace me. And
        those who are drawn to me, I will certainly raise them up in the last day.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 6:44
        content: "  The Greek word is \u201Cdrag\u201D or \u201Cpull by force.\u201D
          The name Moses means \u201Cpulled\u201D (from the Nile). The Aramaic is
          \u201Cransom\u201D or \u201Csave.\u201D    "
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "Jesus continued, <JESUS>\u201CIt has been written by the prophets,
        \u2018They will all be taught by God himself.\u2019</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>If you are really listening to the Father and learning directly from
        him, you will come to me.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 6:45
        content: '  See  ;  .    '
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "<JESUS>For I am the only One who has come from the Father\u2019s
        side, and I have seen the Father!</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CI speak to you living truth: Unite your heart to me
        and believe\u2014and you will experience eternal life!</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: '<JESUS>I am the true Bread of Life.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 6:48
        content: "  Although not found in the Greek text, there are some Aramaic
          manuscripts that have \u201CI am the living God, the Bread of Life.\u201D    "
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: '<JESUS>Your ancestors ate manna in the desert and died.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: '<JESUS>But standing here before you is the true Bread that comes
        out of heaven, and when you eat this Bread you will never die.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "<JESUS>I alone am this living Bread that has come to you from heaven.
        Eat this Bread and you will live forever. The living Bread I give you is
        my body, which I will offer as a sacrifice so that all may live.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "These words of Jesus sparked an angry outburst among the Jews. They
        protested, saying, \u201CDoes this man expect us to eat his body?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: "Jesus replied to them, <JESUS>\u201CListen to this eternal truth:
        Unless you eat the body of the Son of Man and drink his blood, you will not
        have eternal life.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: '<JESUS>Eternal life comes to the one who eats my body</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>and drinks my blood, and I will raise him up in the last day.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: 6:54
        content: "  To eat his flesh is to take into our life by faith all that Jesus
          did for us by giving his body for us. To drink his blood is to take by
          faith all that the blood of Jesus has purchased for us. This \u201Ceating\u201D
          and \u201Cdrinking\u201D is receiving the life, power, and virtue of all
          that Jesus is to replace all that we were in Adam. Jesus\u2019 blood and
          body is the Tree of Life, which is offered to everyone who follows him.    "
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: '<JESUS>For my body is real food for your spirit and my blood is real
        drink.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: '<JESUS>The one who eats my body and drinks my blood lives in me and
        I live in him.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 6:56
        content: "  The Aramaic is \u201CHe that eats my body and drinks my blood
          is strengthened in me and I in him.\u201D    "
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: '<JESUS>The Father of life sent me, and he is my life. In the same
        way, the one who feeds upon me, I will become his life.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: "<JESUS>I am not like the bread your ancestors ate and later died.
        I am the living Bread that comes from heaven. Eat this Bread and you will
        live forever!\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '59: Many Disciples Became Offended'
      title: Many Disciples Became Offended
      number: 59
      content: Jesus preached this sermon in the synagogue in Capernaum.
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: "And when many of Jesus\u2019 followers heard these things, it caused
        a stir. \u201CThat\u2019s disgusting!\u201D they said. \u201CHow could anybody
        accept it?\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 6:60
        content: "  Jesus knew that these words were offending the religious Jews.
          To eat flesh that was not kosher was a violation of the law; how much more
          so to eat human flesh. Drinking blood of any kind was also forbidden ().
          The imagery is similar to Ezekiel who \u201Cate the scroll\u201D (of the
          Word,  ).    "
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: "Without anyone telling him, Jesus knew they were outraged and told
        them, <JESUS>\u201CAre you offended over my teaching?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: <JESUS>What will you do when you see the Son of Man ascending</JESUS> 
        <JESUS>into the realm</JESUS>  <JESUS>from where he came?</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 6:62
        content: '  The greatest offense of all will be the cross where Jesus will
          soon be crucified, and they will watch him surrender his Spirit to the
          Father in death. See  ;  .    '
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThe Holy Spirit is the one who gives life, that which
        is of the natural realm</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>is of no help. The
        words I speak to you are Spirit and life. But there are still some of you
        who won\u2019t believe.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 6:63
        content: "  The Aramaic is \u201Cthe body.\u201D    "
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: In fact, Jesus already knew from the beginning who the skeptics were
        and who his traitor would be.
      comments: []
    - name: "65: Peter\u2019s Confession of Faith"
      title: "Peter\u2019s Confession of Faith"
      number: 65
      content: "He went on to say, <JESUS>\u201CThis is why I told you that no one
        embraces me unless the Father has given you to me.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '66: '
      title: 
      number: 66
      content: 'And so from that time on many of the disciples turned their backs
        on Jesus and refused to be associated with him. [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 6:66
        content: "  Jesus went from feeding five thousand to offending five thousand.
          They wanted him to feed them, but didn\u2019t want Jesus alone to be their
          feast.    "
    - name: '67: '
      title: 
      number: 67
      content: "So Jesus said to his twelve, <JESUS>\u201CAnd you\u2014do you also
        want to leave?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '68: '
      title: 
      number: 68
      content: "Peter spoke up and said, \u201CBut Lord, where would we go? No one
        but you gives us the revelation of eternal life. "
      comments: []
    - name: '69: '
      title: 
      number: 69
      content: "We\u2019re fully convinced that you are the Anointed One, the Son
        of the Living God, [[COMMENT(0)]] and we believe in you!\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 6:69
        content: "  As translated from the Aramaic. Although many Greek scholars
          believe this is borrowed from the Synoptic Gospels, and is found in variant
          forms in Greek texts, the Aramaic and many Greek manuscripts have \u201CYou
          are the Christ, the Son of the living God.\u201D    "
    - name: '70: '
      title: 
      number: 70
      content: "Then Jesus shocked them with these words: <JESUS>\u201CI have hand-picked
        you to be my twelve, knowing that one of you is the devil.\u201D</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 6:70
        content: "  The Greek word for \u201Cdevil\u201D means \u201Cslanderer\u201D
          or \u201Cadversary.\u201D    "
    - name: '71: '
      title: 
      number: 71
      content: Jesus was referring to Judas Iscariot, [[COMMENT(0)]] son of Simon,
        for he knew that Judas, one of his chosen disciples, was getting ready to
        betray him.
      comments:
      - number: 6:71
        content: "  Judas is the name Judah.    was not his last name. There are
          two possibilities for the meaning of  . Some believe it is taken from a
          Hebrew word that means \u201Clock.\u201D Judah the \u201Clocksmith.\u201D
          He most likely was the one who locked the collection bag, which means he
          had the key and could pilfer the fund at will. It\u2019s his sad history
          that he wanted to lock up Jesus and control him for his own ends. Other
          scholars see the possibility that    is actually \u201CIsh\u201D (man)
          of \u201CKerioth\u201D (a town once situated south of Hebron). This would
          mean Judas was the only non-Galilean among the Twelve.  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus at the Feast of Tabernacles'
      title: Jesus at the Feast of Tabernacles
      number: 1
      content: 'After this Jesus traveled extensively throughout the province of
        Galilee, but he avoided the province of Judea, for he knew the Jewish leaders
        in Jerusalem were plotting to have him killed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Now the annual Feast of Tabernacles [[COMMENT(0)]] was approaching. '
      comments:
      - number: 7:2
        content: "  Or \u201CTents.\u201D See  .    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So Jesus\u2019 brothers [[COMMENT(0)]] came to advise him, saying,
        \u201CWhy don\u2019t you leave the countryside villages and go to Judea where
        the crowds are,  so that your followers can see your miracles? "
      comments:
      - number: 7:3
        content: "  These were actually Jesus\u2019 half brothers, for Joseph was
          his stepfather.      Or \u201Cso that your followers can see your miracles.\u201D    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "No one can see what you\u2019re doing here in the backwoods of Galilee.
        How do you expect to be successful and famous if you do all these things
        in secret? Now is your time\u2014go to Jerusalem, come out of hiding, and
        show the world who you are!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "His brothers were pushing him, even though they didn\u2019t yet believe
        in him as the Savior. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 7:5
        content: '  As translated from the Aramaic and implied in the Greek text.
          This fulfills the prophecy of  .    '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Jesus responded, <JESUS>\u201CMy time of being unveiled hasn\u2019t
        yet come, but any time is a suitable opportunity for you</JESUS>  <JESUS>to
        gain man\u2019s approval.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "<JESUS>The world can\u2019t hate you, but it does me, for I am exposing
        their evil deeds.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "<JESUS>You can go ahead and celebrate the feast without me\u2014my
        appointed time has not yet come.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '9-10: '
      title: 
      number: 9-10
      content: 'Jesus lingered in Galilee until his brothers had left for the feast
        in Jerusalem. Then later, Jesus took a back road and went into Jerusalem
        in secret. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9-10: '
      title: 
      number: 9-10
      content: 'Jesus lingered in Galilee until his brothers had left for the feast
        in Jerusalem. Then later, Jesus took a back road and went into Jerusalem
        in secret. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "During the feast, the Jewish leaders kept looking for Jesus and asking
        around, \u201CWhere is he? Have you seen him?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "A controversy was brewing among the people, with so many differing
        opinions about Jesus. Some were saying, \u201CHe\u2019s a good man!\u201D
        While others weren\u2019t convinced and insisted, saying, \u201CHe\u2019s
        just a demagogue.\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 7:12
        content: "  Or \u201CHe leads the people astray.\u201D    "
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Yet no one was bold enough to speak out publicly on Jesus\u2019 behalf
        for fear of the Jewish leaders."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Not until the feast was half over did Jesus finally appear in the
        temple courts and begin to teach. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The Jewish leaders were astonished by what he taught and said, \u201CHow
        did this man acquire such knowledge? He wasn\u2019t trained in our schools\u2014who
        taught him?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So Jesus responded, <JESUS>\u201CI don\u2019t teach my own ideas,</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>but the truth revealed to me by the One who sent me.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 7:16
        content: "  Or \u201CMy doctrine is not my own.\u201D    "
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "<JESUS>If you want to test my teachings and discover where I received
        them, first be passionate to do God\u2019s will,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>and then you will be able to discern if my teachings are from the
        heart of God or from my own opinions.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 7:17
        content: "  The Aramaic is very poetic: \u201CWhoever is satisfied to do
          God\u2019s satisfaction shall gain liberating knowledge.\u201D    "
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '<JESUS>Charlatans praise themselves and seek honor from men, but
        my Father sent me to speak truth on his behalf. And I have no false motive,
        because I seek only the glory of God.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "<JESUS>Moses has given you the law, but not one of you is faithful
        to keep it. So if you are all law-breakers, why then would you seek to kill
        me?\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then some in the crowd shouted out, \u201CYou must be out of your
        mind! [[COMMENT(0)]] Who\u2019s trying to kill you?\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 7:20
        content: "  Or \u201CAre you demon possessed?\u201D This is an Aramaic figure
          of speech for lunacy.    "
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CI only had to do one miracle,</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>and all of you marvel!</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 7:21
        content: "  Or \u201Cone deed.\u201D Although Jesus performed many miracles,
          it is likely he is referring to the miracle of the lame man being healed
          in  .    "
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "<JESUS>Yet isn\u2019t it true that Moses and your forefathers</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>ordered you to circumcise your sons even if the eighth
        day fell on a Sabbath?</JESUS>    "
      comments:
      - number: 7:22
        content: '  This is the patriarchs. Circumcision actually began with a sign
          of the covenant God instituted with Abraham. See  .      A son was to be
          circumcised eight days after he was born. See  .    '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "<JESUS>So if you cut away part of a man on the Sabbath and that doesn\u2019t
        break the Jewish law,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>why then would you
        be indignant with me for making a man completely healed on the Sabbath?</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 7:23
        content: "  Or \u201CTorah.\u201D Jesus was saying, \u201CWho are you to
          judge me when you don\u2019t practice what you preach?\u201D    "
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "<JESUS>Stop judging based on the superficial.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>First you must</JESUS>  <JESUS>embrace the standards of mercy</JESUS>   
        <JESUS>and truth.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 7:24
        content: "  Or \u201CNever judge as a hypocrite wearing a mask.\u201D     
          Jesus was teaching that the law of mercy (healing the lame man) overrides
          the laws of Moses (regulations of the Sabbath). Seeing situations and people
          with the lens of mercy gives us true discernment.    "
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then some of the residents of Jerusalem spoke up and said, \u201CIsn\u2019t
        this the one they\u2019re trying to kill? "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "So why is he here speaking publicly and not one of the Jewish leaders
        is doing anything about it? Are they starting to think that he\u2019s the
        Anointed One? "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "But how could he be, since we know this man is from Galilee, but
        no one will know where the true Messiah comes from, he\u2019ll just appear
        out of nowhere.\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 7:27
        content: '  This was a Rabbinical interpretation that was common in that
          day. However, they knew that the Messiah would come from Bethlehem, for
          it was prophesied in    where the Christ would be born. So in truth, they
          did not know where Jesus was from.    '
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Knowing all of this, Jesus one day preached boldly in the temple
        courts, <JESUS>\u201CSo, you think you know me and where I come from? But
        you don\u2019t know the One who sent me\u2014the Father who is always faithful.</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>I have not come simply on my own initiative.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 7:28
        content: "  Or \u201Ctruthful.\u201D    "
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "<JESUS>The Father has sent me here, and I know all about him, for
        I have come from his presence.\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 7:29
        content: "  Or \u201CI am from next to him.\u201D The Aramaic is \u201Cfrom
          his presence I am.\u201D    "
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "His words caused many to want to arrest him, but no man was able
        to lay a hand on him, for it wasn\u2019t yet his appointed time. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And there were many people who thought he might be the Messiah. They
        said, \u201CAfter all, when the Anointed One appears, could he possibly do
        more signs and wonders than this man has done?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: So when the Pharisees [[COMMENT(0)]] heard these rumors circulating
        about Jesus, they went with the leading priests and the temple guards to
        arrest him.
      comments:
      - number: 7:32
        content: "  Or \u201Cseparated ones.\u201D    "
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Then Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CMy days to be with you are numbered.
        Then I will return to the One who sent me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "<JESUS>And you will search for me and not be able to find me. For
        where I am,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>you cannot come.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 7:34
        content: "  In this tremendous statement, Jesus was telling them that he
          was about to return to the realm where I AM dwells. Of course, the Jewish
          leaders didn\u2019t understand the impact of what he was telling them.     
          Jesus was speaking of his approaching death on the cross, which he knew
          was near, and his ascension back to the Father, the realm of I AM.    "
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "When the Jewish leaders heard this, they discussed among themselves,
        \u201CWhere could he possibly go that we won\u2019t be able to find him?
        Is he going to minister in a different land where our people live scattered
        among the nations? Is he going to teach those who are not Jews? [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 7:35
        content: '  There were many of the tribes of Israel who were scattered at
          that time in Assyria, Iran, Afghanistan, and other adjacent nations. These
          had been taken captive by the kings of Assyria in 722 BC. See  .    '
    - name: '36: Rivers of Living Water'
      title: Rivers of Living Water
      number: 36
      content: "What did he really mean by his statement, \u2018You will search for
        me and won\u2019t be able to find me. And where I am you can\u2019t come\u2019?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Then on the most important day of the feast, the last day, [[COMMENT(0)]]
        Jesus stood and shouted out to the crowds\u2014<JESUS>\u201CAll you thirsty
        ones, come to me! Come to me and drink!</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 7:37
        content: "  When man\u2019s feasting is over there is still thirst. Jesus
          comes at the last day of the feast to satisfy the thirst of those who seek
          God. Only the Lord Jesus can quench the spiritual thirst of men by giving
          them his living water.    "
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "<JESUS>Believe in me so that rivers of living water will burst out
        from within you, flowing</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>from your innermost
        being, just like the Scripture says!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 7:38
        content: "  The root word used here is the same as the River Jordan, which
          means \u201Cflowing\u201D (down).      Or \u201Crivers of living water
          will flow from his throne within.\u201D See  ;  ;  ;  ;  . A drink becomes
          a river!    "
    - name: '39: Divided Opinions about Jesus'
      title: Divided Opinions about Jesus
      number: 39
      content: 'Jesus was prophesying about the Holy Spirit that believers were being
        prepared to receive. [[COMMENT(0)]] But the Holy Spirit had not yet been
        poured out upon them, because Jesus had not yet been unveiled in his full
        splendor. '
      comments:
      - number: 7:39
        content: '  As translated from the Aramaic.      This splendor included the
          splendor of the cross, the splendor of his resurrection, and the glory
          of his ascension into heaven. Just as water poured out of the rock that
          was struck by Moses, so from the wounded side of Jesus living water poured
          out to heal, save, and bring life to everyone who believes. The Holy Spirit
          poured out of Christ and into the church at Pentecost.    '
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "When the crowd heard Jesus\u2019 words, some said, \u201CThis man
        really is a prophet!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Others said, \u201CHe\u2019s the Messiah!\u201D But others said,
        \u201CHow could he be the Anointed One since he\u2019s from Galilee? "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "Don\u2019t the Scriptures say that he will be one of David\u2019s
        descendants and be born in Bethlehem, the city of David?\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 7:42
        content: '  They had an understanding of the Bible but still missed who Jesus
          was. Bible knowledge alone, without the Holy Spirit opening our hearts
          and bringing us to Christ, can leave us as a skeptic. They jumped to conclusions,
          not realizing that Jesus may have been raised in Nazareth in Galilee, but
          he was born in Bethlehem and was a true descendant of David. See  ;  ; 
          ;  ;  .    '
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'So the crowd was divided over Jesus, '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: The Unbelief of Religious Leaders'
      title: The Unbelief of Religious Leaders
      number: 44
      content: some wanted him arrested but no one dared to lay a hand on him.
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "So when the temple guards returned to the Pharisees and the leading
        priests without Jesus, they were questioned, \u201CWhere is he? Why didn\u2019t
        you bring that man back with you?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "They answered, \u201CYou don\u2019t understand\u2014he speaks amazing
        things like no one else has ever spoken!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "The religious leaders mocked, \u201COh, so now you also have been
        led astray by him? "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'Do you see even one of us, your leaders, following him? '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "This ignorant rabble swarms around him because none of them know
        anything about the Law! They\u2019re all cursed!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'Just then, Nicodemus, who had secretly spent time with Jesus, spoke
        up, for he was a respected voice among them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "He cautioned them, saying, \u201CDoes our law decide a man\u2019s
        guilt before we first hear him and allow him to defend himself?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "They argued, \u201COh, so now you\u2019re an advocate for this Galilean!
        Search the Scriptures, Nicodemus, and you\u2019ll see that there\u2019s no
        mention of a prophet coming out of Galilee!\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]  So with
        that their debate ended, "
      comments:
      - number: 7:52
        content: "  They apparently didn\u2019t know their own Jewish history, for
          the prophet Jonah, in 580 BC, came from Gathepher, a village only three
          miles from Nazareth. It is believed that Elijah, Nahum, and Hosea also
          came from Galilee. Jesus\u2019 Galilean ministry was prophesied in  .  "
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: and they each went their own way.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: An Adulteress Forgiven'
      title: An Adulteress Forgiven
      number: 1
      content: 'Jesus walked up the Mount of Olives [[COMMENT(0)]] near the city
        where he spent the night. '
      comments:
      - number: 8:1
        content: '  Named for the many olive trees on its slopes, the Mount of Olives
          was a high slope just east of Jerusalem across the Kidron Valley.    '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then at dawn Jesus appeared in the temple courts again, and soon
        all the people gathered around to listen to his words, so he sat down and
        taught them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Then in the middle of his teaching, the religious scholars [[COMMENT(0)]]
        and the Pharisees broke through the crowd and brought a woman who had been
        caught in the act of committing adultery and made her stand in the middle
        of everyone.
      comments:
      - number: 8:3
        content: "  Or \u201Cscribes.\u201D The scribes were not merely professional
          copyists, they were the scholarly experts who were to be consulted over
          the details of the written law of Moses.    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then they said to Jesus, \u201CTeacher, we caught this woman in the
        very act of adultery. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Doesn\u2019t Moses\u2019 law command us to stone to death a woman
        like this? [[COMMENT(0)]] Tell us, what do you say we should do with her?\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: 8:5
        content: '  See    and  , where it is clear that both the man and woman were
          to be stoned to death.    '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "They were only testing Jesus because they hoped to trap him with
        his own words and accuse him of breaking the laws of Moses.But Jesus didn\u2019t
        answer them. Instead he simply bent down and wrote in the dust with his finger.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 8:6
        content: '  This is not the first time God wrote with his finger. See  .    '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Angry, they kept insisting [[COMMENT(0)]] that he answer their question,
        so Jesus stood up and looked at them and said, <JESUS>\u201CLet\u2019s have
        the man who has never had a sinful desire</JESUS>    <JESUS>throw the first
        stone at her.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 8:7
        content: "  As translated from the Aramaic.      The Greek word    means
          more than simply \u201Csin,\u201D but is best translated \u201Ca sinful
          desire.\u201D    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: And then he bent over again and wrote some more words in the dust.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 8:8
        content: "  See  . Jesus wrote in the dust to fulfill Jeremiah\u2019s prophecy
          that those who forsake God (spiritual adultery) will be written in the
          dust. All of the accusers were guilty of having forsaken God, the fountain
          of living water, and yet were so anxious to stone this woman to death.
          The same finger that wrote the Ten Commandments in stone also wrote the
          names of each of the accusers, or perhaps he wrote    in the dirt in front
          of their eyes, pointing to their hypocrisy.    "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Upon hearing that, her accusers slowly left the crowd one at a time,
        beginning with the oldest to the youngest, [[COMMENT(0)]] with a convicted
        conscience. '
      comments:
      - number: 8:9
        content: "  The Aramaic can be translated \u201Cstarting with the priests.\u201D    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Until finally, Jesus was left alone with the woman still standing
        there in front of him. So he stood back up and said to her, <JESUS>\u201CDear
        woman, where are your accusers? Is there no one here to condemn you?\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Jesus, the Light of the World'
      title: Jesus, the Light of the World
      number: 11
      content: "Looking around, she replied, \u201CI see no one, Lord.\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>!
        See also</smallcaps>Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CThen I certainly</JESUS>   
        <JESUS>don\u2019t condemn you either.</JESUS>    <JESUS>Go, and from now
        on, be free from a life of sin.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 8:11
        content: "  The Aramaic contains a powerful testimony from this woman. Apparently
          the woman had the revelation of who Jesus really was, for she addressed
          Jesus with the divine name in the Aramaic,  , Lord    . The Greek texts
          use the word    for \u201CLord,\u201D which can also mean \u201Csir\u201D
          or \u201Clandowner.\u201D      The Greek has the emphatic use of the personal
          pronoun.      The Aramaic is \u201CNeither do I put you down\u201D (or
          \u201Coppress you\u201D). The Torah required two witnesses. There were
          none left!      Or \u201Cno longer be sinning.\u201D It should be noted
          that this entire episode (referred to commonly as the \u201CPericope Adulterae\u201D)
          is missing in the majority of the most reliable Greek manuscripts. There
          are some manuscripts that have this story at the end of the book of John
          and at least two that include it in the Gospel of Luke. Many scholars surmise
          that this episode in the ministry of Jesus was added after the Gospel of
          John had been completed. However, it is the conclusion of this translation
          that the above text is indeed an inspired account of the ministry of Jesus
          and may have been deleted by many translators and copyists who doubted
          that Jesus could tell an adulterer that he would not condemn her. Augustine,
          one of the early church fathers, mentioned this story and stated that many
          translators had removed it because they interpreted it as Jesus giving
          license to immorality. God\u2019s grace always seems to startle the religious
          (Augustine,  , II:6.)    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CI am</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>light
        to the world, and those who embrace me will experience life-giving light,
        and they will never</JESUS>    <JESUS>walk</JESUS>    <JESUS>in darkness.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 8:12
        content: "  Again we see Jesus using the words \u201CI Am,\u201D which is
          the name of God.      The Greek word is a double negative, emphatically
          saying, \u201Cnever, no never!\u201D      The Aramaic is \u201Cthey will
          never be driven (pushed) by the darkness.\u201D    "
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The Pharisees were immediately offended and said, \u201CYou\u2019re
        just boasting about yourself! Since we only have your word on this, it makes
        your testimony invalid!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Jesus responded, <JESUS>\u201CJust because I am the one making these
        claims doesn\u2019t mean they\u2019re invalid.</JESUS>  <JESUS>For I absolutely
        know who I am</JESUS><JESUS>, where I\u2019ve come from, and where I\u2019m
        going. But you Pharisees have no idea about what I\u2019m saying.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "<JESUS>For you\u2019ve set yourselves up as judges of others based
        on outward appearances, but I certainly never judge others in that way.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: <JESUS>For I discern the truth. And I am not alone in my judgments,
        for my Father and I have the same understanding in all things, and he has
        sent me to you.</JESUS>
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CIsn\u2019t it written in the law of Moses that the testimony
        of two men is trustworthy?</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 8:17
        content: '  See  .    '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "<JESUS>Then what I say about who I am is true, for I am not alone
        in my testimony\u2014my Father is the other witness, and we testify together
        of the truth.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then they asked, \u201CJust who is this \u2018Father\u2019 of yours?
        Where is he?\u201DJesus answered, <JESUS>\u201CYou wouldn\u2019t ask that
        question if you knew who I am, or my Father. For if you knew me, you would
        recognize my Father too.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: "20: \u201CI Am Not from This World\u201D"
      title: "\u201CI Am Not from This World\u201D"
      number: 20
      content: "(Jesus taught all these things while standing in the treasure room
        of the temple. [[COMMENT(0)]] And no one dared to arrest him, for it wasn\u2019t
        yet his time to surrender to men.)"
      comments:
      - number: 8:20
        content: "  Jesus unlocks that \u201Ctreasure room\u201D to us, his temple.
          When we receive him as our life-giving light, we see the treasures that
          have been given to us by grace.    "
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "One day Jesus said again, <JESUS>\u201CI am about to leave you. You
        will want to find me, but you will still die in your sins.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>You won\u2019t be able to come where I am going.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 8:21
        content: '  Jesus gave a stern warning of dying before you have turned away
          from sin and put your faith in the Savior.    '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "This so confused the Jewish leaders that they began to say, \u201CIs
        he planning to commit suicide? What\u2019s he talking about\u2014\u2018You
        won\u2019t be able to come where I am going\u2019?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Jesus spoke up and said, <JESUS>\u201CYou are all from the earth;
        I am from above. I am not from this world like you are.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "<JESUS>That\u2019s why I\u2019ve told you that you will all die in
        your sins if you fail to believe that I AM who I AM.\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 8:24
        content: "  Believing the truth that Jesus Christ is the \u201CI AM,\u201D
          God who became a man, is an essential part of our faith as followers of
          Christ.    "
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "So they asked him plainly, \u201CWho are you?\u201D<JESUS>\u201CI
        am the One I\u2019ve always claimed to be.\u201D</JESUS> Jesus replied. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CAnd I still have many more things to pronounce in judgment
        about you. For I will testify to the world of the truths that I have heard
        from my Father, and the Father who sent me is trustworthy.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "(Even after all of this, they still didn\u2019t realize that he was
        speaking about his heavenly Father.)"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CYou will know me as \u2018I AM\u2019 after you have
        lifted me up from the earth</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>as the Son of
        Man. Then you will realize that I do nothing on my own initiative, but I
        only speak the truth that the Father has revealed to me.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 8:28
        content: "  There is a dual meaning in these words. To honor Jesus and exalt
          him reveals his true identity to our hearts. The word for \u201Clifted
          up\u201D can also mean \u201Cto exalt\u201D and therefore \u201Cto honor.\u201D
          However, Jesus was \u201Clifted up\u201D on a cross, suspended between
          heaven and earth, and died for the sins of all mankind. Both of these implications
          are found in these words of Jesus.    "
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "<JESUS>I am his messenger and he is always with me, for I only do
        that which delights his heart.\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 8:29
        content: "  The Aramaic is \u201CI only do what adorns [beautifies] him.\u201D    "
    - name: '30: The Son Gives Freedom'
      title: The Son Gives Freedom
      number: 30
      content: These words caused many respected Jews to believe in him.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Jesus said to those Jews who believed in him, <JESUS>\u201CWhen you
        continue to embrace all that I teach, you prove that you are my true followers.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "<JESUS>For if you embrace the truth, it will release true freedom
        into your lives.\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 8:32
        content: "  The truth Jesus gives us releases us from the bondage of our
          past, the bondage of our sins, and the bondage of religion. Jesus was speaking
          these words to those who were not fully free from man\u2019s traditions.
          Truth must be embraced and worked out through the divine process of spiritual
          maturity. The Greek word for \u201Ctruth\u201D is  . To embrace the reality
          of Christ brings more freedom into your life. See the book of Galatians
          for a clear explanation of the freedom Jesus referred to here.    "
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Surprised by this, they said, \u201CBut we\u2019re the descendants
        of Abraham and we\u2019re already free. We\u2019ve never been in bondage
        [[COMMENT(0)]] to anyone. How could you say that we will be released into
        more freedom?\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: 8:33
        content: "  The Greek is translated \u201Cslavery.\u201D However, the Aramaic
          word used here () refers not to slavery but to paying off debts (indentured
          servants). The Jews were not forgetting their slavery in Egypt, but rather
          saying that they were not in bondage to serve anyone as free sons of Abraham.
          Jesus reminded them that ancestral lineage does not guarantee spiritual
          freedom.      The Aramaic is translated \u201Creleased as children of freedom.\u201D    "
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CI speak eternal truth,\u201D</JESUS> Jesus said. <JESUS>\u201CWhen
        you sin you are not free. You\u2019ve become a slave in bondage to your sin.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: '<JESUS>And slaves have no permanent standing in a family, like a
        son does, for a son is a part of the family forever.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: '<JESUS>So if the Son sets you free from sin, then become a true son
        and be unquestionably free!</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: '<JESUS>Even though you are descendants of Abraham, you desire to
        kill me because the message I bring has not found a home in your hearts.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "<JESUS>Yet the truths I speak I\u2019ve seen and received in my Father\u2019s
        presence. But you are doing what you\u2019ve learned from your father!\u201D</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 8:38
        content: "  Some Greek manuscripts have \u201CSince I\u2019m saying what
          I\u2019ve seen while with my Father, put my Father\u2019s words into practice.\u201D    "
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "\u201CWhat do you mean?\u201D they replied. \u201CAbraham is our
        father!\u201DJesus said, <JESUS>\u201CIf you are really Abraham\u2019s sons,
        then you would follow in the steps of Abraham.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "<JESUS>I\u2019ve only told you the truth that I\u2019ve heard in
        my Father\u2019s presence, but now you are wanting me dead\u2014is that how
        Abraham acted?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "<JESUS>No, you people are doing what your father has taught you!\u201D</JESUS>Indignant,
        they responded, \u201CWhat are you talking about? We only have one Father,
        God himself! We\u2019re not illegitimate!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CThen if God were really your father, you
        would love me, for I\u2019ve come from his presence. I didn\u2019t come here
        on my own, but God sent me to you.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "<JESUS>Why don\u2019t you understand what I say?</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>You don\u2019t understand because your hearts are closed to my message!</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 8:43
        content: "  The Aramaic is \u201CWhy don\u2019t you receive my manifestation?\u201D    "
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CYou are the offspring of your father, the devil,</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>and you serve your father very well, passionately
        carrying out his desires. He\u2019s been a murderer right from the start!
        He never stood with the truth, for he\u2019s full of nothing but lies\u2014lying
        is his native tongue.</JESUS>    <JESUS>He is a master of deception and the
        father of lies!</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 8:44
        content: "  The word for \u201Cdevil\u201D in Greek means \u201Cslanderer-accuser.\u201D
          The Aramaic word is  , or \u201Cadversary.\u201D It is taken from a root
          word that means \u201Cto ridicule\u201D or \u201Cto gnaw.\u201D See v.   
          where the Jewish leaders ridiculed Jesus\u2019 words.      Or \u201Cwhen
          he lies he\u2019s only doing what is natural to him.\u201D    "
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: '<JESUS>But I am the true Prince who speaks nothing but the truth,
        yet you refuse to believe and you want nothing to do with me.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "<JESUS>Can you name one sin that I\u2019ve committed? Then if I am
        telling you only the truth, why don\u2019t you believe me?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "<JESUS>If you really knew God, you would listen, receive, and respond
        with faith to his words. But since you don\u2019t listen and respond to what
        he says, it proves you don\u2019t belong to him and you have no room for
        him in your hearts.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "\u201CSee! We were right all along!\u201D some of the Jewish leaders
        shouted. \u201CYou\u2019re nothing but a demon-possessed Samaritan!\u201D
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 8:48
        content: "  They are obviously scorning Jesus by calling him \u201Ca demon-possessed
          Samaritan.\u201D The Jews despised their northern cousins, the Samaritans,
          for their ancestors had come from Assyria and occupied Israel\u2019s lands.
          The three major groups in Israel at that time were Judeans (Jews), Galileans,
          and Samaritans. The Jerusalem Jews saw themselves as superior and more
          faithful to the God of the Hebrews than their northern neighbors. Jesus
          was a Galilean, having come from Nazareth. But Nazareth was part of the
          northern region looked down upon by the Jews. The Aramaic can be translated
          \u201CYou\u2019re a crazy Samaritan.\u201D    "
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CIt is not a demon that would cause me
        to honor my Father. I live my life for his honor, even though you insult
        me for it.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 8:49
        content: "  The Aramaic is \u201Cyou curse me.\u201D    "
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: '<JESUS>I never have a need to seek my own glory, for the Father will
        do that for me, and he will judge those who do not.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "<JESUS>I speak to you this eternal truth: whoever cherishes my words
        and keeps them will never experience death.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "This prompted the Jewish leaders to say, \u201CNow we know for sure
        that you\u2019re demon possessed! You just said that those who keep watch
        over your words will never experience death, but Abraham and all the prophets
        have died! "
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: "Do you think you\u2019re greater than our father Abraham and all
        the prophets? You are so delusional about yourself that you make yourself
        greater than you are!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: "Jesus answered them, <JESUS>\u201CIf I were to tell you how great
        I am, it would mean nothing. But my Father is the One who will prove it and
        will glorify me. Isn\u2019t he the One you claim is your God?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: "<JESUS>But in reality, you\u2019ve never embraced him as your own.
        I know him, and I would be a liar, like yourselves, if I told you anything
        less than that. I have fully embraced him, and I treasure his every word.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: "<JESUS>And not only that, Abraham, your ancestor, was overjoyed when
        he received the revelation of my coming to earth. Yes, he foresaw me coming
        and was filled with delight!\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 8:56
        content: "  This refers to the prophetic insight God gave to Abraham about
          the coming Messiah. Many Hebrew scholars believe this was given to Abraham
          on the day of \u201Cbinding.\u201D That is, the day he tied his son, Isaac,
          to the altar to offer him as a sacrifice. It was then that God showed him
          a ram that was caught in a thicket nearby to be the substitute for Isaac.
          See  ;  ,  .    "
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: "But many of the Jewish leaders doubted him and said, \u201CWhat are
        you talking about? You\u2019re not even fifty years old yet. You talk like
        you\u2019ve seen Abraham!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: "Jesus said to them, <JESUS>\u201CI give you this eternal truth: I
        have existed long before Abraham was born, for I AM!\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps> 
        </smallcaps>"
      comments:
      - number: 8:58
        content: "  Proper English grammar would be, \u201CBefore Abraham was born,
          I Was.\u201D However, Jesus indentified himself with the \u201CI AM that
          I AM\u201D of  , when  appeared to Moses in the flames of the sacred shrub.    "
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: When they heard this, they picked up rocks to stone him, but Jesus
        concealed himself as he passed through the crowd [[COMMENT(0)]] and went
        away from there.
      comments:
      - number: 8:59
        content: "  Some reliable Greek texts present Jesus\u2019 exit in a less
          than supernatural way. But the Aramaic and many other Greek manuscripts
          make it clear that it was a supernatural exit from the Jewish leaders who
          wanted to kill him. See also    for another incident of Jesus walking through
          a hostile crowd. Chapter    begins with the self-righteous wanting to stone
          the adulterous woman and ends with them wanting to stone the sinless Messiah.  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Healed a Man Born Blind'
      title: Jesus Healed a Man Born Blind
      number: 1
      content: 'Afterward, as Jesus walked down the street, he noticed a man blind
        from birth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "His disciples asked him, \u201CTeacher, whose sin caused this guy\u2019s
        blindness, his own, or the sin of his parents?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Jesus answered, <JESUS>\u201CNeither. It happened to him so that
        you could watch him experience God\u2019s miracle.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '<JESUS>While I am with you, it is daytime and we must do the works
        of God who sent me while the light shines.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>For
        there is coming a dark night when no one will be able to work.</JESUS>    '
      comments:
      - number: 9:4
        content: "  A possible translation of vv.    can be, \u201CJesus answered,
          \u2018This man didn\u2019t sin, nor did his parents; but, that the works
          of God might be revealed in him. I must work the works of him who sent
          me while it is day. The night is coming, when no man can work\u2019&nbsp;\u201D
          (WEB translation).      The Aramaic can be translated \u201CThe One who
          sent me is the day, and we must do his works. But the night (of mankind)
          will follow when no work can be accomplished.\u201D    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "<JESUS>As long as I am with you my life is the light that pierces
        the world\u2019s darkness.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Jesus spat on the ground and made some clay with his saliva.
        [[COMMENT(0)]] Then he anointed the blind man\u2019s eyes with the clay. "
      comments:
      - number: 9:6
        content: '  John has left us a book of pictures. The picture here is the
          mingling of spit and clay, a picture of the Christ who is God and man.
          The saliva comes from the mouth, the spoken Word, God incarnate. The clay
          is always a picture of man, for our human vessel is a jar of clay. No doubt,
          the blind man had heard people spit as they walked by him, as a sign of
          disgust, for in that day they believed blindness was caused by a curse
          (). But this day, as he heard Jesus spit on the ground, it was for his
          healing.    '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And he said to the blind man, <JESUS>\u201CNow go and wash the clay
        from your eyes in the ritual pool of Siloam.\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]
        So he went and washed his face and as he came back, he could see for the
        first time in his life! "
      comments:
      - number: 9:7
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe pool of apostleship.\u201D    is a Hebrew word that
          means \u201Cto be sent\u201D or \u201Cto be commissioned\u201D\u2014the
          Greek word for \u201Capostle\u201D or \u201Capostleship\u201D is the closest
          meaning. The apostle of our faith is the Lord Jesus Christ who was sent
          from the Father. To wash in the Pool of Apostleship is to recognize the
          healing that flows from the One who was sent from heaven.      In the context
          of Jesus\u2019 teaching on the light of the world and mankind being in
          the dark, this miracle of giving sight to the blind man is a powerful proof
          of Jesus\u2019 words. Christ, in his birth, became a man of clay. When
          he applies this clay over our eyes and we wash in the water of his Word,
          our spiritual sight is restored.    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "This caused quite a stir among the people of the neighborhood, for
        they noticed the blind beggar was now seeing! They began to say to one another,
        \u201CIsn\u2019t this the blind man who once sat and begged?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Some said, \u201CNo, it can\u2019t be him!\u201D Others said, \u201CBut
        it looks just like him\u2014it has to be him!\u201D All the while the man
        kept insisting, \u201CI\u2019m the man who was blind!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Finally, they asked him, \u201CWhat has happened to you?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "He replied, \u201CI met the man named Jesus! He rubbed clay on my
        eyes and said, \u2018Go to the pool named Siloam and wash.\u2019 So I went
        and while I was washing the clay from my eyes I began to see for the very
        first time ever!\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 9:11
        content: '  See also vv.  ,  .    '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So the people of the neighborhood inquired, \u201CWhere is this man?\u201D\u201CI
        have no idea.\u201D the man replied."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So the people marched him over to the Pharisees to speak with them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "They were concerned because the miracle Jesus performed by making
        clay with his saliva and anointing the man\u2019s eyes happened on a Sabbath
        day, a day that no one was allowed to \u201Cwork.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then the Pharisees asked the man, \u201CHow did you have your sight
        restored?\u201DHe replied, \u201CA man anointed my eyes with clay, then I
        washed, and now I can see for the first time in my life!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then an argument broke out among the Pharisees over the healing of
        the blind man on the Sabbath. Some said, \u201CThis man who performed this
        healing is clearly not from God! He doesn\u2019t even observe the Sabbath!\u201D
        Others said, \u201CIf Jesus is just an ordinary sinner, [[COMMENT(0)]] how
        could he perform a miracle like that?\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 9:16
        content: "  Or \u201Ca sinning man.\u201D    "
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "This prompted them to turn on the man healed of blindness, putting
        him on the spot in front of them all, demanding an answer. They asked, \u201CWho
        do you say he is\u2014this man who opened your blind eyes?\u201D\u201CHe\u2019s
        a prophet of God!\u201D the man replied."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Still refusing to believe that the man had been healed and was truly
        blind from birth, the Jewish leaders called for the man\u2019s parents to
        be brought to them."
      comments: []
    - name: '19-20: '
      title: 
      number: 19-20
      content: "So they asked his parents, \u201CIs this your son?\u201D\u201CYes,\u201D
        they answered.\u201CWas he really born blind?\u201D\u201CYes, he was,\u201D
        they replied.So they pressed his parents to answer, \u201CThen how is it
        that he\u2019s now seeing?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19-20: '
      title: 
      number: 19-20
      content: "So they asked his parents, \u201CIs this your son?\u201D\u201CYes,\u201D
        they answered.\u201CWas he really born blind?\u201D\u201CYes, he was,\u201D
        they replied.So they pressed his parents to answer, \u201CThen how is it
        that he\u2019s now seeing?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CWe have no idea,\u201D they answered. \u201CWe don\u2019t know
        what happened to our son. Ask him, he\u2019s a mature adult. He can speak
        for himself.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '(Now the parents were obviously intimidated by the Jewish religious
        leaders, for they had already announced to the people that if anyone publicly
        confessed Jesus as the Messiah, they would be excommunicated. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "That\u2019s why they told them, \u201CAsk him, he\u2019s a mature
        adult. He can speak for himself.\u201D)"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "So once again they summoned the man who was healed of blindness and
        said to him, \u201CSwear to God to tell us the truth! [[COMMENT(0)]] We know
        the man who healed you is a sinful man! Do you agree?\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 9:24
        content: "  Or \u201CGive glory to God.\u201D This has been interpreted by
          some as an idiomatic saying, which would put the man under oath to testify
          to the truth.    "
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "The healed man replied, \u201CI have no idea what kind of man he
        is. All I know is that I was blind and now I can see for the first time in
        my life!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CBut what did he do to you?\u201D they asked. \u201CHow did
        he heal you?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "The man responded, \u201CI told you once and you didn\u2019t listen
        to me. Why do you make me repeat it? Are you wanting to be his followers
        too?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "This angered the Jewish leaders. They heaped insults on him, \u201CWe
        can tell you are one of his followers\u2014now we know it! We are true followers
        of Moses, "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "for we know that God spoke to Moses directly. But as for this one,
        we don\u2019t know where he\u2019s coming from!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CWell, what a surprise this is!\u201D the man said. \u201CYou
        don\u2019t even know where he comes from, but he healed my eyes and now I
        can see! "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "We know that God doesn\u2019t listen to sinners, but only to godly
        people who do his will. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Yet who has ever heard of a man born blind that was healed and given
        his eyesight for the very first time? '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "I tell you, if this man isn\u2019t from God, he wouldn\u2019t be
        able to heal me like he has!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Some of the Jewish leaders were enraged and said, \u201CJust who
        do you think you are to lecture us! You were born a blind, filthy sinner!\u201D
        So they threw the man out in the street."
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "When Jesus learned they had thrown him out, he went to find him and
        said to him, <JESUS>\u201CDo you believe in the Son of God?\u201D</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 9:35
        content: "  This is a common title of the Lord Jesus in the book of John.
          Although there are many reliable Greek manuscripts that have \u201Cthe
          Son of Man,\u201D the Aramaic and a few early Greek manuscripts have \u201Cthe
          Son of Elohim [God].\u201D    "
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "The man whose blind eyes were healed answered, \u201CWho is he, Master?
        Tell me so that I can place all my faith in him.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CYou\u2019re looking right at him. He\u2019s
        speaking with you. It\u2019s me, the one in front of you now.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Then the man threw himself at his feet and worshiped Jesus and said,
        \u201CLord, I believe in you!\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 9:38
        content: '  Although this man had never been able to read the Scriptures,
          he had faith in Jesus. Traditions and superficial knowledge of the Bible
          can actually blind our hearts if we do not believe in Jesus above all other
          religious dogmas. Many of those who knew the Scriptures refused to believe.
          The miracle of blind eyes opening is proof that God had come to us. See 
          .    '
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "And Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CI have come to judge those who think
        they see and make them blind. And for those who are blind, I have come to
        make them see.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Some of the Pharisees were standing nearby and overheard these words.
        They interrupted Jesus and said, \u201CYou mean to tell us that we are blind?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Jesus told them, <JESUS>\u201CIf you would acknowledge your blindness,
        then your sin would be removed. But now that you claim to see, your sin remains
        with you!\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 9:41
        content: "  Or \u201Cyour sin stands\u201D (rises up).  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Parable of the Kind Shepherd'
      title: The Parable of the Kind Shepherd
      number: 1
      content: "Jesus said to the Pharisees, <JESUS>\u201CListen to this eternal
        truth: The person who sneaks over the wall to enter into the sheep pen, rather
        than coming through the gate, reveals himself as a thief coming to steal.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '<JESUS>But the true Shepherd walks right up to the gate,</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '<JESUS>and because the gatekeeper knows who he is, he opens the gate
        to let him in.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>And the sheep recognize the
        voice of the true Shepherd, for he calls his own by name and leads them out,
        for they belong to him.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: 10:3
        content: "  In this parable the gatekeeper would represent John the Baptizer
          who recognized Jesus as the Shepherd. John opened the gate for him to be
          introduced to Israel at Jesus\u2019 baptism.    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '<JESUS>And when he has brought out all his sheep, he walks ahead
        of them and they will follow him, for they are familiar with his voice.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "<JESUS>But they will run away from strangers and never follow them
        because they know it\u2019s the voice of a stranger.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Jesus told the Pharisees this parable even though they didn\u2019t
        understand a word of what he meant. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 10:6
        content: "  They didn\u2019t understand this allegory of the Old Testament
          law as the sheepfold that became the religion of Judaism, like a pen that
          confined the people. Christ is the gate that not only allowed everyone
          in, but he let them out in the New Testament to enjoy all the riches of
          the pasture. The Holy Spirit is the gatekeeper and the false prophets and
          Pharisees are the thieves and robbers (). Remember that this chapter follows
          the healing of the blind man who was cast out of the \u201Csheep pen\u201D
          but accepted in Christ. See  . Jesus is the shepherd, the gate, and the
          pasture.    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So Jesus went over it again, <JESUS>\u201CI speak to you eternal
        truth: I am the Gate for the flock.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 10:7
        content: "  As translated from the Aramaic. There is a word play with \u201CI\u201D
          () and \u201Cflock\u201D (). As the gateway, he brings us to the Father
          and his kingdom realm. As the shepherd, he cares for us and shows us his
          loving heart.    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '<JESUS>All those who broke in before me are thieves who came to steal,</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>but the sheep never listened to them.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: 10:8
        content: "  The Old Testament refers to the kings of Israel and Judah as
          \u201Cshepherds.\u201D These kings along with false prophets are shepherds
          who don\u2019t always have God\u2019s heart for the sheep. After the healing
          of the blind man, the Pharisees refused to acknowledge Jesus\u2019 rightful
          place as shepherd of his flock, so the    would also refer to them.    "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '<JESUS>I am the Gateway.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>To enter
        through me is to experience life, freedom, and satisfaction.</JESUS>    '
      comments:
      - number: 10:9
        content: "  A sheep pen was an enclosure with walls and no roof that would
          often have the sheep of an entire village kept within. After the sheep
          were brought in for the night, it was common for the shepherd to sleep
          at the entrance so he could protect his sheep. Only the shepherds of the
          sheep would be recognized by that gatekeeper. Jesus is the one who will
          remain with his flock and keep his sheep living in peace and safety. His
          teaching (voice) will guard us from the unreliable teachers who want to
          steal our hearts and bind us to themselves. They steal and rob the affection
          that belongs only to Jesus, our kind shepherd.      Or \u201Cgo in and
          out and find pasture.\u201D    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "<JESUS>A thief has only one thing in mind\u2014he wants to steal,
        slaughter,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>and destroy. But I have come to</JESUS> 
        <JESUS>give you everything in abundance,</JESUS>    <JESUS>more than you
        expect</JESUS>  <JESUS>\u2014life in its fullness until you overflow!</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 10:10
        content: "  The Greek word    is not the usual word for \u201Ckill.\u201D
          It means \u201Csacrifice\u201D or \u201Cslaughter.\u201D      Implied in
          the Aramaic text.      Implied in the Greek text.    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '<JESUS>I am the Good</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>Shepherd who
        lays down my life as a sacrifice for the sheep.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: 10:11
        content: "  The word for \u201Cgood\u201D in Greek () can also mean \u201Cbeautiful,\u201D
          \u201Cvirtuous,\u201D \u201Cexcellent,\u201D \u201Cgenuine,\u201D or \u201Cbetter.\u201D
          (See  , Gr. 2570.) Jesus is also called the \u201CGreat Shepherd\u201D
          () and the \u201CShepherd-King\u201D ().    "
    - name: '12-13: '
      title: 
      number: 12-13
      content: <JESUS>But the worker who serves only for wages is not a real shepherd.
        Because he has no heart for the sheep he will run away and abandon them when
        he sees the wolf coming. And then the wolf mauls the sheep, drags them off,
        and scatters them.</JESUS>
      comments: []
    - name: '12-13: '
      title: 
      number: 12-13
      content: <JESUS>But the worker who serves only for wages is not a real shepherd.
        Because he has no heart for the sheep he will run away and abandon them when
        he sees the wolf coming. And then the wolf mauls the sheep, drags them off,
        and scatters them.</JESUS>
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CI alone am the Good Shepherd, and I know those whose
        hearts are mine, for they recognize me and know me,</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "<JESUS>just as my Father knows my heart and I know my Father\u2019s
        heart. I am ready to give my life for the sheep.</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CAnd I have other sheep that I will gather which are
        not of this Jewish flock. And I, their shepherd, must lead them too, and
        they will follow me and listen to my voice. And I will join them all into
        one flock with one shepherd.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 10:16
        content: "  This \u201Cone flock\u201D is the church made up of both Jews
          and non-Jews. See  ;  .    "
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThe Father has an intense love for me because I freely
        give my own life\u2014to raise it up again.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "<JESUS>I surrender my own life, and no one has the power to take
        my life from me. I have the authority to lay it down and the power to take
        it back again. This is the destiny my Father has set before me.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'This teaching set off another heated controversy among the Jewish
        leaders. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Many of them said, \u201CThis man is a demon-possessed lunatic! Why
        would anyone listen to a word he says?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Jesus at the Feast of Renewal'
      title: Jesus at the Feast of Renewal
      number: 21
      content: "But then there were others who weren\u2019t so sure: \u201CHis teaching
        is full of insight. These are not the ravings of a madman! How could a demonized
        man give sight to one born blind?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22-23: '
      title: 
      number: 22-23
      content: "The time came to observe the winter Feast of Renewal in Jerusalem.
        [[COMMENT(0)]] Jesus walked into the temple area under Solomon\u2019s covered
        walkway "
      comments:
      - number: "10:22\u201323"
        content: "  This is also known as the \u201CFeast of Dedication\u201D or
          \u201CThe Feast of Lights.\u201D The Aramaic word for \u201Cdedication\u201D
          is  , which is equivalent to the Hebrew word  . Contemporary Judaism recognizes
          this as Hanukkah, celebrated on Kislev 25 on the Jewish calendar. The Greek
          is literally \u201CThe Feast of Renewing\u201D to commemorate the miraculous
          renewing of oil that burned for eight days.    "
    - name: '22-23: '
      title: 
      number: 22-23
      content: "The time came to observe the winter Feast of Renewal in Jerusalem.
        [[COMMENT(0)]] Jesus walked into the temple area under Solomon\u2019s covered
        walkway "
      comments:
      - number: "10:22\u201323"
        content: "  This is also known as the \u201CFeast of Dedication\u201D or
          \u201CThe Feast of Lights.\u201D The Aramaic word for \u201Cdedication\u201D
          is  , which is equivalent to the Hebrew word  . Contemporary Judaism recognizes
          this as Hanukkah, celebrated on Kislev 25 on the Jewish calendar. The Greek
          is literally \u201CThe Feast of Renewing\u201D to commemorate the miraculous
          renewing of oil that burned for eight days.    "
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "when the Jewish leaders encircled him and said, \u201CHow much longer
        will you keep us in suspense? Tell us the truth and clarify this for us once
        and for all. Are you really the Messiah, the Anointed One?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Jesus answered them, <JESUS>\u201CI have told you the truth already
        and you did not believe me. The proof of who I am is revealed by all the
        miracles that I do in the name of my Father.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "<JESUS>Yet, you stubbornly refuse to follow me, because you are not
        my sheep. As I\u2019ve told you before:</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '<JESUS>My own sheep will hear my voice and I know each one, and they
        will follow me.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: '<JESUS>I give to them the gift of eternal life and they will never
        be lost and no one has the power to snatch them out of my hands.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "<JESUS>My Father, who has given them to me as his gift, is the mightiest
        of all, and no one has the power to snatch them from my Father\u2019s care.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "<JESUS>The Father and I are one.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'When they heard this, the Jewish leaders were so enraged that they
        picked up rocks to stone him to death. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "But Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CMy Father has empowered me to work many
        miracles and acts of mercy among you. So which one of them do you want to
        stone me for?\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "The Jewish leaders responded, \u201CWe\u2019re not stoning you for
        anything good you did\u2014it\u2019s because of your blasphemy! You\u2019re
        just a son of Adam, but you\u2019ve claimed to be God!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Jesus answered, <JESUS>\u201CIsn\u2019t it written in your Scriptures
        that God said, \u2018You are gods?\u2019</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>The
        Scriptures cannot be denied or found to be in error.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 10:34
        content: '  See  .    '
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "<JESUS>So if those who have the message of the Scriptures are said
        to be \u2018gods,\u2019 then why would you accuse me of blasphemy?</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "<JESUS>For I have been uniquely chosen by God and he is the one who
        sent me to you. How then could it be blasphemy for me to say, \u2018I am
        the Son of God!\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "<JESUS>If I\u2019m not doing the beautiful works that my Father sent
        me to do, then don\u2019t believe me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "<JESUS>But if you see me doing the beautiful works of God upon the
        earth, then you should at least believe the evidence of the miracles, even
        if you don\u2019t believe my words! Then you would come to experience me
        and be convinced that I am in the Father and the Father is in me.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Once again they attempted to seize him, but he escaped miraculously 
        [[COMMENT(0)]] from their clutches. '
      comments:
      - number: 10:39
        content: '  Implied in the context of being encircled by those with stones
          in their hands ready to kill him. It was clearly a miracle. He may have
          become invisible, transported himself to another location, or caused his
          accusers to be momentarily paralyzed or blinded as he slipped away.  '
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Then Jesus went back to the place where John had baptized him at
        the crossing of the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Many came out to where he was and said about him, \u201CEven though
        John didn\u2019t perform any miracles, everything he predicted about this
        man is true!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: And many people became followers of Jesus at the Jordan and believed
        in him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1-2: Lazarus Raised from the Dead'
      title: Lazarus Raised from the Dead
      number: 1-2
      content: "In the village of Bethany there was a man named Lazarus, and his
        sisters, Mary and Martha. Mary was the one who would anoint Jesus\u2019 feet
        with costly perfume and dry his feet with her long hair. One day Lazarus
        became very sick to the point of death. "
      comments: []
    - name: '1-2: Lazarus Raised from the Dead'
      title: Lazarus Raised from the Dead
      number: 1-2
      content: "In the village of Bethany there was a man named Lazarus, and his
        sisters, Mary and Martha. Mary was the one who would anoint Jesus\u2019 feet
        with costly perfume and dry his feet with her long hair. One day Lazarus
        became very sick to the point of death. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So his sisters sent a message to Jesus, \u201CLord, our brother Lazarus,
        the one you love, is very sick. Please come!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "When he heard this, he said, <JESUS>\u201CThis sickness will not
        end in death for Lazarus, but will bring glory and praise to God. This will
        reveal the greatness of the Son of God by what takes place.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '5-6: '
      title: 
      number: 5-6
      content: 'Now even though Jesus loved Mary, Martha, and Lazarus, he remained
        where he was for two more days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5-6: '
      title: 
      number: 5-6
      content: 'Now even though Jesus loved Mary, Martha, and Lazarus, he remained
        where he was for two more days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Finally, on the third day, he said to his disciples, <JESUS>\u201CCome.
        It\u2019s time to go to Bethany.\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 11:7
        content: "  Or \u201CJudea.\u201D    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CBut Teacher,\u201D they said to him, \u201Cdo you really want
        to go back there? It was just a short time ago the people of Judea were going
        to stone you!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9-10: '
      title: 
      number: 9-10
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CAre there not twelve hours of daylight</JESUS> 
        <JESUS>in every day?</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>You can go through a
        day without the fear of stumbling when you walk in the One who gives light
        to the world. But you will stumble when the light is not in you, for you\u2019ll
        be walking in the dark.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: "11:9\u201310"
        content: "  Jesus used a parable to respond to why he was not afraid to go
          where his life could be in danger. This is more than the sun, but \u201Cthe
          One who gives light to the world.\u201D    "
    - name: '9-10: '
      title: 
      number: 9-10
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CAre there not twelve hours of daylight</JESUS> 
        <JESUS>in every day?</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>You can go through a
        day without the fear of stumbling when you walk in the One who gives light
        to the world. But you will stumble when the light is not in you, for you\u2019ll
        be walking in the dark.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: "11:9\u201310"
        content: "  Jesus used a parable to respond to why he was not afraid to go
          where his life could be in danger. This is more than the sun, but \u201Cthe
          One who gives light to the world.\u201D    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Jesus added, <JESUS>\u201CLazarus, our friend, has just fallen
        asleep.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>It\u2019s time that I go and awaken
        him.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 11:11
        content: "  Jesus was stating an obvious euphemism. Lazarus \u201Csleeping\u201D
          means that he has died. To \u201Cawaken\u201D him means that Jesus would
          raise him from the dead.    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "When they heard this, the disciples replied, \u201CLord, if he has
        just fallen asleep, then he\u2019ll get better.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Jesus was speaking about Lazarus\u2019 death, but the disciples presumed
        he was talking about natural sleep."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Jesus made it plain to them, <JESUS>\u201CLazarus is dead.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "<JESUS>And for your sake, I\u2019m glad I wasn\u2019t there,</JESUS> 
        <JESUS>because now you have another opportunity to see who I am</JESUS> 
        <JESUS>so that you will learn to trust in me. Come, let\u2019s go and see
        him.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So Thomas, nicknamed the Twin, remarked to the other disciples, \u201CLet\u2019s
        go so that we can die with him.\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 11:16
        content: '  It is likely that Thomas was expressing pessimism about the fate
          of Jesus going back into the region where he was threatened with death.    '
    - name: '17-18: '
      title: 
      number: 17-18
      content: 'Now when they arrived at Bethany, which was only about two miles
        from Jerusalem, Jesus found that Lazarus had already been in the tomb for
        four days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17-18: '
      title: 
      number: 17-18
      content: 'Now when they arrived at Bethany, which was only about two miles
        from Jerusalem, Jesus found that Lazarus had already been in the tomb for
        four days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Many friends [[COMMENT(0)]] of Mary and Martha had come from the
        region to console them over the loss of their brother. '
      comments:
      - number: 11:19
        content: "  Or \u201CJews.\u201D    "
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: And when Martha heard that Jesus was approaching the village, she
        went out to meet him, but Mary stayed in the house.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Martha said to Jesus, \u201CMy Lord, if only you had come sooner,
        my brother wouldn\u2019t have died. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But I know that if you were to ask God for anything, he would do
        it for you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Jesus told her, <JESUS>\u201CYour brother will rise and live.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "She replied, \u201CYes, I know he will rise with everyone else on
        resurrection day.\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 11:24
        content: "  Or \u201Cat the last day.\u201D    "
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CMartha,\u201D</JESUS> Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201C</JESUS><JESUS>You
        don\u2019t have to wait until then.</JESUS>  <JESUS>I am</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>the Resurrection,</JESUS>    <JESUS>and I am Life Eternal. Anyone
        who clings to me in faith, even though he dies, will live forever.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 11:25
        content: "  The words    in the Aramaic are a clear statement of Christ\u2019s
          deity: \u201CI am the living God, the Resurrection and the Life!\u201D     
          The Aramaic uses a word that is related linguistically to the name Noah,
          who was symbolically \u201Cresurrected\u201D from the flood as the life-giver
          to those who repopulated the earth. Resurrection is superior to life, for
          life can be defeated and ended. But resurrection overcomes. Life is the
          power to exist, but resurrection is the power to conquer all, even death
          itself. Believers must learn to live in Christ our Life, but also, Christ
          our Resurrection to conquer all things. See  .    "
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "<JESUS>And the one who lives by believing in me will never die.</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>Do you believe this?\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 11:26
        content: "  This is very emphatic in the Greek, \u201Cnever die forever!\u201D     
          John presents Jesus as the great Savior who saves us from sin (), blindness
          (), and death ().    "
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then Martha replied, \u201CYes, Lord, I do! I\u2019ve always believed
        that you are the Anointed One, the Son of God who has come into the world
        for us!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then she left and hurried off to her sister, Mary, and called her
        aside from all the mourners and whispered to her, \u201CThe Master is here
        and he\u2019s asking for you.\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 11:28
        content: "  This is one of the most beautiful things that ever could be said
          to you: \u201CThe Master is here and he\u2019s asking for you.\u201D Mary\u2019s
          response must be ours: \u201Cshe quickly went off to find him\u201D (v. 
          ).    "
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'So when Mary heard this, she quickly went off to find him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'for Jesus was lingering outside the village at the same spot where
        Martha met him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Now when Mary\u2019s friends who were comforting her [[COMMENT(0)]]
        noticed how quickly she ran out of the house, they followed her, assuming
        she was going to the tomb of her brother to mourn."
      comments:
      - number: 11:31
        content: "  The Aramaic is \u201CMary\u2019s friends who loved her.\u201D    "
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "When Mary finally found Jesus outside the village, she fell at his
        feet in tears and said, \u201CLord, if only you had been here, my brother
        would not have died.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'When Jesus looked at Mary and saw her weeping at his feet, and all
        her friends who were with her grieving, he shuddered with emotion [[COMMENT(0)]]
        and was deeply moved with tenderness and compassion. '
      comments:
      - number: 11:33
        content: "  The Greek word used here () can also mean \u201Cindignant and
          stirred with anger.\u201D Was he angry at the mourners? Not at all. He
          was angry over the work of the devil in taking the life of his friend,
          Lazarus. The Aramaic, however, has no connotation of indignation, only
          tenderness and compassion (lit. \u201Chis heart melted with compassion\u201D).    "
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "He said to them, <JESUS>\u201CWhere did you bury him?\u201D</JESUS>\u201CLord,
        come with us and we\u2019ll show you,\u201D they replied."
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Then tears streamed down Jesus\u2019 face."
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Seeing Jesus weep caused many of the mourners to say, \u201CLook
        how much he loved Lazarus.\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 11:36
        content: "  The Aramaic is \u201Chow much mercy he felt for Lazarus.\u201D    "
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Yet others said, \u201CIsn\u2019t this the One who opens blind eyes?
        Why didn\u2019t he do something to keep Lazarus from dying?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Then Jesus, with intense emotions, came to the tomb\u2014a cave with
        a stone placed over its entrance. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Jesus told them, <JESUS>\u201CRoll away the stone.\u201D</JESUS>Then
        Martha said, \u201CBut Lord, it\u2019s been four days since he died\u2014by
        now his body is already decomposing!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Jesus looked at her and said, <JESUS>\u201CDidn\u2019t I tell you
        that if you will believe in me, you will see God unveil his power?\u201D</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 11:40
        content: "  Or \u201Cyou would see the glory of God.\u201D    "
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "So they rolled away the heavy stone. Jesus gazed into heaven and
        said, <JESUS>\u201CFather, thank you</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>that
        you have heard my prayer,</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 11:41
        content: "  Resurrection power is released when we give thanks to God. Jesus
          stood at Lazarus\u2019 tomb and gave thanks, then commanded him to arise.
          Giving thanks to God has more power than you can ever imagine. Have you
          stopped to thank God yet today?    "
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "<JESUS>for you listen to every word I speak. Now, so that these who
        stand here with me will believe that you have sent me to the earth as your
        messenger,</JESUS>  <JESUS>I will use the power you have given me.</JESUS><JESUS>\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "Then with a loud voice Jesus shouted with authority: <JESUS>\u201CLazarus!
        Come out of the tomb!\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "Then in front of everyone, Lazarus, who had died four days earlier,
        slowly hobbled out\u2014he still had grave clothes tightly wrapped around
        his hands and feet and covering his face! Jesus said to them, <JESUS>\u201CUnwrap
        him and let him loose.\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 11:44
        content: '  Burial customs in the ancient Near East were to wrap the corpse
          in white cotton cloths from the neck to the feet. The head was then covered
          with a large handkerchief.    '
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'From that day forward many of those [[COMMENT(0)]] who had come to
        visit Mary believed in him, for they had seen with their own eyes this amazing
        miracle! '
      comments:
      - number: 11:45
        content: "  Or \u201CJews.\u201D    "
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: But a few went back to inform the Pharisees about what Jesus had done.
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "So the Pharisees and the chief priests called a special meeting of
        the High Council [[COMMENT(0)]] and said, \u201CSo what are we going to do
        about this man? Look at all the great miracles he\u2019s performing! "
      comments:
      - number: 11:47
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe Sanhedrin.\u201D This was the Great Sanhedrin, equivalent
          to a Jewish court, which would be comprised of seventy men who would judge
          Jewish religious matters.    "
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "If we allow him to continue like this, everyone will believe in him.
        And the Romans will take action and destroy both our country and our people!\u201D
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 11:48
        content: "  As translated from the Aramaic. The Greek is translated \u201Cour
          place [position] and our nation.\u201D \u201COur place\u201D could refer
          to the temple.    "
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "Now Caiaphas, the high priest that year, spoke up and said, \u201CYou
        don\u2019t understand a thing! "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "Don\u2019t you realize we\u2019d be much better off if this one man
        were to die for the people than for the whole nation to perish?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "(This prophecy that Jesus was destined to die [[COMMENT(0)]] for
        the Jewish people didn\u2019t come from Caiaphas himself, but he was moved
        by God to prophesy as the chief priest. "
      comments:
      - number: 11:51
        content: '  As translated from the Aramaic.    '
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "And Jesus\u2019 death would not be for the Jewish people only, but
        to gather together God\u2019s children scattered around the world and unite
        them as one.) [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 11:52
        content: '  See  .    '
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: So from that day on, they were committed to killing Jesus.
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: For this reason Jesus no longer went out in public among the Jews.
        But he went in the wilderness to a village called Ephraim, [[COMMENT(0)]]
        where he secluded himself with his disciples.
      comments:
      - number: 11:54
        content: "  The Aramaic can be translated \u201Cthe fortress city of Ephraim\u201D
          or \u201Cthe mill called Ephraim.\u201D Ephraim means \u201Cdouble fruitfulness.\u201D
          Some believe this location is the present town of Et-Taiyibeh, which would
          make it about fourteen miles (twenty-two kilometers) northeast of Jerusalem.  "
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'Now the time came for the Passover preparations, and many from the
        countryside went to Jerusalem for their ceremonial cleansing before the feast
        began. '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: "And all the people kept looking out for Jesus, expecting him to come
        to the city. They said to themselves while they waited in the temple courts,
        \u201CDo you think that he will dare come to the feast?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: For the leading priests and the Pharisees had given orders that they
        be informed immediately if anyone saw Jesus, so they could seize and arrest
        him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Mary Anoints Jesus'
      title: Mary Anoints Jesus
      number: 1
      content: 'Six days before the Passover began, Jesus went back to Bethany, the
        town where he raised Lazarus from the dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'They had prepared a supper for Jesus. [[COMMENT(0)]] Martha served,
        and Lazarus and Mary were among those at the table. '
      comments:
      - number: 12:2
        content: '  We see from    that this took place at the house of Simon, the
          leper Jesus had healed.    '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Mary picked up an alabaster [[COMMENT(0)]] jar filled with nearly
        a liter  of extremely rare and costly perfume\u2014the purest extract of
        nard,  and she anointed Jesus\u2019 feet. Then she wiped them dry with her
        long hair. And the fragrance of the costly oil filled the house.   "
      comments:
      - number: 12:3
        content: "  As translated from the Aramaic.      Or \u201Cnearly a pound.\u201D     
          Nard is an extremely expensive perfume taken from the root and spike of
          the nard plant found in northern India. See  ;  .      This fragrance,
          usually associated with a king, was upon Jesus\u2019 feet as he stood before
          his accusers and as the soldiers pierced his feet with a nail. It is possible
          they would all have smelled the fragrance of this costly perfume.    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But Judas the locksmith, [[COMMENT(0)]] Simon\u2019s son, the betrayer,
        spoke up and said, "
      comments:
      - number: 12:4
        content: "  Or \u201CIscariot,\u201D a word related linguistically to \u201Ca
          lock\u201D or \u201Clocksmith.\u201D Judas apparently held the key to the
          lockbox of funds to support Jesus\u2019 ministry. See ch.    and footnote.    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CWhat a waste! We could have sold this perfume for a fortune
        [[COMMENT(0)]] and given the money to the poor!\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 12:5
        content: "  Or \u201Cthree hundred silver coins (denarii),\u201D which would
          be equal to a year\u2019s salary.    "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "(In fact, Judas had no heart for the poor. He only said this because
        he was a thief and in charge of the money case. He would steal money whenever
        he wanted from the funds given to support Jesus\u2019 ministry.)"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Jesus said to Judas, <JESUS>\u201CLeave her alone! She has saved
        it for the time of my burial.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 12:7
        content: "  The Aramaic could be translated \u201CLet her conduct my burial
          day ceremony.\u201D It is possible that this rare and expensive perfume
          could have been her family\u2019s treasure or her inheritance.    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "<JESUS>You\u2019ll always have the poor with you;</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>but you won\u2019t always have me.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 12:8
        content: "  That is, \u201CYou will have many opportunities to help the poor,
          but you will not always have me.\u201D See also  .    "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'When the word got out that Jesus was not far from Jerusalem, a large
        crowd came out to see him, and they also wanted to see Lazarus, the man Jesus
        had raised from the dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'This prompted the chief priests to seal their plans to do away with
        both Jesus and Lazarus, [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 12:10
        content: "  Darkness has only one way to deal with the truth\u2014kill it.    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: for his miracle testimony was irrefutable and was persuading many
        of the Jews living in Jerusalem to believe in Jesus.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The next day the news that Jesus was on his way to Jerusalem swept
        through the massive crowd gathered for the feast. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So they took palm branches [[COMMENT(0)]] and went out to meet him.
        Everyone was shouting, \u201CLord, be our Savior!  Blessed is the one who
        comes to us sent from <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>,  the King of Israel!\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 12:13
        content: "  The palm tree is a symbol of triumph, victory over death. Palms
          grow in the desert and overcome the arid climate. Deborah sat under a palm
          tree as a judge in Israel and received the strategy to overcome her enemies.
          See  .      Or \u201CHosanna!\u201D      See  .    "
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then Jesus found a young donkey and rode on it to fulfill what was
        prophesied: '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CPeople of Zion, [[COMMENT(0)]] have no fear! Look\u2014it\u2019s
        your king coming to you riding on a young donkey!\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: 12:15
        content: "  Or \u201CDaughter of Zion.\u201D      See  . Conquering kings
          would ride on a warhorse or in a golden chariot, but Jesus rode into Jerusalem
          on a domesticated donkey. He is the King of Peace.    "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Now Jesus\u2019 disciples didn\u2019t fully understand the importance
        of what was taking place, but after he was raised and exalted into glory,
        they understood how Jesus fulfilled all the prophecies in the Scriptures
        that were written about him."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'All the eyewitnesses of the miracle Jesus performed when he called
        Lazarus out of the tomb and raised him from the dead kept spreading the news
        about Jesus to everyone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The news of this miracle of resurrection caused the crowds to swell
        as great numbers of people welcomed him into the city with joy. [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 12:18
        content: "  The Greek is \u201Cthe crowd went out to meet him.\u201D The
          Aramaic is \u201Cgreat crowds went in front of him.\u201D    "
    - name: '19: True Seekers'
      title: True Seekers
      number: 19
      content: "But the Pharisees were disturbed by this and said to each other,
        \u201CWe won\u2019t be able to stop this. [[COMMENT(0)]] The whole world
        is going to run after him!\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 12:19
        content: "  The Aramaic is \u201CSee, you have lost your influence.\u201D    "
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Now there were a number of foreigners from among the nations who
        were worshipers at the feast. [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 12:20
        content: "  As translated from the Aramaic. The Greek text states they were
          \u201CGreeks.\u201D    "
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "They went to Philip (who came from the village of Bethsaida in Galilee)
        and they asked him, \u201CWould you take us to see Jesus? We want to see
        him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: So Philip went to find Andrew, and then they both went to inform Jesus.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 12:22
        content: '  See  .    '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "He replied to them, <JESUS>\u201CNow is the time for the Son of Man
        to be glorified.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "<JESUS>Let me make this clear:</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>A
        single grain of wheat will never be more than a single grain of wheat unless
        it drops into the ground and dies. Because then it sprouts and produces</JESUS>   
        <JESUS>a great harvest of wheat\u2014all because one grain</JESUS>    <JESUS>died.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 12:24
        content: "  The Aramaic is translated \u201CTimeless truth I say to you.\u201D     
          The Aramaic has an interesting word play with \u201Cit dies\u201D () and
          \u201Cit produces\u201D ().      The \u201Cone grain\u201D is Jesus Christ,
          who will within days be offered as the sacrifice for sin on Calvary\u2019s
          cross. He will \u201Cdrop\u201D into the ground as \u201Ca grain of wheat\u201D
          and bring forth a great \u201Charvest\u201D of \u201Cseeds.\u201D This
          parable given to Philip and Andrew was meant to be Jesus\u2019 reply to
          the request by the non-Jewish seekers to see Jesus. Christ\u2019s answer?
          \u201CThey will see me through you. As you follow me, you will also experience
          the dying and birthing experience.\u201D The harvest among the nations
          will come when we follow Jesus where he goes.      The Aramaic is translated
          \u201Cif it dies, it will bring forth a great rebirth.\u201D    "
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThe person who loves his life and pampers himself will
        miss true life! But the one who detaches his life from this world and abandons
        himself to me, will find true life and enjoy it forever!</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: <JESUS>If you want to be my disciple, follow me and you will go where
        I am going.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>And if you truly follow me as
        my disciple,</JESUS>    <JESUS>the Father will shower his favor upon your
        life.</JESUS>
      comments:
      - number: 12:26
        content: "  The implication in the text is that a life of full surrender
          to God will make us \u201Ca grain of wheat\u201D that multiplies into a
          \u201Charvest.\u201D The Greek text can be translated \u201CIf anyone ministers
          to me (materially provides for me), where I am, my minister will be there
          too.\u201D      Or \u201Cmaterially provides for me.\u201D    "
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CEven though I am torn within, and my soul is in turmoil,
        I will not ask the Father to rescue me from this hour of trial. For I have
        come to fulfill my purpose</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]<JESUS>\u2014</JESUS><JESUS>to
        offer myself to God.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 12:27
        content: "  The Aramaic is translated \u201Cto fulfill this hour I have come.\u201D    "
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "<JESUS>So, Father, bring glory to your name!\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]
        Then suddenly a booming voice was heard from the sky,\u201CI have glorified
        my name! And I will glorify it through you again!\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 12:28
        content: "  Some later manuscripts have \u201CFather, bring glory to your
          Son.\u201D One of the oldest manuscripts reads \u201CFather, bring glory
          to your name with the glory that I had with you before the world was created.\u201D
          The majority of reliable manuscripts have \u201CFather, bring glory to
          your name.\u201D    "
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "The audible voice of God startled the crowd standing nearby. Some
        thought it was only thunder, yet others said, \u201CAn angel just spoke to
        him!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then Jesus told them, <JESUS>\u201CThe voice you heard was not for
        my benefit, but for yours\u2014</JESUS><JESUS>to help you believe.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: '<JESUS>From this moment on, everything in this world is about to
        change,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>for the ruler of this dark world</JESUS>   
        <JESUS>will be overthrown.</JESUS>    '
      comments:
      - number: 12:31
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe time of judging the world (system) has come.\u201D
          The judging of the world is the overthrow of the kingdom of darkness. The
          preaching of the gospel of Jesus Christ is passing a sentence of judgment
          on this fallen world and declaring treason in the kingdom of darkness.
          Everything changes because of the cross\u2014the hinge of history.     
          An obvious reference to Satan.      Or \u201Cdriven into exile.\u201D    "
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "<JESUS>And I will do this</JESUS>  <JESUS>when I am lifted up off
        the ground</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>and when I draw the hearts of
        people</JESUS>    <JESUS>to gather them to me.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 12:32
        content: "  The Aramaic phrase \u201Clifted up\u201D is another way of saying
          \u201Clifted up in crucifixion.\u201D The Greek implies being lifted up
          from beneath the earth (resurrection).      Or \u201CI will draw all things
          to myself\u201D or \u201CI will bundle everyone/everything next to me.\u201D
          Jesus also drew all our judgment to himself when he died for our sins.
          The Judge became the payment for the guilty.    "
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: He said this to indicate that he would die by being lifted up on the
        cross. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 12:33
        content: "  Or \u201Cto clarify what kind of death he would die.\u201D    "
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "People from the crowd spoke up and said, \u201CDie? How could the
        Anointed One die? The Word of God says that the Anointed One will live with
        us forever, [[COMMENT(0)]] but you just said that the Son of Man must be
        lifted up from the earth.  And who is this Son of Man anyway?\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 12:34
        content: '  See  ;  ;  ;  .      It was obvious to the crowd that Jesus being
          lifted up was a reference to the cross.    '
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CYou will have the light shining with
        you for only a little while longer. While you still have me, walk in the
        light, so that the darkness doesn\u2019t overtake you. For when you walk
        in the dark you have no idea where you\u2019re going.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: The Unbelief of the Crowd'
      title: The Unbelief of the Crowd
      number: 36
      content: "<JESUS>So believe and cling to the light while I am with you, so
        that you will become children of light.\u201D</JESUS> After saying this,
        Jesus then entered into the crowd and hid himself from them."
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Even with the overwhelming evidence of all the many signs and wonders
        that Jesus had performed in front of them, his critics still refused to believe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: This fulfilled the prophecy given by Isaiah:Lord, who has believed
        our message? Who has seen the unveiling of your great power? [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 12:38
        content: "  Or \u201CTo whom is the arm of the Lord revealed.\u201D The arm
          of the Lord is a metaphor for God\u2019s great power. The word for \u201Crevealed\u201D
          means \u201Cto unveil.\u201D See  .    "
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And the people were not able to believe, for Isaiah also prophesied:'
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'God has blinded their eyes and hardened their hearts [[COMMENT(0)]]
        to the truth. So with their eyes and hearts closed they cannot understand
        the truth nor turn to me so that I could instantly cleanse and heal them. '
      comments:
      - number: 12:40
        content: "  Or \u201Cclosed their minds.\u201D The Aramaic is translated
          \u201Cdarkened their hearts.\u201D The Aramaic indicates that they did
          this to themselves, rather than God doing this.      The Aramaic is translated
          \u201Ccleansed\u201D; the Greek is translated \u201Chealed.\u201D Both
          are included here. See  .    "
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Isaiah said these things because he had seen and experienced the
        splendor of Jesus [[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>  </smallcaps> and prophesied
        about him. '
      comments:
      - number: 12:41
        content: "  See  . This is a profound statement that Isaiah saw Jesus Christ
          when he was taken into heaven and encountered the Lord  on the throne.
          This \u201CLord high and exalted\u201D was none less than Jesus Christ
          before he became a man.    "
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "Yet there were many Jewish leaders who believed in Jesus, but because
        they feared the Pharisees they kept it secret, so they wouldn\u2019t be ostracized
        by the assembly of the Jews. "
      comments: []
    - name: "43: Jesus\u2019 Last Public Teaching"
      title: "Jesus\u2019 Last Public Teaching"
      number: 43
      content: For they loved the glory that men could give them rather than the
        glory that came from God!
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "Jesus shouted out passionately, <JESUS>\u201CTo believe in me is
        to also believe in God who sent me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: '<JESUS>For when you look at me you are seeing the One who sent me.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: '<JESUS>I have come as a light to shine in this dark world so that
        all who trust in me will no longer wander in darkness.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: '<JESUS>If you hear my words and refuse to follow them, I do not judge
        you. For I have not come to judge you but to save you.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: '<JESUS>If you reject me and refuse to follow my words,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>you already have a judge. The message of truth I have given you will
        rise up to judge you at the Day of Judgment.</JESUS>    '
      comments:
      - number: 12:48
        content: "  This is the plural form of the Greek word    and would refer
          to all that Jesus taught.      Or \u201Cat the last day.\u201D    "
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "<JESUS>For I\u2019m not speaking as someone who is self-appointed,
        but I speak by the authority of the Father himself who sent me, and who instructed
        me what to say.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "<JESUS>And I know that the Father\u2019s commands result</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>in eternal life, and that\u2019s why I speak the very
        words I\u2019ve heard him speak.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 12:50
        content: "  Or in the Aramaic \u201Crepresent.\u201D  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Washes Feet'
      title: Jesus Washes Feet
      number: 1
      content: "Jesus knew that the night before Passover would be his last night
        on earth before leaving this world to return to the Father\u2019s side. All
        throughout his time with his disciples, Jesus had demonstrated a deep and
        tender love for them. And now he longed to show them the full measure of
        his love. [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 13:1
        content: "  Or \u201Che loved them to the very end.\u201D    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Before their evening meal had begun, the accuser [[COMMENT(0)]] had
        already deeply embedded betrayal  into the heart of Judas Iscariot, the son
        of Simon.
      comments:
      - number: 13:2
        content: "  Or \u201Cdevil.\u201D      Or \u201Cthat he should betray Jesus.\u201D
          The Aramaic is \u201CSatan arose in the heart of Judas to betray Jesus.\u201D    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now Jesus was fully aware that the Father had placed all things under
        his control, for he had come from God and was about to go back to be with
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So he got up from the meal and took off his outer robe, and took
        a towel and wrapped it around his waist. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then he poured water into a basin and began to wash the disciples\u2019
        dirty feet and dry them with his towel. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 13:5
        content: "  Jesus knew that betrayal was hiding in Judas\u2019 heart, yet
          our Master still washed his feet.    "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But when Jesus got to Simon Peter, he objected and said, \u201CI
        can\u2019t let you wash my dirty feet\u2014you\u2019re my Lord!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CYou don\u2019t understand yet the meaning
        of what I\u2019m doing, but soon it will be clear to you.\u201D</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 13:7
        content: "  By removing their sandals and washing their feet, Jesus was showing
          them that he was granting them a new inheritance\u2014his own. The sandal
          is often used in covenants of inheritance in Hebrew culture. Every defilement
          would be removed so that they could \u201Cplace the sole of their feet\u201D
          upon the new covenant inheritance. See  ;  . God likewise told Moses to
          remove his sandals (), for he was about to receive a new inheritance\u2014the
          holiness of God and the authority that came with it.    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Peter looked at Jesus and said, \u201CYou\u2019ll never wash my dirty
        feet\u2014never!\u201D<JESUS>\u201CBut Peter, if you don\u2019t allow me
        to wash your feet,\u201D</JESUS> Jesus responded, <JESUS>\u201Cthen you will
        not be able to share life with me.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So Peter said, \u201CLord, in that case, don\u2019t just wash my
        feet, wash my hands and my head too!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Jesus said to him, <JESUS>\u201CYou are already clean. You\u2019ve
        been washed completely and you just need your feet to be cleansed\u2014but
        that can\u2019t be said of all of you.\u201D</JESUS> For Jesus knew which
        one was about to betray him, "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "and that\u2019s why he told them that not all of them were clean."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "After washing their feet, he put his robe on and returned to his
        place at the table. [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>\u201CDo you understand what I
        just did?\u201D</JESUS> Jesus said. "
      comments:
      - number: 13:12
        content: '  There has never been a nobleman, a teacher, or a king that loves
          and serves his servants like Jesus.    '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CYou\u2019ve called me your teacher and lord, and you\u2019re
        right, for that\u2019s who I am.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14-15: '
      title: 
      number: 14-15
      content: "<JESUS>So if I\u2019m your teacher and lord and have just washed
        your dirty feet, then you should follow the example that I\u2019ve set for
        you and wash one another\u2019s dirty feet. Now do for each other what I
        have just done for you.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14-15: '
      title: 
      number: 14-15
      content: "<JESUS>So if I\u2019m your teacher and lord and have just washed
        your dirty feet, then you should follow the example that I\u2019ve set for
        you and wash one another\u2019s dirty feet. Now do for each other what I
        have just done for you.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '<JESUS>I speak to you timeless truth: a servant is not superior to
        his master, and an apostle is never greater than the one who sent him.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Jesus Predicts His Betrayal'
      title: Jesus Predicts His Betrayal
      number: 17
      content: "<JESUS>So now put into practice what I have done for you, and you
        will experience a life of happiness enriched with untold blessings!\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CI don\u2019t refer to all of you when I tell you these
        things, for I know the ones I\u2019ve chosen\u2014to fulfill the Scripture
        that says, \u2018The one who shared supper with me treacherously betrays
        me.\u2019</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 13:18
        content: "  Or \u201Chas lifted up his heel against me.\u201D The Greek text
          preserves the idiom of  , which speaks of a treacherous betrayal. In the
          Semitic culture it is the greatest breach of etiquette to sit and eat with
          a friend and then later betray them. This is why many would never eat with
          someone they were not on good terms with. See also footnotes on  .    "
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '<JESUS>I am telling you this now, before it happens, so that when
        the prophecy comes to pass you will be convinced that I AM.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 13:19
        content: "  Or \u201CI Am the One\u201D or \u201CI AM Who I AM.\u201D Jesus
          once again equated himself with the I Am.    "
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CListen to this timeless truth: whoever receives the
        messenger I send receives me, and the one who receives me receives the Father</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>who sent me.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 13:20
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe One.\u201D By implication, this is the Father.    "
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Jesus was moved deeply in his spirit. [[COMMENT(0)]] Looking
        at his disciples, he announced, <JESUS>\u201CI tell you the truth\u2014one
        of you is about to betray me.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 13:21
        content: "  As translated from the Greek. The Aramaic describes Jesus\u2019
          emotion as \u201Cfeeling a profound tenderness\u201D or \u201Chis spirit
          felt a longing.\u201D We can conclude that everything within our Lord Jesus
          was moved deeply by the thought of being betrayed by one of his beloved
          disciples.    "
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Eyeing each other, his disciples puzzled over which one of them could
        do such a thing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The disciple that Jesus dearly loved [[COMMENT(0)]] was at the right
        of him at the table  and was leaning his head on Jesus. '
      comments:
      - number: 13:23
        content: "  The Aramaic is \u201Cthe one Jesus showed mercy to.\u201D This
          was obviously John, the one who wrote this Gospel. Remember, you too can
          say, \u201CI am the disciple who Jesus dearly loves and shows mercy to.\u201D     
          This could be a figure of speech for \u201Cthe place of honor.\u201D    "
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Peter gestured to this disciple to ask Jesus who it was he was referring
        to. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then the dearly loved disciple leaned into Jesus\u2019 chest and
        whispered, \u201CMaster, who is it?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThe one I give this piece of bread to after I\u2019ve
        dipped it in the bowl,\u201D</JESUS> Jesus replied. Then he dipped the piece
        of bread into the bowl and handed it to Judas Iscariot, the son of Simon.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 13:26
        content: '  This was culturally an act of cherished friendship and intimacy,
          to hand over choice bits of food to a friend. This is the love of Christ,
          to give food to his enemy. It is no wonder Satan entered his heart after
          Judas ate the bread handed to him by his friend. For how can one accept
          the gift of true friendship and still hold on to treachery and the spirit
          of betrayal?    '
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And when Judas ate the piece of bread, Satan [[COMMENT(0)]] entered
        him. Then Jesus looked at Judas and said, <JESUS>\u201CWhat you are planning
        to do, go do it now.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 13:27
        content: "  This is an Aramaic word that means \u201Cadversary.\u201D    "
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'None of those around the table realized what was happening. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Some thought that Judas, their trusted treasurer, was being told
        to go buy what was needed for the Passover celebration, or perhaps to go
        give something to the poor. '
      comments: []
    - name: "30: Jesus Predicts Peter\u2019s Denial"
      title: "Jesus Predicts Peter\u2019s Denial"
      number: 30
      content: So Judas left quickly and went out into the dark night to betray Jesus.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "After Judas left the room, Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CThe time has
        come for the glory of God to surround the Son of Man, and God will be greatly
        glorified through what happens to me.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 13:31
        content: "  Or \u201CThe Son of Man was glorified and the Father was glorified
          by him.\u201D    "
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: <JESUS>And very soon God will unveil the glory of the Son of Man.</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 13:32
        content: "  Or \u201CSince God is glorified in him (the Son of Man) God will
          also glorify him in himself, and glorify him immediately.\u201D The Greek
          text has the word    (\u201Cglory\u201D or \u201Chonor\u201D) five times
          in vv.  . This repetition would mean that it speaks of more than simply
          honor. It is the clear statement of the exchange of glory between God and
          his Son, Jesus Christ.    "
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CMy dear friends,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>I only
        have a brief time left to be with you. And then you will search and long
        for me. But I tell you what I told the Jewish leaders: you\u2019ll not be
        able to come where I am.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 13:33
        content: "  Or \u201Cchildren.\u201D      See  .    "
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CSo I give you now a new</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>commandment:
        Love each other just as much as I have loved you.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 13:34
        content: '  Jesus set a new standard of love before his followers. Although
          the Old Testament does instruct us to love one another (,  ;  ), Jesus
          now gives the commandment to use his standard of love for us as the true
          measurement of love as we care for one another.    '
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "<JESUS>For when you demonstrate the same love I have for you by loving
        one another, everyone will know that you\u2019re my true followers.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Peter interjected, \u201CBut, Master, where are you going?\u201DJesus
        replied, <JESUS>\u201CWhere I am going you won\u2019t be able to follow,
        but one day you will follow me there.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Peter [[COMMENT(0)]] said, \u201CWhat do you mean I\u2019m not able
        to follow you now? I would sacrifice my life to die for you!\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: 13:37
        content: "  The Aramaic is translated \u201CSimon the Rock.\u201D      The
          Aramaic uses the word \u201Cconsecrate,\u201D which means to offer up a
          sacrifice. Peter implied that he would willingly offer himself in Jesus\u2019
          place.    "
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Jesus answered, <JESUS>\u201CWould you really lay down your life
        for me, Peter? Here\u2019s the absolute truth: Before the rooster crows in
        the morning, you will say three times that you don\u2019t even know me!\u201D</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 13:38
        content: "  Peter, like all of us, resisted the acknowledgment of his weakness
          and chose to cling to the illusion of strength. Peter was given the sign
          of a rooster crowing, for that is what he was. He was like a crowing rooster,
          strutting in pride. \u201CRocky\u201D got cocky and forgot where true strength
          is found.  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Comforts His Disciples'
      title: Jesus Comforts His Disciples
      number: 1
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CDon\u2019t worry or surrender to your fear.</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>For you\u2019ve believed in God, now trust and believe
        in me also.</JESUS>    "
      comments:
      - number: 14:1
        content: "  Or \u201CDon\u2019t let your hearts be distressed.\u201D The
          Aramaic is translated \u201CLet not your heart flutter.\u201D      Or \u201CBelieve
          in God and believe in me.\u201D    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "<JESUS>My Father\u2019s house has many dwelling places.</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>If it were otherwise, I would tell you plainly, because
        I go</JESUS>    <JESUS>to prepare a place for you.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 14:2
        content: "  Or \u201CThere are many resting places on the way to my Father\u2019s
          house.\u201D Or \u201CThere are many homes in my Father\u2019s household.\u201D
          The Father\u2019s house is also mentioned by Jesus in  , where it is his
          temple on earth, his dwelling place. This is not just heaven, but the dwelling
          place of God among men. There is ample room for people from every nation
          and ethnicity, room to spare, for the church, the body of Christ, is now
          the house of God. See  ;  ;  ;  ;  . Every believer is now one of the many
          dwelling places that make up God\u2019s house (temple). See also v.  .     
          Jesus\u2019 \u201Cgoing\u201D was to go through death and resurrection
          in order to make us ready to be his dwelling place. He had to \u201Cgo,\u201D
          not to heaven, but to the cross and pass through resurrection.    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '<JESUS>And when everything is ready, I will come back and take</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>you to myself so that you will be where I am.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: 14:3
        content: "  The Greek verb used here,  , is the word used for a bridegroom
          coming to take his bride. He \u201Ctakes\u201D us as his bride through
          his death and resurrection. His \u201Ccoming back\u201D can also refer
          to his \u201Ccoming\u201D to live within believers. The place he has prepared
          for us is in his Father\u2019s house (temple), which is the body of Christ.
          He chooses our place in the body where we will have the most impact for
          his glory. See  .    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "<JESUS>And you already know the way to the place where I\u2019m going.\u201D</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 14:4
        content: "  Or \u201CYou know where I\u2019m going and the way to get there.\u201D    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Thomas said to him, \u201CMaster, we don\u2019t know where you\u2019re
        going, so how could we know the way there?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Jesus explained, <JESUS>\u201CI am the Way, I am the Truth,</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>and I am the Life. No one comes next to the Father</JESUS>   
        <JESUS>except through</JESUS>  <JESUS>union with me.</JESUS>    <JESUS>To
        know me is to know my Father too.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 14:6
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe True Reality.\u201D      Jesus does more than take
          us to heaven, he brings us next to (alongside of) the Father. The Father
          is the destination.      Or \u201Cthrough [faith in] me.\u201D    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "<JESUS>And from now on you will realize that you have seen him and
        experienced him.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Philip spoke up, \u201CLord, show us the Father, and that will be
        all that we need!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CPhilip, I\u2019ve been with you all this
        time and you still don\u2019t know who I am? How could you ask me to show
        you the Father, for anyone who has looked at me has seen the Father.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "<JESUS>Don\u2019t you believe that the Father is living in me and
        that I am living in the Father? Even my words are not my own but come from
        my Father, for he lives in me and performs his miracles of power through
        me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "<JESUS>Believe that I live as one with my Father and that my Father
        lives as one with me\u2014or at least, believe because of the mighty miracles
        I have done.</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CI tell you this timeless truth: The person who follows
        me in faith, believing in me, will do the same mighty miracles that I do\u2014even
        greater miracles than these because I go to be with my Father!</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '<JESUS>For I will do whatever you ask me to do when you ask me in
        my name. And that is how the Son will show what the Father is really like
        and bring glory to him.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Jesus Prophesies about the Holy Spirit'
      title: Jesus Prophesies about the Holy Spirit
      number: 14
      content: "<JESUS>Ask me anything in my name, and I will do it for you!\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CLoving me empowers you to obey my commands.</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 14:15
        content: '  Love for Christ is proven and demonstrated by our obedience to
          all that he says.    '
    - name: '16-17: '
      title: 
      number: 16-17
      content: "<JESUS>And I will ask the Father and he will give you another</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>Savior,</JESUS>    <JESUS>the Holy Spirit of Truth,
        who will be to you a friend just like me\u2014and he will never leave you.
        The world won\u2019t receive him because they can\u2019t see him or know
        him. But you know him intimately because he remains with you and will live
        inside you.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: "14:16\u201317"
        content: "  The Greek word    means \u201Canother of the same kind.\u201D
          As Jesus is the Savior from the guilt of sin, the Holy Spirit is the Savior
          who saves us from the power of sin by living through us in fullness.     
          The Greek word used here is  , a technical word that could be translated
          \u201Cdefense attorney.\u201D It means \u201Cone called to stand next to
          you as a helper.\u201D Various translations have rendered this \u201CCounselor,\u201D
          \u201CComforter,\u201D \u201CAdvocate,\u201D \u201CEncourager,\u201D \u201CIntercessor,\u201D
          or \u201CHelper.\u201D However none of these words alone are adequate and
          fall short in explaining the full meaning. This translation has chosen
          the word  , for it depicts the role of the Holy Spirit to protect, defend,
          and save us from our self and our enemies and keep us whole and healed.
          He is the One who guides and defends, comforts and consoles. Keep in mind
          that the Holy Spirit is the Spirit of Christ, our Savior. The Aramaic word
          is  , which is taken from two root words: (1)  , \u201Cto end, finish,
          or to save,\u201D and (2)  , which means \u201Cthe curse.\u201D What a
          beautiful word picture: the Holy Spirit comes to end the work of the curse
          (of sin) in our lives and to save us from its every effect!    means \u201Ca
          redeemer who ends the curse.\u201D (See  , Gr. 6561 and 6562;  , p. 237;
          and  , p. 250.)      Jesus is prophesying about the coming of the Holy
          Spirit at Pentecost, who will indwell every believer. See  .    "
    - name: '16-17: '
      title: 
      number: 16-17
      content: "<JESUS>And I will ask the Father and he will give you another</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>Savior,</JESUS>    <JESUS>the Holy Spirit of Truth,
        who will be to you a friend just like me\u2014and he will never leave you.
        The world won\u2019t receive him because they can\u2019t see him or know
        him. But you know him intimately because he remains with you and will live
        inside you.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: "14:16\u201317"
        content: "  The Greek word    means \u201Canother of the same kind.\u201D
          As Jesus is the Savior from the guilt of sin, the Holy Spirit is the Savior
          who saves us from the power of sin by living through us in fullness.     
          The Greek word used here is  , a technical word that could be translated
          \u201Cdefense attorney.\u201D It means \u201Cone called to stand next to
          you as a helper.\u201D Various translations have rendered this \u201CCounselor,\u201D
          \u201CComforter,\u201D \u201CAdvocate,\u201D \u201CEncourager,\u201D \u201CIntercessor,\u201D
          or \u201CHelper.\u201D However none of these words alone are adequate and
          fall short in explaining the full meaning. This translation has chosen
          the word  , for it depicts the role of the Holy Spirit to protect, defend,
          and save us from our self and our enemies and keep us whole and healed.
          He is the One who guides and defends, comforts and consoles. Keep in mind
          that the Holy Spirit is the Spirit of Christ, our Savior. The Aramaic word
          is  , which is taken from two root words: (1)  , \u201Cto end, finish,
          or to save,\u201D and (2)  , which means \u201Cthe curse.\u201D What a
          beautiful word picture: the Holy Spirit comes to end the work of the curse
          (of sin) in our lives and to save us from its every effect!    means \u201Ca
          redeemer who ends the curse.\u201D (See  , Gr. 6561 and 6562;  , p. 237;
          and  , p. 250.)      Jesus is prophesying about the coming of the Holy
          Spirit at Pentecost, who will indwell every believer. See  .    "
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CI promise that I will never leave you helpless or abandon
        you as orphans\u2014I will come back to you!</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 14:18
        content: '  There are three ways Jesus will come to them. He came after his
          resurrection and appeared numerous times to his disciples. He came in the
          person of the Holy Spirit at Pentecost to live within them (), and he will
          come in the  , known traditionally as the second coming.    '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '<JESUS>Soon I will leave this world and they will see me no longer,
        but you will see me, because I will live again, and you will come alive too.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '<JESUS>So when that day comes, you will know that I am living in
        the Father and that you are one with me, for I will be living in you.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "<JESUS>Those who truly love me are those who obey my commands. Whoever
        passionately loves me will be passionately loved by my Father. And I will
        passionately love him in return and will reveal</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>myself to him.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 14:21
        content: "  The verb translated \u201Creveal\u201D is used in John\u2019s
          Gospel only here and in the following verse. As in the Septuagint of  ,
          it is used of a special divine manifestation. \u201CI&nbsp;.&nbsp;.&nbsp;.
          will reveal myself to him\u201D is more than merely \u201Cshowing him who
          I am.\u201D It means \u201CI will personally come to him.\u201D    "
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then one of the disciples named Judas [[COMMENT(0)]] (not Judas Iscariot)
        said, \u201CLord, why is it you will only reveal your identity to us and
        not to everyone?\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 14:22
        content: '  Judas was a common name in the time of Jesus. It is actually
          the name Judah.    '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CLoving me empowers you to obey my word.</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>And my Father will love you so deeply that we will
        come to you and make you our dwelling place.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 14:23
        content: '  Love for Christ is proven and demonstrated by our obedience to
          all that he says.    '
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "<JESUS>But those who don\u2019t love me will not obey my words. The
        Father did not send me to speak my own revelation, but the words of my Father.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '<JESUS>I am telling you this while I am still with you.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "<JESUS>But when the Father sends the Spirit of Holiness, the One
        like me who sets you free,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>he will teach
        you all things in my name. And he will inspire you to remember every word
        that I\u2019ve told you.</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 14:26
        content: "  The Aramaic is translated \u201Cthe Redeemer from the curse.\u201D
          See the second footnote on  .    "
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CI leave the gift of peace with you\u2014my peace. Not
        the kind of fragile peace given by the world, but my perfect peace. Don\u2019t
        yield to fear or be troubled in your hearts\u2014instead, be courageous!</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 14:27
        content: "  These are the same words Moses gave before he died and the words
          God spoke to Joshua as he entered into his life\u2019s plan of taking the
          promised land for Israel. See  ;  ;  . God has not given us a spirit of
          cowardly fear. See also  .    "
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CRemember what I\u2019ve told you, that I must go away,
        but I promise to come back to you. So if you truly love me, you will be glad
        for me, since I\u2019m returning to my Father, who is greater than I.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: '<JESUS>So when all of these things happen, you will still trust and
        cling to me.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "<JESUS>I won\u2019t speak with you much longer, for the ruler of
        this dark world</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>is coming. But he has no
        power over me,</JESUS>  <JESUS>for he has nothing to use against me.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 14:30
        content: "  Implied in the text and in the word  , which means \u201Cslanderer\u201D
          and \u201Caccuser.\u201D    "
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "<JESUS>I am doing exactly what the Father destined for me to accomplish,</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>so that the world will discover how much I love my
        Father. Now come with me.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 14:31
        content: "  Or \u201Ccommanded me to do.\u201D  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus the Living Vine'
      title: Jesus the Living Vine
      number: 1
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CI am a true sprouting vine, and the farmer who tends
        the vine is my Father.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '<JESUS>He cares for the branches connected to me by lifting and propping
        up the fruitless branches</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>and pruning</JESUS>   
        <JESUS>every fruitful branch to yield a greater harvest.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: 15:2
        content: "  The Greek phrase can also be translated \u201Che takes up [to
          himself] every fruitless branch.\u201D He doesn\u2019t remove these branches,
          but he takes them to himself. As the wise and loving farmer, he lifts them
          up off the ground to enhance their growth. In the context, Christ\u2019s
          endless love for his disciples on the last night of his life on earth seems
          to emphasize God\u2019s love even for those who fail and disappoint him.
          Peter\u2019s denial didn\u2019t bring rejection from Jesus.      The Greek
          word for \u201Cpruning,\u201D  , can also mean \u201Ccleansing.\u201D    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '<JESUS>The words I have spoken over you have already cleansed</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>you.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: 15:3
        content: "  Or \u201Cpruned.\u201D    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: <JESUS>So you must remain in life-union with me,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>for I remain in life-union with you. For as a branch severed from
        the vine will not bear fruit, so your life will be fruitless unless you live
        your life intimately joined to mine.</JESUS>
      comments:
      - number: 15:4
        content: "  Or \u201Cgrafted into me.\u201D    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CI am the sprouting vine and you\u2019re my branches.</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>As you live in union with me as your source, fruitfulness
        will stream from within you\u2014but when you live separated from me you
        are powerless.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 15:5
        content: '  See  ;  ;  . The branch of the Lord is now Christ living in his
          people, branching out through them. The church is now his lampstand with
          seven branches.    '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '<JESUS>If a person is separated from me, he is discarded; such branches
        are gathered up and thrown into the fire to be burned.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "<JESUS>But if you live in life-union with me and if my words</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>live powerfully</JESUS>    <JESUS>within you\u2014then
        you can ask</JESUS>    <JESUS>whatever you desire and it will be done.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 15:7
        content: "  This is the Greek word  , which refers to the spoken words, or
          the sayings, of God.      The Aramaic is translated \u201Cmy words take
          hold (are strong) within you.\u201D      Or \u201Cdemand\u201D or \u201Cinsist.\u201D    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: <JESUS>When your lives bear abundant fruit, you demonstrate that you
        are my mature disciples who glorify my Father!</JESUS>
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CI love each of you with the same love that the Father
        loves me. You must continually let my love nourish your hearts.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "<JESUS>If you keep my commands, you will live in my love, just as
        I have kept my Father\u2019s commands, for I continually live nourished and
        empowered by his love.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: <JESUS>My purpose for telling you these things is so that the joy
        that I experience will fill your hearts with overflowing gladness!</JESUS>
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CSo this is my command: Love each other deeply, as much
        as I have loved you.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 15:12
        content: "  Because we are all branches in one vine, if we don\u2019t love
          one another it means that our fellowship with the vine has been cut off.
          To bear fruit must come from loving each other, for the same Christ-life
          lives within every believer. We are not branches of many trees, but of
          one vine.    "
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: <JESUS>For the greatest love of all is a love that sacrifices all.
        And this great love is demonstrated when a person sacrifices his life</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>for his friends.</JESUS>
      comments:
      - number: 15:13
        content: "  Or \u201Cwillingly lay down his soul for his friends.\u201D The
          Aramaic word for \u201Cfriends\u201D is actually \u201Cfamily\u201D or
          \u201Crelatives.\u201D    "
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CYou show that you are my intimate friends when you obey</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>all</JESUS>    <JESUS>that I command you.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 15:14
        content: "  The Greek verb indicates \u201Cif you keep on obeying as a habit.\u201D     
          The Aramaic is translated \u201Call\u201D; the Greek is translated \u201Cwhat
          I command you.\u201D    "
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "<JESUS>I have never called you \u2018servants,\u2019</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>because a master doesn\u2019t confide in his servants, and servants
        don\u2019t always understand what the master is doing. But I call you my
        most intimate and cherished friends,</JESUS>    <JESUS>for I reveal to you
        everything that I\u2019ve heard from my Father.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 15:15
        content: "  As translated from the Aramaic. The Greek is \u201CI will no
          longer call you servants.\u201D The Greek word for \u201Cservants\u201D
          is  , which means \u201Cslaves.\u201D      Both the Aramaic and Greek word
          for \u201Cintimate friends\u201D is actually \u201Cthose cared for from
          the womb.\u201D You are more than a friend to him, for you were born again
          from his wounded side.    "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "<JESUS>You didn\u2019t choose me, but I\u2019ve chosen</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>and commissioned you to go into the world</JESUS>    <JESUS>to bear
        fruit. And your fruit will last, because whatever you ask of my Father, for
        my sake,</JESUS>    <JESUS>he will give it to you!</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 15:16
        content: "  The Aramaic is \u201CI have invited you\u201D (as dinner guests).     
          This could mean \u201Cto go on into maturity\u201D (character), or \u201Cto
          go into the world\u201D (ministry). However, the \u201Cchoosing\u201D and
          \u201Ccommissioning\u201D infers the latter.      Or \u201Cin my name.\u201D    "
    - name: '17: True Disciples Can Expect Persecution'
      title: True Disciples Can Expect Persecution
      number: 17
      content: "<JESUS>So this is my parting command: Love one another deeply!\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CJust remember, when the unbelieving world hates you,
        they first hated me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "<JESUS>If you were to give your allegiance to the world, they would
        love and welcome you as one of their own. But because you won\u2019t align
        yourself with the values of this world, they will hate you. I have chosen
        you and taken you out of the world to be mine.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "<JESUS>So remember what I taught you, that a servant isn\u2019t superior
        to his master.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>And since they persecuted
        me, they will also persecute you. And if they obey my teachings, they will
        also obey yours.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 15:20
        content: "  Or \u201Credeemer.\u201D See  .    "
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "<JESUS>They will treat you this way because you are mine,</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>and they don\u2019t know the One who sent me.</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 15:21
        content: "  Or \u201Cbecause of my name.\u201D    "
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CIf I had not come and spoken these things to the unbelieving
        world, they would not feel the guilt of their sin, but now their sin is left
        uncovered.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 15:22
        content: '  As translated from the Aramaic.    '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '<JESUS>If anyone hates me, they hate my Father also.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '<JESUS>If I had not performed miracles in their presence like no
        one else has done, they would not feel the guilt of their sins. But now,
        they have seen and hated both me and my Father.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '<JESUS>And all of this has happened to fulfill what is written in
        their Scriptures:</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>They hated me for no reason.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: 15:25
        content: "  Or \u201Cwritten in their law.\u201D      See  ;  .    "
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CAnd I will send you the Divine Encourager</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>from the very presence of my Father. He will come to you, the Spirit
        of Truth, emanating from the Father, and he will speak</JESUS>    <JESUS>to
        you about me.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 15:26
        content: "  Or \u201CRedeemer from the curse.\u201D See the second footnote
          on  .      Or \u201Cprovide evidence.\u201D  "
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "<JESUS>And you will tell everyone the truth about me, for you have
        walked with me from the start.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Warns His Disciples'
      title: Jesus Warns His Disciples
      number: 1
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CI have told you this so that you would not surrender
        to confusion or doubt.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 16:1
        content: "  Or \u201Cso that you won\u2019t have a trap laid for you.\u201D
          The Aramaic is translated \u201Cso that you will not be crushed.\u201D    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '<JESUS>For you will be excommunicated from the synagogues, and a
        time is coming when you will be put to death by misguided ones who will presume
        to be doing God a great service by putting you to death.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 16:2
        content: "  The Aramaic is \u201Cthose who kill you will think they are presenting
          a holy offering to God.\u201D    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "<JESUS>And they will do these things because they don\u2019t know
        anything about the Father or me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "<JESUS>I\u2019m telling you this now so that when their time comes
        you will remember that I foretold it. I didn\u2019t tell you this in the
        beginning because I was still with you.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "<JESUS>But now that I\u2019m about to leave you and go back to join
        the One who sent me, you need to be told. Yet, not one of you are asking
        me where I\u2019m going.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "<JESUS>Instead your hearts are filled with sadness because I\u2019ve
        told you these things.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "<JESUS>But here\u2019s the truth: It\u2019s to your advantage that
        I go away, for if I don\u2019t go away the Divine Encourager</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>will not be released to you. But after I depart, I will send him to
        you.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 16:7
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe Redeemer of the curse.\u201D See the second footnote
          on  .    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "<JESUS>And when he comes, he will expose sin and prove that the world
        is wrong about God\u2019s righteousness and his judgments.</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "<JESUS>\u201C&nbsp;\u2018Sin,\u2019 because they refuse to believe
        in who I am.</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CGod\u2019s \u2018righteousness,\u2019 because I\u2019m
        going back to join the Father and you\u2019ll see me no longer.</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CAnd \u2018judgment\u2019 because the ruler of this dark
        world has already received his sentence.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 16:11
        content: "  In essence, \u201Csin&nbsp;.&nbsp;.&nbsp;. righteousness&nbsp;.&nbsp;.&nbsp;.
          and judgment are related to three persons.\u201D Sin is related to Adam,
          for it was through Adam that sin entered humanity (). Righteousness is
          related to Christ, because it comes through him, and he has become our
          righteousness (). Judgment is related to Satan, for the pure works of Christ
          bring judgment to the works of Satan. If we do not embrace Christ\u2019s
          righteousness, we will share Satan\u2019s judgment.    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CThere is so much more I would like to say to you, but
        it\u2019s more than you can grasp at this moment.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "<JESUS>But when the truth-giving Spirit comes, he will unveil the
        reality of every truth</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>within you. He won\u2019t
        speak on his own, but only what he hears from the Father, and he will reveal</JESUS> 
        <JESUS>prophetically</JESUS>  <JESUS>to you what is to come.</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 16:13
        content: "  The Greek word for \u201Ctruth\u201D is \u201Creality,\u201D
          not \u201Cdoctrine.\u201D It is the application of truth that matters,
          not just a superficial knowledge.    "
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '<JESUS>He will glorify me on the earth, for he will receive from
        me what is mine</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>and reveal it to you.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: 16:14
        content: "  As translated from the Aramaic. Or \u201Che plants what is mine
          and shows it to you.\u201D    "
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "<JESUS>Everything that belongs to the Father belongs to me\u2014that\u2019s
        why I say that the Divine Encourager will receive what is mine and reveal
        it to you.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "<JESUS>Soon you won\u2019t see me any longer, but then, after a little
        while, you will see me</JESUS>  <JESUS>in a new way</JESUS><JESUS>.\u201D</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 16:16
        content: "  Jesus used two different Greek words for \u201Csee\u201D in this
          verse. The Aramaic adds \u201Cbecause I go to my Father.\u201D    "
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Some of the disciples asked each other, \u201CWhat does he mean,
        \u2018Soon you won\u2019t see me,\u2019 and, \u2018A little while after that
        and you will see me in a new way\u2019? And what does he mean, \u2018Because
        I\u2019m going to my Father\u2019?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So they kept on repeating, \u201CWhat\u2019s the meaning of \u2018a
        little while\u2019? We have no clue what he\u2019s talking about!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Jesus knew what they were thinking, and it was obvious that they
        were anxious to ask him what he had meant, [[COMMENT(0)]] so he spoke up
        and said, '
      comments:
      - number: 16:19
        content: "  Or \u201CAre you asking each other what I meant when I told you,
          \u2018A little while and you will see me no more, and then after a little
          while you will see me\u2019?\u201D    "
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CLet me make it quite clear: You will weep and be overcome
        with grief</JESUS>  <JESUS>over what happens to me</JESUS><JESUS>. The unbelieving
        world will be happy, while you will be filled with sorrow. But know this,
        your sadness will turn into joy</JESUS>  <JESUS>when you see me again!</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: <JESUS>Just like a woman giving birth experiences intense labor pains
        in delivering her baby,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>yet after the child
        is born she quickly forgets what she went through because of the overwhelming
        joy of knowing that a new baby has been born into the world.</JESUS>
      comments:
      - number: 16:21
        content: "  Or \u201Cbecause her time [for delivery] has come.\u201D It is
          fascinating that Jesus spoke of the disciples in the terms of giving birth.
          Christ is being formed within us (). The church continues in \u201Clabor\u201D
          today so that Jesus can be seen again through us. See  .    "
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CSo will you also pass through a time of intense sorrow</JESUS> 
        <JESUS>when I am taken from you</JESUS><JESUS>, but you will see me again!
        And then your hearts will burst with joy, with no one being able to take
        it from you!</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 16:22
        content: '  Jesus was referring to the prophecy of  ,  .    '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "<JESUS>For here is eternal truth: When that time comes you won\u2019t
        need to ask me for anything, but instead you will go directly to the Father
        and ask him for anything you desire and he will give it to you, because of
        your relationship with me.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 16:23
        content: "  Or \u201Che will give it to you in my name.\u201D    "
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "<JESUS>Until now you\u2019ve not been bold enough to ask the Father
        for a single thing in my name,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>but now you
        can ask, and keep on asking him! And you can be sure that you\u2019ll receive
        what you ask for, and your joy will have no limits!</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 16:24
        content: "  To ask in Jesus\u2019 name is to ask in the name of \u201CI AM.\u201D
          We take all the fullness of Jesus (his name, his glory, his virtue) as
          the \u201CI AM\u201D of  \u2014because of our relationship with him.    "
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CI have spoken to you using figurative language,</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>but the time is coming when I will no longer teach
        you with veiled speech, but I will teach you about the Father with your eyes
        unveiled.</JESUS>    "
      comments:
      - number: 16:25
        content: "  This is the Greek word  , which can mean obscure \u201Cfigurative
          speech,\u201D \u201Canalogies,\u201D \u201Cparables,\u201D \u201Cproverbs,\u201D
          \u201Cmetaphors,\u201D or \u201Callegory.\u201D These were all utilized
          as Jesus\u2019 preferred teaching method while on earth. See v.    and 
          .      As translated from the Aramaic.    "
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "<JESUS>And I will not need to ask the Father on your behalf, for
        you\u2019ll ask him directly because of your new relationship with me.</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 16:26
        content: "  Or \u201Cin my name.\u201D    "
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "<JESUS>For the Father tenderly loves you, because you love me and
        believe that I\u2019ve come from God.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "<JESUS>I came to you sent from the Father\u2019s presence, and I
        entered into the created world, and now I will leave this world and return
        to the Father\u2019s side.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "His disciples said, \u201CAt last you\u2019re speaking to us clearly
        and not using veiled speech and metaphors! "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Now we understand that you know everything there is to know, and
        we don\u2019t need to question you further. And everything you\u2019ve taught
        us convinces us that you have come directly from God!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CNow you finally believe in me.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: '<JESUS>And the time has come when you will all be scattered, and
        each one of you will go your own way, leaving me alone!</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>Yet I am never alone, for the Father is always with me.</JESUS>  '
      comments:
      - number: 16:32
        content: '  This will fulfill the prophecy of  .    '
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "<JESUS>And everything I\u2019ve taught you is so that the peace which
        is in me will be in you and will give you great confidence as you rest in
        me. For in this unbelieving world you will experience trouble and sorrows,
        but you must be courageous,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>for I have conquered
        the world!\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 16:33
        content: "  Or \u201Ccheer up!\u201D      Jesus has taken away the power
          this world has to defeat us and has conquered it for us. Peace is resting
          in his victory.  "
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jesus Finished the Father\u2019s Work"
      title: "Jesus Finished the Father\u2019s Work"
      number: 1
      content: "This is what Jesus prayed as he looked up into heaven,<JESUS>\u201CFather,
        the time has come.</JESUS><JESUS>Unveil the glorious splendor of your Son</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]<JESUS>so that I will magnify your glory!</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 17:1
        content: "  Or \u201CGlorify your Son!\u201D The Father unveiled the glory
          of his Son on the cross, by the empty tomb, through his ascension into
          heaven, and by the mighty outpouring of the Holy Spirit upon his church.    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: <JESUS>You have already given me authority</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]<JESUS>over
        all people so that I may give</JESUS><JESUS>the gift of eternal life to all
        those that you have given to me.</JESUS>
      comments:
      - number: 17:2
        content: "  The Aramaic is translated \u201Cresponsibility.\u201D    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: <JESUS>Eternal life means to know and experience you</JESUS><JESUS>as
        the only true God,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]<JESUS>and to know and experience
        Jesus Christ,</JESUS><JESUS>as the Son whom you have sent.</JESUS>
      comments:
      - number: 17:3
        content: "  The Aramaic is translated \u201Cthe God of truth.\u201D This
          alludes to  .    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "<JESUS>I have glorified you on the earth</JESUS><JESUS>by faithfully
        doing everything you\u2019ve told me to do.</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Jesus Prays for His Disciples'
      title: Jesus Prays for His Disciples
      number: 5
      content: "<JESUS>So my Father, restore me back to the glory</JESUS><JESUS>that
        we shared together when we were face-to-face</JESUS><JESUS>before the universe
        was created.\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 17:5
        content: "  The Aramaic is translated \u201Cbefore the light of the universe.\u201D    "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CFather, I have manifested who you really are</JESUS><JESUS>and
        I have revealed you</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>to the men and women</JESUS><JESUS>that
        you gave to me.</JESUS>  <JESUS>They were yours, and you gave them to me,</JESUS><JESUS>and
        they have fastened your Word firmly to their hearts.</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 17:6
        content: "  Or \u201CI have made known your name.\u201D The Greek word, 
          , means \u201Cto make visible,\u201D \u201Cto manifest,\u201D \u201Cto
          reveal,\u201D and \u201Cto be plainly recognized.\u201D (See  , Gr. 5319.)     
          Or \u201Cyou gave to me out of the world.\u201D    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: <JESUS>And now at last they know that everything I have is a gift
        from you,</JESUS>
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: <JESUS>And the very words you gave to me to speak</JESUS><JESUS>I
        have passed on to them.</JESUS><JESUS>They have received your words</JESUS><JESUS>and</JESUS> 
        <JESUS>carry them in their hearts.</JESUS><JESUS>They are convinced that
        I have come from your presence,</JESUS><JESUS>and they have fully believed
        that you sent me to represent you.</JESUS>
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "<JESUS>So with deep love,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>I pray
        for my disciples.</JESUS><JESUS>I\u2019m not asking on behalf of the unbelieving
        world,</JESUS>  <JESUS>but for those who belong to you,</JESUS><JESUS>those
        you have given me.</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 17:9
        content: "  The Aramaic can be translated \u201CI desired [loved] them.\u201D
          The Greek is \u201CI pray for them.\u201D This translation has chosen to
          include both concepts.      This is emphatic in the Greek sentence structure.
          How could it be that Jesus loved the world and gave himself for the sin
          of the world, yet emphasized that he was praying for his disciples and
          not praying for the world? Jesus\u2019 coming into the world brought life
          to those who believe and judgment to those who do not. The implication
          is that the key to reaching the world is the life, maturity, unity, and
          love of the disciples. This does not mean that Jesus didn\u2019t love the
          world, but that the world will only be reached when the disciples come
          into the fullness of Christ and in unity of the faith. This is what consumed
          the heart of Jesus as he prayed for them before the cross.    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: <JESUS>For all who belong to me now belong to you.</JESUS><JESUS>And
        all who belong to you now belong to me as well,</JESUS><JESUS>and my glory
        is revealed through</JESUS>  <JESUS>their surrendered lives.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 17:10
        content: "  Or \u201CI am glorified in them.\u201D    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CHoly Father, I am about to leave this world</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]<JESUS>to return and be with you,</JESUS><JESUS>but my disciples
        will remain here.</JESUS>Holy Father, each one that you have given me,keep
        them in your name <JESUS>so that they will be united</JESUS><JESUS>as one,
        even as we are one.</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 17:11
        content: "  Or \u201CI am no longer in the world.\u201D    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: <JESUS>While I was with these that you have given me,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]<JESUS>I
        was guarding them and keeping them in your name.</JESUS><JESUS>Not one of
        them is lost,</JESUS><JESUS>except the one that was destined to be lost,</JESUS> 
        <JESUS>so that the Scripture would be fulfilled.</JESUS>
      comments:
      - number: 17:12
        content: "  See footnote on v.  .      Or \u201Cson of perdition,\u201D which
          is a Semitic idiom that means \u201Cto be destined to destruction.\u201D
          This obviously refers to Judas, the betrayer. See also  ;  .    "
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CBut now I am returning to you so Father,</JESUS><JESUS>I
        pray</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>that they will experience</JESUS><JESUS>and
        enter into my joyous delight in you</JESUS>  <JESUS>so that it is fulfilled
        in them and overflows.</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 17:13
        content: "  Or \u201CI speak these things [this prayer] in the world [before
          I leave].\u201D      This \u201Cdelight\u201D is more than happiness. It
          is the complete satisfaction that comes in knowing that our lives are pleasing
          to the Father and that we fulfill his desires on the earth. This is the
          delight that Jesus shares with us and prays that we would experience.    "
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: <JESUS>I have given them your message</JESUS><JESUS>and that is why
        the unbelieving world hates them.</JESUS><JESUS>For their allegiance is no
        longer to this world</JESUS><JESUS>because I am not of this world.</JESUS>
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: <JESUS>I am not asking that you remove them from the world,</JESUS><JESUS>but
        I ask that you guard their hearts from evil,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 17:15
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe Evil One\u201D (or \u201CSatan\u201D). The implication
          is that the disciples of Jesus will influence the systems of this world
          but need to be preserved from evil influences.    "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: <JESUS>For they no longer belong to this world any more than I do.</JESUS>
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CYour Word is truth! So make them holy by the truth.</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: <JESUS>I have commissioned them to represent me</JESUS><JESUS>just
        as you commissioned me to represent you.</JESUS>
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Jesus Prays for You'
      title: Jesus Prays for You
      number: 19
      content: "<JESUS>And now I dedicate myself to them as a holy sacrifice</JESUS><JESUS>so
        that they will live as fully dedicated to God</JESUS><JESUS>and be made holy
        by your truth.\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 17:19
        content: "  The Aramaic can be translated \u201CAnd in their sight I will
          glorify [consecrate] myself, so that they will be glorified [consecrated]
          by the truth.\u201D    "
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CAnd I ask not only for these disciples,</JESUS><JESUS>but
        also for all those who will one day</JESUS><JESUS>believe in me through their
        message.</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: <JESUS>I pray for them all to be joined together as one</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]<JESUS>even
        as you and I, Father, are joined together as one.</JESUS><JESUS>I pray for
        them to become one with us</JESUS>  <JESUS>so that the world will recognize
        that you sent me.</JESUS>
      comments:
      - number: 17:21
        content: "  Jesus prayed for the birth of the church, made up of Jewish and
          non-Jewish believers.      Or \u201Cin us.\u201D    "
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: <JESUS>For the very glory you have given to me I have given them</JESUS><JESUS>so
        that they will be joined together as one</JESUS><JESUS>and experience the
        same unity that we enjoy.</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 17:22
        content: "  It is important to note that the key to unity among believers
          is experiencing the glory of God that Jesus has imparted to us. As one
          with God through faith in Christ, he shares his glory with us, since we
          are not \u201Canother,\u201D but have been made one with the triune God
          through the blood of Jesus. See  .    "
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: <JESUS>You live fully in me and now I live fully in them</JESUS><JESUS>so
        that they will experience perfect unity,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]<JESUS>and
        the world will be convinced that you have sent me,</JESUS><JESUS>for they
        will see that you love each one of them</JESUS><JESUS>with the same passionate
        love that you have for me.</JESUS>
      comments:
      - number: 17:23
        content: "  The Aramaic is \u201Cshrink into one.\u201D When we see Jesus
          in one another, our vaulted opinions of ourselves will shrink.    "
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CFather, I ask that you allow everyone that you have
        given to me</JESUS><JESUS>to be with me where I am!</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]<JESUS>Then
        they will see my full glory\u2014</JESUS><JESUS>the very splendor you have
        placed upon me</JESUS><JESUS>because you have loved me even before the beginning
        of time.</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 17:24
        content: '  This is experienced not only after we die, but also took place
          when the ascended Christ took us up into the heavenly realm and seated
          us at his side with the Father. See  ;  .    '
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CYou are my righteous Father,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]<JESUS>but
        the unbelieving world has never known you</JESUS><JESUS>in the perfect way
        that I know you!</JESUS><JESUS>And all those who believe in me</JESUS>  <JESUS>also
        know that you have sent me!</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 17:25
        content: "  As translated from the Aramaic.      The Greek is simply \u201Cthese\u201D
          (disciples).    "
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "<JESUS>I have revealed to them who you are</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]<JESUS>and
        I will continue to make you even more real to them,</JESUS><JESUS>so that
        they may experience the same endless love</JESUS><JESUS>that you have for
        me,</JESUS><JESUS>for your love will now live in them, even as I live in
        them!\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 17:26
        content: "  Or \u201CI have revealed your name to them.\u201D  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus in the Garden of Gethsemane'
      title: Jesus in the Garden of Gethsemane
      number: 1
      content: 'After Jesus finished this prayer; he left with his disciples and
        went across the Kidron Valley [[COMMENT(0)]] to a place where there was a
        garden.   '
      comments:
      - number: 18:1
        content: "  The Kidron ravine is the path David took when he was forced to
          flee Jerusalem because of the betrayal of his son Absalom. David went up
          the Mount of Olives weeping. Jesus went up also in sorrow. David went up
          to save himself; Jesus went up to save the people of the world.      This
          is the garden of Gethsemane, which means \u201Colive press.\u201D Jesus
          not only went to the garden to pray, but to be captured. He knew full well
          the Father\u2019s plan. Just as Adam fell in a garden of paradise, Jesus
          stood faithful in a garden of betrayal.    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Judas, the traitor, knew where this place was, for Jesus had gone
        there often with his disciples. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The Pharisees and the leading priests had given Judas a large detachment
        [[COMMENT(0)]] of Roman soldiers and temple police to seize Jesus. Judas
        guided them to the garden, all of them carrying torches and lanterns and
        armed with swords and spears.   '
      comments:
      - number: 18:3
        content: "  The Greek and Aramaic word used for this company of soldiers
          implies quite a large number, up to five or six hundred men sent to arrest
          Jesus. Even his enemies knew his power was great.      The Greek word is
          \u201Cfoot-soldiers\u2019 weapons.\u201D    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Jesus, knowing full well what was about to happen, went out to the
        garden entrance to meet them. Stepping forward, he asked, <JESUS>\u201CWho
        are you looking for?\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CJesus of Nazareth,\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]] they replied. (Now
        Judas, the traitor, was among them.)He replied, <JESUS>\u201CI am he.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 18:5
        content: "  Or \u201CJesus, the Nazarene.\u201D This is the Aramaic word 
          , which means \u201Cvictorious one\u201D or \u201Cheir of a powerful family.\u201D
          The Hebrew word for \u201CNazareth\u201D comes from the root word  , which
          means \u201Cbranch.\u201D See  ;  .    "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the moment Jesus spoke the words, <JESUS>\u201CI am he,\u201D</JESUS>
        the mob fell backward to the ground! [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 18:6
        content: '  This was a stunning event as the great I Am spoke his name before
          those who sought to seize him. It is obvious in the text that they did
          not trip over each other in surprise, for every one of these strong men
          fell backward to the ground by the power of God. Jesus was in charge that
          night as the captain of the host of the Lord. They could not seize him
          unless he permitted them to do so. What a wonderful Savior who willingly
          submitted to the hands of cruel men to bring us the gift of salvation.    '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So once more, Jesus asked them, <JESUS>\u201CWho are you looking
        for?\u201D</JESUS>As they stood up, they answered, \u201CJesus of Nazareth.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CI told you that I am the one you\u2019re
        looking for, so if you want me, let these men go home.\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 18:8
        content: "  \u201CThese men\u201D were the eleven disciples who were with
          Jesus in the garden.    "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He said this to fulfill the prophecy he had spoken, <JESUS>\u201CFather,
        not one of those you have given me has been lost.\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 18:9
        content: '  See  ;  .    '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Suddenly, Peter took out his sword and struck the high priest\u2019s
        servant, slashing off his right ear! [[COMMENT(0)]] The servant\u2019s name
        was Malchus. "
      comments:
      - number: 18:10
        content: "  This event is a vivid picture of what happens when we act impetuously
          and in anger. We hinder people\u2019s ability to hear our message (we cut
          off their ear) when we walk in angry offense toward others.      Malchus\u2019
          name means \u201Cking.\u201D Perhaps at the moment of healing his ear,
          Jesus personally revealed himself to Malchus in a supernatural way, the
          King who healed a king. Jesus is the true servant to the High Priest. We
          can imagine Jesus reaching out his hand to help Malchus up. And in an instant,
          Malchus believes. Malchus\u2019 ears, both of them, are healed.    "
    - name: '11: Jesus Is Taken before Annas'
      title: Jesus Is Taken before Annas
      number: 11
      content: "Jesus ordered Peter, <JESUS>\u201CPut your sword away! Do you really
        think I will avoid the suffering</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>which my
        Father has assigned to me?\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 18:11
        content: "  Or \u201CShall I not drink the cup (of suffering) assigned me
          by the Father?\u201D    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then the soldiers and their captain, along with the Jewish officers,
        seized Jesus and tied him up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'They took him first to Annas, [[COMMENT(0)]] as he was the father-in-law
        of Caiaphas, the high priest that year.   '
      comments:
      - number: 18:13
        content: "  John is the only Gospel account that inserts this pre-trial meeting
          with Annas. He was the retired and illegal high priest.      Or \u201Cclose
          friend to the high priest.\u201D The priesthood was corrupt in the time
          of Jesus. It was not proper for two men to hold the office of high priest
          at the same time, as it apparently was done in Jesus\u2019 day. They both
          were called high priest in this narrative. See  ,  .    "
    - name: "14: Peter\u2019s First Denial"
      title: "Peter\u2019s First Denial"
      number: 14
      content: Caiaphas was the one who had persuaded the Jewish leaders that it
        would be better off to have one person die for the sake of the people. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 18:14
        content: '  See  .    '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Peter and another disciple followed along behind them as they took
        Jesus into the courtyard of Annas\u2019 palace. Since the other disciple
        was well known to the high priest, he entered in, [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 18:15
        content: '  Although it is impossible to determine who exactly was this other
          disciple, some have surmised it was John himself, or Nicodemus. If it was
          Nicodemus, as a leader among the Pharisees, this would explain his inclusion
          into the proceedings taking place that night.    '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'but Peter was left standing outside by the gate. Then the other disciple
        came back out to the servant girl who was guarding the gate and convinced
        her to allow Peter inside. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "As he passed inside, the young servant girl guarding the gate took
        a look at Peter and said to him, \u201CAren\u2019t you one of his disciples?\u201DHe
        denied it, saying, \u201CNo! I\u2019m not!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Jesus Interrogated by Annas'
      title: Jesus Interrogated by Annas
      number: 18
      content: Now because it was cold, the soldiers and guards made a charcoal fire
        and were standing around it to keep warm. So Peter huddled there with them
        around the fire.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: The high priest interrogated Jesus concerning his disciples [[COMMENT(0)]]
        and his teachings.
      comments:
      - number: 18:19
        content: "  It is interesting that Annas was concerned about Jesus\u2019
          disciples. The religious spirit is always concerned with impressive numbers
          and influence. Jesus only had twelve disciples who were always with him.    "
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Jesus answered Annas\u2019 questions by saying, <JESUS>\u201CI have
        said nothing in secret. At all times I have taught openly and publicly in
        a synagogue, in the temple courts, and wherever the people assemble.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "<JESUS>Why would you ask me for evidence to condemn me? Ask those
        who have heard what I\u2019ve taught. They can tell you.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Just then one of the guards standing near Jesus punched him in the
        face with his fist [[COMMENT(0)]] and said, \u201CHow dare you answer the
        high priest like that!\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 18:22
        content: "  The Greek is simply \u201Cstruck him.\u201D This could have been
          with a rod, for the verb has an etymological connection to the word for
          \u201Crod.\u201D Most translators have chosen to use \u201Cstruck [or \u2018slapped\u2019]
          with his hand.\u201D Regardless, Jesus was beaten everywhere he went that
          night and the next morning until he was finally crucified.    "
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CIf my words are evil, then prove it.
        But if I haven\u2019t broken any laws, then why would you hit me?\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: "24: Peter\u2019s Second and Third Denials"
      title: "Peter\u2019s Second and Third Denials"
      number: 24
      content: Then Annas sent Jesus, still tied up, across the way to the high priest
        Caiaphas.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Meanwhile, Peter was still standing in the courtyard by the fire.
        And one of the guards standing there said to him, \u201CAren\u2019t you one
        of his disciples? I know you are!\u201D Peter swore [[COMMENT(0)]] and said,
        \u201CI am not his disciple!\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: 18:25
        content: "  As translated from the Aramaic. This is a very strong word that
          can also be translated \u201Cblasphemed.\u201D God\u2019s loving grace
          forgave Peter\u2019s sin\u2014and our sin.    "
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "But one of the servants of the high priest, a relative to the man
        whose ear Peter had cut off, looked at him and said, \u201CWait! Didn\u2019t
        I see you out there in the garden with Jesus?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "27: Pilate Questions Jesus\u2019 Arrest"
      title: "Pilate Questions Jesus\u2019 Arrest"
      number: 27
      content: "Then Peter denied it the third time and said, \u201CNo!\u201D\u2014and
        at that very same moment, a rooster crowed nearby."
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Before dawn they took Jesus from his trial before Caiaphas to the
        Roman governor\u2019s palace. [[COMMENT(0)]] Now the Jews refused to go into
        the Roman governor\u2019s residence to avoid ceremonial defilement before
        eating the Passover meal. "
      comments:
      - number: 18:28
        content: "  The Greek is  , which is the transliteration of the Latin word
          meaning \u201Cgeneral\u2019s tent.\u201D It became used for the Roman governor\u2019s
          official residence.    "
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "So Pilate came outside where they waited and asked them pointedly,
        \u201CTell me, what exactly is the accusation [[COMMENT(0)]] that you bring
        against this man? What has he done?\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 18:29
        content: "  The Aramaic word for \u201Caccusation\u201D is similar to the
          word    (\u201Caccuser\u201D). Pilate is saying, \u201CWhat the devil do
          you have against this man?\u201D    "
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "They answered, \u201CWe wouldn\u2019t be coming here to hand over
        [[COMMENT(0)]] this \u2018criminal\u2019 to you if he wasn\u2019t guilty
        of some wrongdoing!\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 18:30
        content: "  The Aramaic word for \u201Chand over\u201D can also be translated
          \u201Cbetray.\u201D    "
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Pilate said, \u201CVery well, then you take him yourselves and go
        pass judgment on him according to your Jewish laws!\u201DBut the Jewish leaders
        complained and said, \u201CWe don\u2019t have legal authority to put anyone
        to death. You should have him crucified!\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 18:31
        content: '  Implied in the context and made explicit to clarify the illegality
          of the Jews to crucify Jesus. The Jewish law permitted death by stoning,
          not by crucifixion. The Scriptures had prophesied that he would be pierced
          and crucified. This was the cruel manner of death used by the Romans to
          execute the worst of criminals. For this reason they wanted Pilate to order
          his crucifixion. See  .    '
    - name: '32: Pilate Interrogates Jesus'
      title: Pilate Interrogates Jesus
      number: 32
      content: (This was to fulfill the words of Jesus when he predicted the manner
        of death that he would die.)
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Upon hearing this, Pilate went back inside his palace and summoned
        Jesus. Looking him over, Pilate asked him, \u201CAre you really the king
        of the Jews?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CAre you asking because you really want
        to know,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>or are you only asking this because
        others have said it about me?\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 18:34
        content: "  The Aramaic is \u201CHave you spoken this from your soul?\u201D    "
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Pilate responded, \u201COnly a Jew would care about this; do I look
        like a Jew? It\u2019s your own people and your religious leaders that have
        handed you over to me. So tell me, Jesus, what have you done wrong?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Jesus looked at Pilate and said, <JESUS>\u201CThe royal power of
        my kingdom realm doesn\u2019t come from this world. If it did, then my followers
        would be fighting to the end to defend me from the Jewish leaders. My kingdom
        realm authority is not</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>from this realm.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 18:36
        content: "  The Aramaic is \u201Cnot yet from here.\u201D      The Greek
          text is not \u201Cworld,\u201D but literally \u201Cthis side\u201D or \u201Cthis
          realm.\u201D The Aramaic word used here can be translated \u201Cnot of
          this age.\u201D    "
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Then Pilate responded, \u201COh, so then you are a king?\u201D<JESUS>\u201CYou
        are right.\u201D</JESUS> Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CI was born a King, and
        I have come into this world to prove what truth really is. And everyone who
        loves the truth</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>will receive my words.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 18:37
        content: "  Or \u201Ceveryone who is not deaf to the truth.\u201D The Aramaic
          is \u201Ceveryone who came from the truth.\u201D    "
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Pilate looked at Jesus and said, \u201CWhat is truth?\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]As
        silence filled the room, Pilate went back out to where the Jewish leaders
        were waiting and said to them, \u201CHe\u2019s not guilty. I couldn\u2019t
        even find one fault with him.   "
      comments:
      - number: 18:38
        content: "  The Aramaic could be translated \u201CWho is truth?\u201D or
          \u201CWho is the true prince?\u201D This skepticism is still voiced today
          in postmodernism.      As translated from the Aramaic.    "
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Now, you do know that we have a custom that I release one prisoner
        every year at Passover\u2014shall I release your king\u2014the king of the
        Jews?\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 18:39
        content: '  Pilate was not a saint. He was considered to be a corrupt and
          violent leader who would execute people without a trial. (Philo,  , ed.
          Mangey, ii.590). He stole money from the temple treasury and brought pagan
          statues into Jerusalem, which caused riots and death to many. It was reported
          by the church father Eusebius (. ii 7) that he was later banished to Vienna
          in Gaul, where he committed suicide.    '
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "They shouted out over and over, \u201CNo, not him! Give us Barabbas!\u201D
        [[COMMENT(0)]] (Now Barabbas was a robber and a troublemaker.)"
      comments:
      - number: 18:40
        content: "  Barabbas is an Aramaic name that means \u201Cson of the father.\u201D
          He becomes a picture of every son of Adam, our father. Some believe this
          is a figure of speech, a nickname for one who has no known father, an illegitimate
          son. Both in Greek and Aramaic the word for \u201Cthief\u201D or \u201Crobber\u201D
          can also mean \u201Cone who leads an insurrection.\u201D  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Is Flogged'
      title: Jesus Is Flogged
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Pilate ordered Jesus to be brutally beaten with a whip of leather
        straps embedded with metal. [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 19:1
        content: "  This leather whip, embedded with sharpened pieces of bone and
          metal, was known as \u201Cthe scorpion.\u201D Historians record that many
          people never survived this cruel flogging. The whips were known to break
          open the flesh and cut through muscle and sinew all the way to the bone.
          It was his love for you that enabled him to endure such treatment.    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the soldiers also wove thorn-branches into a crown and set it
        on his head and placed a purple [[COMMENT(0)]] robe over his shoulders. '
      comments:
      - number: 19:2
        content: "  The color purple has long symbolized royalty. Purple\u2019s elite
          status stems from the rarity and cost of the dye originally used to produce
          it. Jesus is the true king for all eternity.    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then, one by one, they came in front of him to mock him by saying,
        \u201CHail, to the king of the Jews!\u201D And one after the other, they
        repeatedly punched him in the face. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 19:3
        content: "  Or \u201Cthey slapped his face\u201D (Aramaic). He turned the
          other cheek and they slapped him on both sides of his face. See  .    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Once more Pilate went out and said to the Jewish officials, \u201CI
        will bring him out once more so that you know that I\u2019ve found nothing
        wrong with him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So when Jesus emerged, bleeding, wearing the purple robe and the
        crown of thorns on his head, Pilate said to them, \u201CLook at him! Here
        is your man!\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 19:5
        content: '  See  .    '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "No sooner did the high priests and the temple guards see Jesus that
        they all shouted in a frenzy, \u201CCrucify him! Crucify him!\u201DPilate
        replied, \u201CYou take him then and nail him to a cross yourselves! I told
        you\u2014he\u2019s not guilty! I find no reason to condemn him.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The Jewish leaders shouted back, \u201CBut we have the Law! And according
        to our Law, he must die, [[COMMENT(0)]] because he claimed to be the Son
        of God!\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 19:7
        content: '  They are most likely referring to  .    '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then Pilate was greatly alarmed [[COMMENT(0)]] when he heard that
        Jesus claimed to be the Son of God! '
      comments:
      - number: 19:8
        content: "  The Aramaic is \u201Chis soul collapsed!\u201D    "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So he took Jesus back inside and said to him, \u201CWhere have you
        come from?\u201D But once again, silence filled the room. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Perplexed, Pilate said, \u201CAre you going to play deaf? Don\u2019t
        you know that I have the power to grant you your freedom or nail you to a
        tree?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Jesus answered, <JESUS>\u201CYou would have no power over me at all,
        unless it was given to you from above. This is why the one who betrayed</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>me is guilty of an even greater sin.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 19:11
        content: "  Or \u201Chanded me over.\u201D This is the same Greek verb translated
          \u201Cbetray\u201D in  . It would obviously point to Judas. However, some
          expositors believe it was Caiaphas who handed over Jesus to Pilate, and
          is referred to here. But in fact, it was the evil spirits of darkness who
          were controlling Pilate and moving in the hearts of all involved to crucify
          Jesus. These dark powers would be the ones to experience the tremendous
          judgment unleashed on them by the power of the cross and resurrection.    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "From then on Pilate tried to find a way out of the situation and
        to set him free, but the Jewish authorities shouted him down: \u201CIf you
        let this man go, you\u2019re no friend of Caesar! Anyone who declares himself
        a king is an enemy of the emperor!\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 19:12
        content: "  In essence, these words were a form of blackmail as the Jewish
          authorities were reminding Pilate that it would ruin his career if he pardoned
          Jesus. The term \u201Cfriend of Caesar\u201D was an honorific title given
          only to the ruling wealthy class of Romans who would have access to the
          emperor\u2019s court. Many of these friends of Caesar were senators and
          members of the Equestrian Order, known also as the Knights. Pilate\u2019s
          position was a political appointment due to his being a member of this
          elite class of Romans who took an oath of loyalty to Caesar. They were,
          in effect, threatening to inform Rome that Pilate was allowing treason
          in Caesar\u2019s empire. As one historian remarked, \u201COne false move
          and his appointment would be cancelled and his career finished\u201D (P.
          Barnett,  , Illinois: InterVarsity, 1999, p. 147). This overruled Pilate\u2019s
          desire to set Jesus free. He went on to condemn him to death. To place
          your career over Jesus is never wise.    "
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So when Pilate heard this threat, he relented and had Jesus, who
        was torn and bleeding, brought outside. Then he went up the elevated stone
        platform and took his seat on the judgment bench\u2014which in Aramaic is
        called Gabbatha, [[COMMENT(0)]] or \u201CThe Bench.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: 19:13
        content: "    is an Aramaic compound word meaning \u201Con the side of the
          house\u201D (, \u201Con the side,\u201D and  , \u201Cthe house\u201D).
          This would be a stone bench that was used by Pilate to issue sentence.
          See  ;  .    "
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And it was now almost noon. And it was the same day they were preparing
        to slay the Passover lambs. [[COMMENT(0)]]Then Pilate said to the Jewish
        officials, \u201CLook! Here is your king!\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 19:14
        content: "  Jesus, our Passover Lamb, would be crucified at the very moment
          Jewish priests were slaughtering lambs in the temple. See  . Because there
          were so many lambs to be killed, the priesthood in that day extended the
          time of slaughter from noon to twilight\u2014the very hours Jesus was on
          the cross.    "
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But they screamed out, \u201CTake him away! Take him away and crucify
        him!\u201DPilate replied, \u201CShall I nail your king to a cross?\u201DThe
        high priests answered, \u201CWe have no other king but Caesar!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Jesus Is Crucified'
      title: Jesus Is Crucified
      number: 16
      content: Then Pilate handed Jesus over to them. So the soldiers seized him
        and took him away to be crucified.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Jesus carried his own cross out of the city to the place called \u201CThe
        Skull,\u201D which in Aramaic is Golgotha. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And there they nailed him to the cross. He was crucified, along with
        two others, one on each side with Jesus in the middle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19-20: '
      title: 
      number: 19-20
      content: "Pilate had them post a sign over the cross, which was written in
        three languages\u2014Aramaic, Latin, and Greek. Many of the people of Jerusalem
        read the sign, for he was crucified near the city. The sign stated: \u201CJesus
        of Nazareth, the King of the Jews.\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>  </smallcaps><smallcaps>.\u201D
        No wonder the chief priests were so offended by this sign and insisted that
        Pilate change it. This was a sign given to Israel, for over Jesus\u2019 head
        on the cross was written, Y-H-W-H! God, the Savior, bled to death for you.</smallcaps>"
      comments:
      - number: "19:19\u201320"
        content: "  Aramaic was the language of the common people in Israel. Hebrew
          ceased to be their spoken language after 450 BC, after the Jews returned
          from Babylon. Aramaic remained the language of Israel for nearly one thousand
          years. Latin was the official language of the Roman Empire. The inscription
          was also in Greek, for the Alexandrian Jews who had come to observe the
          Passover in Jerusalem would be unable to read Aramaic. The words were,
          \u201CJesus, the Nazarene, King of the Jews.\u201D The first letters of
          each of the four words written on the sign in Aramaic (Hebrew) were: Y-H-W-H
          (). To write these letters,  (also known as the tetragrammaton), was the
          Hebrew form of writing the sacred name \u201C    "
    - name: '19-20: '
      title: 
      number: 19-20
      content: "Pilate had them post a sign over the cross, which was written in
        three languages\u2014Aramaic, Latin, and Greek. Many of the people of Jerusalem
        read the sign, for he was crucified near the city. The sign stated: \u201CJesus
        of Nazareth, the King of the Jews.\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>  </smallcaps><smallcaps>.\u201D
        No wonder the chief priests were so offended by this sign and insisted that
        Pilate change it. This was a sign given to Israel, for over Jesus\u2019 head
        on the cross was written, Y-H-W-H! God, the Savior, bled to death for you.</smallcaps>"
      comments:
      - number: "19:19\u201320"
        content: "  Aramaic was the language of the common people in Israel. Hebrew
          ceased to be their spoken language after 450 BC, after the Jews returned
          from Babylon. Aramaic remained the language of Israel for nearly one thousand
          years. Latin was the official language of the Roman Empire. The inscription
          was also in Greek, for the Alexandrian Jews who had come to observe the
          Passover in Jerusalem would be unable to read Aramaic. The words were,
          \u201CJesus, the Nazarene, King of the Jews.\u201D The first letters of
          each of the four words written on the sign in Aramaic (Hebrew) were: Y-H-W-H
          (). To write these letters,  (also known as the tetragrammaton), was the
          Hebrew form of writing the sacred name \u201C    "
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But the chief priests of the Jews [[COMMENT(0)]] said to Pilate,
        \u201CYou must change the sign! Don\u2019t let it say, \u2018King of the
        Jews,\u2019 but rather\u2014\u2018he claimed to be the King of the Jews!\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: 19:21
        content: "  There is obvious irony in the Greek text of these two phrases,
          \u201CKing of the Jews\u201D and \u201Cthe chief priests of the Jews.\u201D
          This is the only place John describes the priests in this way.    "
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Pilate responded, \u201CWhat I have written will remain!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Now when the soldiers crucified Jesus, they divided up his clothes
        into four shares, one for each of them. But his tunic was seamless, woven
        from the top to the bottom [[COMMENT(0)]] as a single garment. '
      comments:
      - number: 19:23
        content: "  The Aramaic could be translated \u201Chis tunic was entirely
          woven from above.\u201D Jesus\u2019 tunic was an emblem of his perfect
          holiness and righteousness as one who came \u201Cfrom above.\u201D As believers,
          we are now robed in that seamless garment of righteousness in Christ. They
          stripped the robe from Jesus and gambled over it at the cross. Many people
          are still gambling over their eternal souls\u2014while others receive freely
          the blood-stained, seamless robe of perfect righteousness. Jesus was unclothed
          so that we could be robed in his glory.    "
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "So the soldiers said to each other, \u201CDon\u2019t tear it\u2014let\u2019s
        throw dice [[COMMENT(0)]] to see who gets it!\u201D The soldiers did all
        of this not knowing they fulfilled the Scripture that says, \u201CThey divided
        my garments among them and gambled for my clothing.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: 19:24
        content: "  Or \u201Ccast lots.\u201D See also v.  .      See  .    "
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Mary, Jesus\u2019 mother, was standing next to his cross, along with
        Mary\u2019s sister, Mary the wife of Clopas, and Mary Magdalene. [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 19:25
        content: "  Many scholars believe that Mary\u2019s sister (Jesus\u2019 aunt)
          was Salome. This would mean she was the wife of Zebedee and the mother
          of Jacob (James) and John (the writer of the Gospel of John). Furthermore,
          that would mean that Jacob (James) and John were cousins of Jesus. See
          also  ;  .    "
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "So when Jesus looked down and saw the disciple he loved standing
        with her, he said, <JESUS>\u201CMother,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>look\u2014John</JESUS>   
        <JESUS>will be a son to you.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 19:26
        content: "  Or \u201Cwoman.\u201D      Although unnamed, this was most certainly
          John the apostle. John, the apostle of love, was the only one of the Twelve
          who stood near the cross and witnessed the crucifixion. Love doesn\u2019t
          quit, run away, or hide from pain. It endures all things, overcomes all
          things, and empowers us in all things. John didn\u2019t run from the suffering
          of the Savior. We must be those who will stand next to Jesus even if the
          entire world is against us.    "
    - name: "27: Jesus\u2019 Death on the Cross"
      title: "Jesus\u2019 Death on the Cross"
      number: 27
      content: "Then he said, <JESUS>\u201C</JESUS><JESUS>John,</JESUS>  <JESUS>look\u2014she
        will be a mother to you!\u201D</JESUS> From that day on, John accepted Mary
        into his home as one of his own family. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 19:27
        content: '  Mary would be nearly fifty years old and a widow. What tenderness
          we see with Jesus toward his mother! Moments before his death, Jesus thought
          about Mary and her long journey back to Nazareth and that no one would
          be there to provide for her. Jesus deeply honored his mother.    '
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Jesus knew that his mission was accomplished, and to fulfill the
        Scripture, [[COMMENT(0)]] Jesus said: <JESUS>\u201CI am thirsty.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 19:28
        content: '  See  ;  . The Fountain of Living Water now thirsts for the souls
          of men and women to come to him. He thirsts for your friendship.    '
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'A jar of sour wine was sitting nearby, so they soaked a sponge with
        it and put it on the stalk of hyssop [[COMMENT(0)]] and raised it to his
        lips. '
      comments:
      - number: 19:29
        content: "  The hyssop branch points to the sacrificial death of Jesus. Hyssop
          is first mentioned in    in reference to the application of lamb\u2019s
          blood upon the door posts of the homes of the Hebrews the night of Passover.
          Hyssop was also used for the cleansing of lepers and points to the cleansing
          of our souls that happened when Jesus was crucified for sinners (spiritual
          lepers). See  ;  .    "
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "When he had sipped the sour wine, he said, <JESUS>\u201CIt is finished,
        my bride!\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] Then he bowed his head and surrendered
        his spirit to God."
      comments:
      - number: 19:30
        content: "  This is from the Hebrew word  , which has a homonym that means
          \u201Cfulfilled [completed]\u201D and \u201Cbride.\u201D Jesus finished
          the work of our salvation for his bride. This translation has combined
          both concepts. For a fascinating study of the Hebrew word used for \u201Cbride\u201D
          and \u201Cfinished,\u201D with its universe of meaning, see  , Hb. 3615,
          3616, 3617, 3618, and 3634. Although the completed work of salvation was
          finished on the cross, he continues to work through his church today to
          extend God\u2019s kingdom realm on the earth and glorify the Father through
          us. He continues to work in us to accomplish all that his cross and resurrection
          have purchased for us, his bride. His cross fulfilled and finished the
          prophecies of the Messiah\u2019s first coming to the earth. There was nothing
          written that was not fulfilled and now offered to his bride.    "
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "The Jewish leaders did not want the bodies of the victims to remain
        on the cross through the next day, since it was the day of preparation [[COMMENT(0)]]
        for a very important Sabbath. So they asked Pilate\u2019s permission to have
        the victims\u2019 legs broken to hasten their death   and their bodies taken
        down before sunset. "
      comments:
      - number: 19:31
        content: "  The Aramaic is \u201Cbecause it was Friday.\u201D      Breaking
          his legs would prevent the one on a cross from lifting himself up and taking
          a deep breath. The victim would die sooner by suffocation. The Roman practice
          was to leave the bodies of the victims on the cross for a day or more as
          a warning to others. See  .    "
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'So the soldiers broke the legs of the two men who were nailed there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'But when they came to Jesus, they realized that he had already died,
        so they decided not to break his legs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "But one of the soldiers [[COMMENT(0)]] took a spear and pierced Jesus\u2019
        side, and blood and water gushed out. "
      comments:
      - number: 19:34
        content: "  Although unverifiable, church tradition indentifies the soldier
          to be Longinus, who later converted to Christ. One tradition holds to the
          belief that he was a Roman centurion suffering from an eye problem or blindness
          that was instantly healed when a drop of Jesus\u2019 blood fell into his
          eye. See Christopher Fuhrmann,    (Oxford University Press, reprint ed.,
          2014) 231; Malcolm Godwin,    (Viking Penguin, 1994), 51.      This becomes
          a picture of the cleansing by blood and the water of the Holy Spirit. However,
          water and blood both come forth when a baby is born. Christ gave birth
          on the cross to \u201Csons.\u201D He is the everlasting Father (), and
          you must have children to be a Father. We are all born again by the wounded
          side of Jesus Christ. He not only died for his bride, but he also gave
          birth to her at the cross.    "
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: '(I, John, [[COMMENT(0)]] do testify to the certainty of what took
        place, and I write the truth so that you might also believe.) '
      comments:
      - number: 19:35
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe person who saw this.\u201D Although unnamed, it
          was John, the author of this narrative, who witnessed and testified to
          the truth of what happened.    "
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "For all these things happened to fulfill the prophecies of the Scriptures:\u201CNot
        one of his bones will be broken,\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 19:36
        content: '  See  ;  .    '
    - name: "37: Jesus\u2019 Burial"
      title: "Jesus\u2019 Burial"
      number: 37
      content: "and, \u201CThey will gaze on the one they have pierced!\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 19:37
        content: '  See  .    '
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'After this, Joseph from the city of Ramah, [[COMMENT(0)]] who was
        a secret disciple of Jesus for fear of the Jewish authorities, asked Pilate
        if he could remove the body of Jesus. So Pilate granted him permission to
        remove the body from the cross. '
      comments:
      - number: 19:38
        content: "  As translated from the Aramaic. Or    (Greek), which means \u201Cheights.\u201D
          This was the likely birthplace of the prophet Samuel. Keep in mind that
          Joseph may have lost a son the age of Jesus when Herod killed all the babies.    "
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Now Nicodemus, who had once come to Jesus privately at night, accompanied
        Joseph, and together they carried a significant amount [[COMMENT(0)]] of
        myrrh and aloes to the cross. '
      comments:
      - number: 19:39
        content: "  Or \u201Capproximately one hundred pounds.\u201D Some calculate
          this as Roman pounds weighing thirty kilograms. Others interpret the one
          hundred pounds to be closer to a liter, or less than one kilogram, which
          seems more appropriate considering the cost and weight of these valuable
          spices.    "
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Then they took Jesus\u2019 body and wrapped it in strips of linen
        with the embalming spices [[COMMENT(0)]] according to the Jewish burial customs. "
      comments:
      - number: 19:40
        content: '  This was the myrrh and aloes, which were embalming spices.    '
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Near the place where Jesus was crucified was a garden, and in the
        garden there was a new tomb where no one had yet been laid to rest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "And because the Sabbath was approaching, and the tomb was nearby,
        that\u2019s where they laid the body of Jesus. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 19:42
        content: "  See  . Jesus\u2019 body was laid on a bed of spices in a garden
          tomb. Death came upon the first Adam in the garden of Eden, but eternal
          life surged through the last Adam in the garden of the cross and his tomb.
          Man fell in a garden, but man now finds life in that empty garden tomb.  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Empty Tomb'
      title: The Empty Tomb
      number: 1
      content: 'Very early Sunday morning, [[COMMENT(0)]] before sunrise, Mary Magdalene
        made her way to the tomb. And when she arrived she discovered that the stone
        that sealed the entrance to the tomb was moved away! '
      comments:
      - number: 20:1
        content: "  Or \u201COn the first day of the week.\u201D    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So she went running as fast as she could to go tell Peter and the
        other disciple, the one Jesus loved. [[COMMENT(0)]] She told them, \u201CThey\u2019ve
        taken the Lord\u2019s body from the tomb, and we don\u2019t know where he
        is!\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 20:2
        content: '  This was obviously John the apostle, the author of this Gospel.    '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then Peter and the other disciple jumped up and ran to the tomb to
        go see for themselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They started out together, but the other disciple outran Peter and
        reached the tomb first. [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 20:4
        content: "  How did John outrun Peter to the tomb? Love will always \u201Coutrun\u201D
          curiosity. Some are simply curious to know Jesus, but we must be those
          who are passionate to experience his love and power.    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "He didn\u2019t enter the tomb, but peeked in, and saw only the linen
        cloths lying there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then Peter came behind him and went right into the tomb. He too noticed
        the linen cloths lying there, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "but the burial cloth that had been on Jesus\u2019 head had been rolled
        up and placed separate from the other cloths."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then the other disciple who had reached the tomb first went in, and
        after one look, he believed! [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 20:8
        content: '  It was lovers of Jesus that were the first to realize the resurrection
          of Christ. What did John see that caused him to believe? Perhaps it was
          the linen burial cloths that had not been unwrapped, but simply were empty.
          And the cloth that had been wrapped around his head was rolled up and placed
          aside. Jesus left everything pertaining to the old creation in the tomb,
          signified by the linen cloths and handkerchief left behind.    '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "For until then they hadn\u2019t understood the Scriptures that prophesied
        [[COMMENT(0)]] that he was destined to rise from the dead.   "
      comments:
      - number: 20:9
        content: '  Some of these prophecies would include  ;  ;  ;  ;  .      As
          translated from the Aramaic.    '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Puzzled, Peter and the other disciple then left and went back to their
        homes.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Mary arrived back at the tomb, broken and sobbing. She stooped to
        peer inside, and through her tears '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "she saw two angels in dazzling white robes, sitting where Jesus\u2019
        body had been laid\u2014one at the head and one at the feet! [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 20:12
        content: "  This becomes a picture of the two golden cherubim engraved on
          the mercy seat, peering down into the treasures of grace. The empty tomb
          has become our \u201Cmercy seat.\u201D    "
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CDear woman, why are you crying?\u201D they asked.Mary answered,
        \u201CThey have taken away my Lord, and I don\u2019t know where they\u2019ve
        laid him.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then she turned around to leave, and there was Jesus standing in
        front of her, but she didn\u2019t realize that it was him!"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "He said to her, <JESUS>\u201CDear woman, why are you crying? Who
        are you looking for?\u201D</JESUS>Mary answered, thinking he was only the
        gardener, \u201CSir, if you have taken his body somewhere else, tell me,
        and I will go and&nbsp;.&nbsp;.&nbsp;.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CMary,\u201D</JESUS> Jesus interrupted her.Turning to
        face him, she said, \u201CRabboni!\u201D (Aramaic for \u201CMy teacher!\u201D)"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Jesus cautioned her, <JESUS>\u201CMary, don\u2019t cling to me,</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>for I haven\u2019t yet ascended to God, my Father.
        And he\u2019s not only my Father and God, but now he\u2019s your Father and
        your God! Now go to my brothers</JESUS>    <JESUS>and tell them what I\u2019ve
        told you, that I am ascending to my Father\u2014and your Father, to my God\u2014and
        your God!\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments:
      - number: 20:17
        content: "  Jesus was telling Mary, \u201CDon\u2019t cling to me in the way
          you once knew me, now we are one. Cling to me in my ascension, in my glory.\u201D
          We don\u2019t cling to a memory of Christ, we cling to the majesty in his
          glory today.      This is the first time in John\u2019s Gospel that Jesus
          called his disciples \u201Cbrothers.\u201D See  .    "
    - name: '18: Jesus Appears to His Disciples'
      title: Jesus Appears to His Disciples
      number: 18
      content: "Then Mary Magdalene left to inform the disciples of her encounter
        with Jesus. \u201CI have seen the Lord!\u201D she told them. And she gave
        them his message."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "That evening, [[COMMENT(0)]] the disciples gathered together, and
        because they were afraid of reprisals from the Jewish leaders, they had locked
        the doors. But suddenly Jesus appeared among them and said,   <JESUS>\u201CPeace
        to you!\u201D</JESUS>    "
      comments:
      - number: 20:19
        content: "  Or \u201CThat Sunday evening.\u201D      Or \u201Ccame and stood
          among them.\u201D      This is the idiomatic equivalent of saying, \u201CHello,
          everyone!\u201D    "
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then he showed them the wounds of his hands and his side\u2014they
        were overjoyed to see the Lord with their own eyes!"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Jesus repeated his greeting, <JESUS>\u201CPeace to you!\u201D</JESUS>
        And he told them, <JESUS>\u201CJust as the Father has sent me, I\u2019m now
        sending you.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then, taking a deep breath, he blew [[COMMENT(0)]] on them and said,
        <JESUS>\u201CReceive the Holy Spirit.</JESUS>    "
      comments:
      - number: 20:22
        content: "  The Greek word used here does not appear elsewhere in the New
          Testament; however, it is the same word found in the Septuagint for when
          God \u201Cbreathed\u201D into Adam\u2019s nostrils the breath of life ().
          The beginning of new creation life came from the breath of Jesus. The mighty
          wind of    was for power, the breath Jesus breathed into his disciples
          in this verse was for life.      Or \u201Caccept the Sacred Breath.\u201D    "
    - name: '23: Jesus Appears to Thomas'
      title: Jesus Appears to Thomas
      number: 23
      content: "<JESUS>I send you to preach the forgiveness</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        <JESUS>of sins\u2014and people\u2019s sins will be forgiven. But if you don\u2019t
        proclaim the forgiveness of their sins, they will remain guilty.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 20:23
        content: "  Or \u201Cremoval, acquittal.\u201D      Or \u201CIf you forgive
          someone for their sins, their sins will be discharged, but if you retain
          their sins, their sins will be retained.\u201D Jesus was not giving absolute
          authority to forgive the guilt of sins, for God alone has that right (),
          and the apostles at no time assumed that authority. What he gave them,
          in the context of being his sent ones, was the authority to proclaim the
          gospel to the nations. If they refused to go and preach the good news,
          then people would have no opportunity to believe it. See  ;  .    "
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "One of the twelve wasn\u2019t present when Jesus appeared to them\u2014it
        was Thomas, whose nickname was \u201Cthe Twin.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "So the disciples informed him, \u201CWe have seen the Lord with our
        own eyes!\u201DStill unconvinced, Thomas replied, \u201CThere\u2019s no way
        I\u2019m going to believe this unless I personally see the wounds of the
        nails [[COMMENT(0)]] in his hands, touch them with my finger, and put my
        hand into the wound of his side where he was pierced!\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 20:25
        content: "  The Aramaic is \u201Cthe blossom of the nails.\u201D You can
          imagine a wide nail head that, when struck with a heavy mallet, \u201Cblossomed\u201D
          over the sacred palm of our Lord Jesus. The wound of the nail had imprinted
          his entire palm. His wounds are like beautiful flowers to the lovers of
          God.    "
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then eight days later, Thomas and all the others were in the house
        together. And even though all the doors were locked, Jesus suddenly stood
        before them! <JESUS>\u201CPeace to you,\u201D</JESUS> he said."
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then, looking into Thomas\u2019 eyes, he said, <JESUS>\u201CPut your
        finger here in the wounds of my hands. Here\u2014put your hand into my wounded
        side and see for yourself. Thomas, don\u2019t give in to your doubts any
        longer, just believe!\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then the words spilled out of his heart\u2014\u201CYou are my Lord,
        and you are my God!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Jesus responded, <JESUS>\u201CThomas, now that you\u2019ve seen me,
        you believe. But there are those who have never seen me with their eyes but
        have believed in me with their hearts, and they will be blessed even more!\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Jesus went on to do many more miraculous signs in the presence of
        his disciples, which are not even included in this book. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: But all that is recorded here is so that you will fully believe [[COMMENT(0)]]
        that Jesus is the Anointed One, the Son of God, and that through your faith
        in him you will experience eternal life  by the power of his name!
      comments:
      - number: 20:31
        content: "  Or \u201Cnever stop believing.\u201D      As translated from
          the Aramaic.  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Appears at Lake Galilee'
      title: Jesus Appears at Lake Galilee
      number: 1
      content: 'Later, Jesus appeared once again to a group of his disciples by Lake
        Galilee. [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 21:1
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe Sea of Tiberias.\u201D    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'It happened one day while Peter, Thomas (the Twin), Nathanael (from
        Cana in Galilee), Jacob, John, [[COMMENT(0)]] and two other disciples were
        all together. '
      comments:
      - number: 21:2
        content: "  Or in place of Jacob (James) and John, \u201Cthe sons of Zebedee.\u201D    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Peter told them, \u201CI\u2019m going fishing.\u201D And they all
        replied, \u201CWe\u2019ll go with you.\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]] So they went
        out and fished through the night, but caught nothing."
      comments:
      - number: 21:3
        content: '  According to  , the disciples were told to wait in Jerusalem
          for the day they would be clothed with power. These seven apostles were
          not following what they had been told, and for this reason they caught
          nothing until Jesus joined them. He became the eighth man.    '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then at dawn, Jesus was standing there on the shore, but the disciples
        didn\u2019t realize that it was him! "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "He called out to them, saying, <JESUS>\u201CHey guys! Did you catch
        any fish?\u201D</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]\u201CNot a thing,\u201D they replied."
      comments:
      - number: 21:5
        content: "  Or \u201CHave you caught anything to eat?\u201D    "
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Jesus shouted to them, <JESUS>\u201CThrow your net over the starboard
        side, and you\u2019ll catch some!\u201D</JESUS> And so they did as he said,
        and they caught so many fish they couldn\u2019t even pull in the net!"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then the disciple whom Jesus loved said to Peter, \u201CIt\u2019s
        the Lord!\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]] When Peter heard him say that, he quickly
        wrapped his outer garment around him, and because he was athletic,  he dove
        right into the lake to go to Jesus! "
      comments:
      - number: 21:7
        content: "  It was John, the one whom Jesus loved, that recognized the voice
          of Jesus. Perhaps it was Peter\u2019s discouragement that prevented him
          from recognizing the voice of the Master. Peter\u2019s name was Simon (Hb. 
          ), which means \u201Che who hears.\u201D Our hearing his voice is hindered
          when we are confused and filled with doubts.      As translated from the
          Aramaic. The Greek is literally \u201Cbecause he was naked.\u201D This
          is very strange and most expositors make quite a case for this not being
          the case, in spite of the Greek saying he was, indeed, naked. The problem
          is solved by the Aramaic, which says, \u201Cbecause Peter was athletic,
          he dove into the water.\u201D    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The other disciples then brought the boat to shore, dragging their
        catch of fish. They weren\u2019t far from land, only about a hundred meters. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And when they got to shore, they noticed a charcoal fire with some
        roasted fish and bread. [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 21:9
        content: '  It was while standing next to a fire that Peter denied Christ;
          now standing next to a fire, Jesus would restore his beloved friend.    '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Jesus said, <JESUS>\u201CBring some of the fish you just caught.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: So Peter waded into the water and helped pull the net to shore. It
        was full of many large fish, exactly one hundred and fifty-three, [[COMMENT(0)]]
        but even with so many fish, the net was not torn.
      comments:
      - number: 21:11
        content: '  This speaks of the great redemption of Christ for all nations
          and all people. One hundred and fifty-three large fish points to a mighty
          harvest from among the people groups of the world. This great catch of
          fish begins the process of inner healing for Peter and the guilt of his
          denial of Christ. Peter began to follow Jesus because of a great catch
          of fish (), so Jesus now repeated that miracle, inviting Peter to begin
          to follow him again. According to the early church father Jerome, there
          were 153 species of fish in Lake Galilee that would remind Peter of his
          original call to be a fisher of men.    '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "<JESUS>\u201CCome, let\u2019s have some breakfast,\u201D</JESUS>
        Jesus said to them.And not one of the disciples needed to ask who it was,
        because every one of them knew it was the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then Jesus came close to them and served them the bread and the fish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Jesus Restores Peter'
      title: Jesus Restores Peter
      number: 14
      content: This was the third time Jesus appeared to his disciples after his
        resurrection.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "After they had breakfast, Jesus said to Peter, <JESUS>\u201CSimon,
        son of Jonah,</JESUS>  [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>do you burn with love</JESUS>   
        <JESUS>for me more than these?\u201D</JESUS>  Peter answered, \u201CYes,
        Lord! You know that I have great affection for you!\u201D<JESUS>\u201CThen
        take care of my lambs,\u201D</JESUS>   Jesus said."
      comments:
      - number: 21:15
        content: "  Jesus called Peter \u201CSimon, son of Jonah\u201D because Jonah
          was the prophet who ran from his calling, but was supernaturally restored.
          So Peter had followed Jonah\u2019s example, by denying Jesus and running
          away. Yet Jesus now stood before him to fully restore him and heal his
          heart. See also vv.  ,  .      The Aramaic word for \u201Clove\u201D is 
          , and is taken from a root word that means \u201Cto set on fire.\u201D
          This was the word Jesus would have used to ask Peter, \u201CDo you burn
          with love for me?\u201D Our love for Jesus must be passionate and kindle
          a holy flame within our hearts. See  .      As often is the case, Jesus\u2019
          words have more than one meaning. \u201CThese\u201D can refer to the fish
          they had just caught, for Peter was a fisherman and loved to fish. He may
          have been counting and sorting the fish when Jesus asked him that question.
          But \u201Cthese\u201D most likely refers to the other disciples. It was
          Peter\u2019s boast that he loved Jesus more than the others, and though
          everyone else would leave him, Peter never would. That boast proved empty,
          as within hours of making the claim, Peter denied he even knew Jesus three
          times. So Jesus asked Peter three times if he loved him. In essence, Jesus
          knew how to bring healing to Peter and remove the pain of his denial. Three
          times Peter denied Jesus, but three times he made his confession of his
          deep love for Christ. By the third time, the \u201Ccrowing rooster\u201D
          inside Peter had been silenced, and now he was ready to be a shepherd for
          Jesus\u2019 flock.      The Aramaic is \u201Cfeed my rams\u201D (male lambs).
          This may refer to the other disciples. In v.    the Aramaic is simply \u201Csheep.\u201D
          And in v.    in Aramaic, Jesus used the third term \u201Cewes\u201D (female
          lambs). Some see in these that Peter was symbolically given charge of three
          flocks: Jews, Samaritans, and gentiles. Regardless, men and women need
          to be cared for and fed by the leadership of Christ\u2019s church among
          the nations.    "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Jesus repeated his question the second time, <JESUS>\u201CSimon,
        son of Jonah, do you burn with love for me?\u201D</JESUS>Peter answered,
        \u201CYes, my Lord! You know that I have great affection for you!\u201D<JESUS>\u201CThen
        take care of my sheep,\u201D</JESUS> Jesus said."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Jesus asked him again, <JESUS>\u201CPeter, son of Jonah, do
        you have great affection for me?\u201D</JESUS>Peter was saddened by being
        asked the third time [[COMMENT(0)]] and said, \u201CMy Lord, you know everything.
        You know that I burn with love for you!\u201DJesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CThen
        feed my lambs!</JESUS>  "
      comments:
      - number: 21:17
        content: '  Three times Peter denied Christ, so Jesus gave him three opportunities
          to redeem himself.    '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "<JESUS>Peter, listen, when you were younger you made your own choices</JESUS> 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  <JESUS>and you went where you pleased. But one day when you
        are old,</JESUS>    <JESUS>others will tie you up and escort you where you
        would not choose to go\u2014and you will spread out your arms.\u201D</JESUS>    "
      comments:
      - number: 21:18
        content: "  Or \u201Cyou girded yourself.\u201D      The Aramaic is \u201Cgrayheaded.\u201D     
          Or \u201Cstretch out your hands.\u201D This was clearly a hint of the martyrdom
          Peter would experience in Rome one day, where historians have recorded
          that Peter was crucified upside down, at his request, because he said that
          he was unworthy to be crucified in the same way as his Lord. He once said
          he was willing to die for our Lord Jesus; here Christ promised that would
          happen.    "
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "(Jesus said this to Peter as a prophecy of what kind of death he
        would die, for the glory of God.) And then he said, <JESUS>\u201CPeter, follow
        me!\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Peter turned and saw that the disciple whom Jesus loved was
        following them. (This was the disciple who sat close to Jesus at the Last
        Supper and had asked him, \u201CLord, who is the one that will betray you?\u201D) "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "So when Peter saw him, he asked Jesus, \u201CWhat\u2019s going to
        happen to him?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Jesus replied, <JESUS>\u201CIf I decide to let him live until I return,
        what concern is that of yours? You must still keep on following me!\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Conclusion'
      title: Conclusion
      number: 23
      content: "So the rumor started to circulate among the believers that this disciple
        wasn\u2019t going to die. But Jesus never said that, he only said, <JESUS>\u201CIf
        I let him live until I return, what concern is that of yours?\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "I, John, [[COMMENT(0)]] am that disciple who has written these things
        to testify of the truth, and we  know that what I\u2019ve documented is accurate. "
      comments:
      - number: 21:24
        content: '  The evidence both internally and externally clearly points to
          John as the author of this book, thus the explicit reference here.     
          The word    implies that John had conferred with the other disciples, as
          he has left us an accurate account of the life of Jesus Christ.    '
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Jesus did countless things that I haven\u2019t included here. And
        if every one of his works were written down and described one by one, [[COMMENT(0)]]
        I suppose that the world itself wouldn\u2019t have enough room to contain
        the books that would have to be written! "
      comments:
      - number: 21:25
        content: "  Implied in the Aramaic.      The Aramaic is very poetic: \u201CThe
          world itself would be emptied out into the books that would be written.\u201D
          An alternate translation of the Aramaic could read \u201CI suppose that
          forever is still not enough time for all the books to be written!\u201D  "
